INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9b786442-7e1e-4d66-997f-ea44e9e55220', '0f891c93-40e0-4d37-9df1-f34c91953f6d', 'matrix', 'Question 11-16', '', '<p>Label the plan below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A-H</strong>, next to questions <strong>11-16.</strong></p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="460" height="419" loading="lazy"></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Toilet block", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Shower block", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Tent site", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Cabins", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Barbecue area", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Bike trail", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 2: <span data-sheets-root=\"1\">Forest lake campsite</span></strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Organizer:</strong> Hello everyone and welcome to this orientation session prior to our camp next week. Thank you for coming along to find out what you and your children will be doing on this year’s camp. To start off with, let’s tell you a bit about the campsite itself so that you’ll be able to find your way around once you get there.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">Firstly, we’ll be arriving by bus into the car park, which if you look at the plan you have in front of you, you’ll see at the top of the picture on the left-hand side. Now, if you cross the road from the car park, the first building you’ll come to is the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"256\">(1) toilet block [Answer: A]</strong></span>. It’s been recently upgraded, so it’s very nice and clean in there now, with plenty of facilities.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">And built onto that—so this is across the road from the community hall—is the new <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">(2) shower block [Answer: C]</strong></span>. The hot water does run out occasionally, but usually there’s enough to cope with a group your size.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">If you now move to the bottom left of your map, among the pine trees, there is a special flat site set up for <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">(3) pitching tents [Answer: G]</strong></span>, with power points and outdoor taps for water.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Now let’s go back and move along the top of your map. There’s another area of Pine Forest, and then over on the far right-hand side, there’s a block of small <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">(4) cabins [Answer: D]</strong></span>. Note that this is different from the main accommodation block, which doesn’t appear on this map but is further over again to the right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Now let’s look down from there over the road, so we’re moving clockwise round your map. Okay, in this next block beside the flower beds, we have a lovely place for <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">(5) barbecues [Answer: F]</strong>,</span> where you can cook in the open air.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">What else to tell you about? Um, below the flower bed and across Lakeside Drive, you’ll see a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">(6) trail for mountain biking [Answer: H]</strong></span>, which is always a popular activity.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Moving on now, in the middle of the campsite, you’ll see the lake where you can canoe, and above that again the community hall. So that completes your introduction to the campsite. I hope you found that useful.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">WHAT TO BRING (Questions 7–8)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Organizer:</strong> Now let’s think about what you need to bring with you. I’m sure you’re all wondering what you need to pack.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">The lake is a bit cold for swimming at this time of year, so you can leave your togs out of the suitcase. While we’re on the subject of weather too, usually I recommend that campers bring sunblock with them, but I guess now that we’re into April, that too can be left behind.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">Ah, let me think… some campers like a torch, but actually the days are still so long that it’s light outside till quite late, and the blocks all have outside lighting now. So I’d say that a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"192\">(7-8) pair of earplugs [Answer: A]</strong></span> are more useful, as in my experience, a lot of talking goes on after lights out. But in April, if it’s wet, it can get muddy around the campsite, so to bring <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"385\">(7-8) boots [Answer: E]</strong></span> isn’t a bad idea.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">FINAL NIGHT CONCERT (Questions 9–10)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Organizer:</strong> Finally, can you all please prepare something for the final night concert? Bring your musical instruments or whatever else you need. You can’t have a camp without a good <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"181\">(9-10) sing-along [Answer: D – singing]</strong></span>; that’s our favourite activity.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\">Maybe you could recite a poem, act out a skit or charades for us if you’re brave enough to try that, or failing that, perhaps you can tell a joke or a funny story. But actually, people much prefer to see some <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"209\">(9-10) good dancing [Answer: B]</strong></span>. I look forward to seeing you all perform next week!</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f53e53da-4513-460d-9452-fb35b69d4624', '81e283d2-50cd-4767-880e-d3528cf9e72d', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21–22', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>points did students most frequently make about their musical background before staring a music degree?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A They had already composed music.", "correct": false}, {"option": "B They had several music qualifications", "correct": false}, {"option": "C They could play more than one instrument.", "correct": true}, {"option": "D They had performed in public.", "correct": true}, {"option": "E They had had piano lessons.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 3: <span data-sheets-root=\"1\">musical background</span></strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> So Gareth, we need to organise the findings from our survey on music students for the final presentation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Yes, Lona. I think we’ve got some very interesting results. Obviously, we need to start by saying that we interviewed all the third-year students doing a music degree and state the objective of our research project—that is to find out about their attitudes to performing.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> And then we should talk about the students’ musical backgrounds before coming to university. The most important points to make are that, although most people have actually composed music during the course, that wasn’t the case when they arrived.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> And the other thing they had in common was the piano. Well, they’d had access to a piano at some point, but not all had studied it formally. I thought the most interesting finding was that before coming here, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"217\">(21-22) almost everyone was involved in a chamber orchestra or band or singing in a choir and playing in front of live audiences [Answer: D – performed in public]</strong></span>, but varying enormously in size. Some had only played in tiny venues. I think it’s worth saying that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> OK, and as you might expect from people wanting to study music, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">(21-22) they all had a degree of proficiency in at least two instruments [Answer: C – play more than one instrument]</strong></span>, but in most cases, one of the instruments was dominant.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MUSIC PRACTICE (Questions 23–24)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Right, we need to talk about attitudes to music practice. The most striking thing here is that even students who you’d expect to practice for hours every day until they get it perfect, say <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">(23-24) it’s being terrified of failing that really makes them practice [Answer: C – motivated by fear]</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> I know, I’m the same!</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Me too. It’s interesting what was said about practicing alone; some people preferred that because they could focus more on their weak points, but that wasn’t a majority view. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"183\">(23-24) What most of them agree on is that there’s nothing more rewarding than mastering something that’s really hard to learn [Answer: E – enjoy the challenge of a difficult piece]</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> That’s right.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">ASSESSED PERFORMANCES (Questions 25–26)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> Okay, after that, we should talk a bit about the pieces that students select for assessed performances. There wasn’t quite so much consensus on this, was there? A few people prefer to do pieces which are relatively unknown, while others choose the ones they think will show off their technical ability, but they were in the minority.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Hmm, I think the first thing to say is that <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">(25-26) a high percentage said they would always try to learn their pieces by heart [Answer: C – play from memory]</strong></span> because it’s too easy to get lost if you’re trying to read and play when you’re nervous.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> Hmm, okay. And <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">(25-26) quite a lot of them said it helps to listen to other people playing your chosen piece [Answer: A – hear others performing the same pieces]</strong></span>, preferably recordings but even just other students.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">ASPECTS OF PERFORMANCE (Questions 27–30)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> So finally, we need to look at the findings for students’ attitudes to performing. We should point out that this includes informal and formal public performances as well as assessed ones.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Yes, that’s important. I expected to find that performing solo would make students very nervous, but in fact, that isn’t the case. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">(27) They do find it hugely challenging to start with, but they appreciate the challenge and find it stimulating [Answer: B – difficult but enjoyable (Performing solo)]</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> Right. I was surprised by what students said about deciding which pieces to perform. I thought they’d all say this was easy. For me, it’s always been quite straightforward—which pieces do I like best and which pieces can I play well? But <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"244\">(28) the most commonly cited answer was that it took them ages to make their minds up [Answer: E – time-consuming (Deciding pieces)]</strong></span>. I suppose it’s because there are so many factors involved—you need to consider your audience, the venue, the time available… you can’t do that in a hurry.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> That’s true. Then there’s performing with musicians from a different genre, like a classical musician playing with a jazz group. That could really be fun, but <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"167\">(29) most of the music students had never even considered it [Answer: G – happens infrequently (Different genre)]</strong></span></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> Right. For <strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"17\">performing with musicians who play the same instrument</strong>, almost everyone put the same thing.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Yes, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"13\">(30) they all said it was incredibly helpful [Answer: A – very beneficial (Same instrument)]</strong></span> and not at all intimidating, which says a lot for the department’s ethos.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> Yes, that’s a good point. OK, what I think we should sort out now is…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4e2c3581-2bf6-4061-8b89-e281d83880ac', 'c532d8cb-154b-4ae7-b02b-b619b2f0a930', 'fillup', 'Questions 8-13', '<p>Complete the table below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>THE DEVELOPMENT OF PAPER</strong></p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="width: 95.8146%; border-collapse: collapse; border: 1px solid #000000; height: 463.625px;" border="1">
<colgroup>
<col class="ql-align-center" style="width: 28.1717%;" width="189" />
<col class="ql-align-center" style="width: 15.5019%;" width="104" />
<col class="ql-align-center" style="width: 28.1717%;" width="189" />
<col class="ql-align-center" style="width: 28.1717%;" width="189" /></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 80.9688px;" data-row="1">
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="1" data-cell-bg="rgb(242, 242, 242)"><strong>Place</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="1" data-cell-bg="rgb(242, 242, 242)"><strong>Date of introduction</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="1" data-cell-bg="rgb(242, 242, 242)"><strong>Materials used</strong></td>
<td style="text-align: center; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="1" data-cell-bg="rgb(242, 242, 242)"><strong>Method of production</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 100.562px;" data-row="2">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="2" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">Egypt</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="2" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">about 2400 BC</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="2" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">a plant called papyrus</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="2" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)"><span class="input-inline2 numquest">{strips} </span>of the plant weresoftened in water, woven and pounded</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 100.562px;" data-row="3">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="3" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">Europe</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="3" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">unknown</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="3" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">parchment made from the skin of animals such as { sheep}</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="3" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">skin was dried and { stretched}</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 100.562px;" data-row="4">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="4" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">China</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="4" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">105 AD</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="4" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)"><span class="input-inline2 numquest">{Bark}</span> of a mulberrytree and hemp rags</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="4" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">ingredients were mixed with water, pressed and but outside in the sun</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 80.9688px;" data-row="5">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: center;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="5" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)"><span class="input-inline2 numquest">{Samarkand}</span></td>
