<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; text-align: left;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="5" data-cell-bg="rgb(255, 255, 255)">mills made of {Stone} used were</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>8. Egypt: Method of production (Papyrus)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>strips</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “The Egyptians cut the plant into <strong>strips</strong> which they softened in water. Papyrus was cross-woven into a mat and then pounded…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cây papyrus được cắt thành các <strong>strips</strong> (dải) trước khi được xử lý tiếp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>9. Europe: Materials used (Parchment)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>sheep</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “…it has been estimated that a single book written on parchment required the skins of 300 <strong>sheep</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Da cừu (<strong>sheep</strong>) là ví dụ cụ thể về nguyên liệu làm parchment.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>10. Europe: Method of production (Parchment)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>stretched</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “The skins had to be specifically prepared by drying them and they were then <strong>stretched</strong> on a special frame.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Da làm parchment được làm khô và sau đó được <strong>stretched</strong> (kéo căng).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>11. China: Materials used (Paper)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Bark</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “Ts’ai Lun seems to have made his paper by mixing finely chopped <strong>mulberry bark</strong> and hemp rags with water…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Vỏ cây (<strong>Bark</strong>) dâu tằm là một trong những nguyên liệu chính.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>12. Place: (Papermaking Center in 751 AD)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Samarkand</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “They were taken away to <strong>Samarkand</strong>, which was a good place to make paper…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Thợ làm giấy Trung Quốc bị bắt và đưa đến <strong>Samarkand</strong>, nơi này trở thành trung tâm làm giấy.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>13. Samarkand: Method of production</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Stone</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “Samarkanders changed the technology of manufacturing paper. They began to prepare it in <strong>stone</strong> mills…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công nghệ mới ở Samarkand sử dụng cối xay làm bằng <strong>Stone</strong> (đá).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('725755ce-6fd0-4a40-bbcc-ce2219ac02c1', '6f130bd7-5216-4027-a64d-a7b14ef79a07', 'matrix', 'Questions 1-8', '', '<p data-path-to-node="5">Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="26">A-F</strong> in boxes 1-8 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="6"><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0">NB</strong> <em data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="3">You may use any letter more than once</em></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "It is the first time these exhibits can be seen outside their country of origin.", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "Some of the exhibits are based on something seen in the press.", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "It portrays a strange event that took place many years ago.", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "It is based on the link between two art forms which was developed in the last century.", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "It contains a painting whose subject is unlikely to be seen elsewhere.", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "It gives examples of how artists have shown changes in their society through their work.", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "Its scientific subject matter is very relevant to current concerns worldwide.", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "It gives a fresh interpretation to some exhibits displayed there some years ago.", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. It is the first time these exhibits can be seen outside their country of origin. — {E} Chinese Prints</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…showcases a newly formed collection… <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">previously exhibited only in China</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Previously exhibited only in China” (trước đây chỉ triển lãm ở Trung Quốc) đồng nghĩa với việc đây là lần đầu tiên chúng được trưng bày bên ngoài quốc gia gốc (first time outside their country of origin).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Some of the exhibits are based on something seen in the press. — {B} The Painting of Modern Life</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…anything from a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">newspaper illustration</strong> to a family snapshot.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Newspaper illustration” (minh họa trên báo chí) chính là thứ được thấy trên báo chí/truyền thông (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">the press</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. It portrays a strange event that took place many years ago. — {A} Whatever the Weather</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…an unusual incident in 1900 when <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">it rained fish</strong>!”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc “mưa ra cá” vào năm 1900 là một sự kiện kỳ lạ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">strange event/unusual incident</strong>) đã xảy ra từ rất nhiều năm trước.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. It is based on the link between two art forms which was developed in the last century. — {F} Eye-Music</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…explores the fascinating relationship between <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">art and music</strong> at the beginning of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\"><span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"20^{th}\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">$20^{th}$</span> century</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Art and music” là hai loại hình nghệ thuật (two art forms). Thế kỷ 20 (<span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"20^{th}\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">$20^{th}$</span> century) chính là thế kỷ trước (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">last century</strong> – tính từ mốc thời gian của bài viết).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. It contains a painting whose subject is unlikely to be seen elsewhere. — {C} Ethiopian Encounters</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…which include images of great historical importance, such as a <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">rare portrait of Sahle Selassie</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một bức chân dung “hiếm” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">rare</strong>) của nhà vua đồng nghĩa với việc đối tượng này khó/không thể tìm thấy ở nơi nào khác (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">unlikely to be seen elsewhere</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. It gives examples of how artists have shown changes in their society through their work. — {E} Chinese Prints</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The display reflects the way in which Chinese artists have portrayed cultural, political and economic <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">transformations in their country</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Transformations” đồng nghĩa với “changes”. Các nghệ sĩ đã thể hiện những thay đổi về văn hóa, chính trị, kinh tế của đất nước họ (society) qua các bản in.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Its scientific subject matter is very relevant to current concerns worldwide. — {A} Whatever the Weather</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“With <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"17\">climate change</strong> high on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">international agenda</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Climate change” (biến đổi khí hậu) là chủ đề khoa học đang được thế giới đặc biệt quan tâm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">current concerns worldwide/international agenda</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. It gives a fresh interpretation to some exhibits displayed there some years ago. — {D} Art Treasures Revisited</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“In 1857 Manchester held the largest art exhibition… Now a <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">new exhibition celebrates this art extravaganza</strong> and examines how it reflected…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Revisited” (xem xét lại) và “new exhibition celebrates this…” cho thấy đây là một cách giải thích/diễn giải mới (fresh interpretation) cho các hiện vật đã từng được trưng bày trước đó (từ năm 1857).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('453d0c53-e963-4a5b-940b-4aafd53a4cbb', '539b2708-48a5-430c-ac11-a5f97c931866', 'matching', 'Questions 36-40', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, <strong>A-G</strong>, below.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. the results of scientific research are not always understood at first."}, {"optionText": "B. science is an unbiased discipline"}, {"optionText": "C. people should be able to choose whether they want fluoride."}, {"optionText": "D. there is insufficient proof to support a cautious approach."}, {"optionText": "E. the serious damage fluoride causes far outweighs any positive effects."}, {"optionText": "F. children are not the only ones who benefit from fluoridation."}, {"optionText": "G. scientific knowledge is affected by the beliefs of everyone concerned."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "The traditional view of science is that ", "correctAnswer": "B. science is an unbiased discipline", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "A sociological view of science argues that", "correctAnswer": "G. scientific knowledge is affected by the beliefs of everyone concerned.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Collins is of the opinion that", "correctAnswer": "A. the results of scientific research are not always understood at first.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The writer suggests that a supporter of fluoridation may conclude that", "correctAnswer": "D. there is insufficient proof to support a cautious approach.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The writer suggests that an opponent of fluoridation may conclude that", "correctAnswer": "C. people should be able to choose whether they want fluoride.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>36. The traditional view of science is that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B. science is an unbiased discipline</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “The traditional view is that science is a special of knowledge, which is established through scientific methods and <strong>objectively applied</strong> by members of a scientific community.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Quan điểm truyền thống coi khoa học được áp dụng <strong>khách quan</strong> (<em>“objectively applied”</em>), tương đương với việc nó là một lĩnh vực không thiên vị (“unbiased discipline”).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>37. A sociological view of science argues that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>G. scientific knowledge is affected by the beliefs of everyone concerned.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “…a sociology of science that shows how scientific knowledge is socially negotiated, and <strong>inevitably linked to the values of the relevant parties, both scientists and nonscientists</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Xã hội học khoa học cho rằng kiến thức khoa học liên kết không thể tránh khỏi với <strong>giá trị của tất cả các bên liên quan</strong>, bao gồm cả nhà khoa học và người không phải nhà khoa học.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>38. Collins is of the opinion that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A. the results of scientific research are not always understood at first.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) Collins asserted that the outcome of experiments was not something whose meaning <strong>“could be immediately comprehended, but rather something for interpretation, discussion between scientists”</strong>.</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Collins tin rằng kết quả nghiên cứu khoa học không thể <strong>được nắm bắt ngay lập tức</strong> (<em>“immediately comprehended”</em>) mà cần có thời gian diễn giải.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>39. The writer suggests that a supporter of fluoridation may conclude that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D. there is insufficient proof to support a cautious approach.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) Một người ủng hộ lập luận: “the evidence for the benefits of fluoridation is quite substantial, while the <strong>evidence for harm is limited and dubious</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Họ kết luận rằng bằng chứng về tác hại là <strong>quá ít và đáng ngờ</strong> (<em>“limited and dubious”</em>) nên không cần thiết phải áp dụng một cách tiếp cận thận trọng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>40. The writer suggests that an opponent of fluoridation may conclude that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C. people should be able to choose whether they want fluoride.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) Lý do phản đối thứ ba là: “fluoridation is thought to be an <strong>infringement on individual rights</strong> because it is <strong>compulsory medication</strong> of all members of a community.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc phản đối sự bắt buộc vì nó vi phạm quyền cá nhân (<em>“infringement on individual rights”</em>) ngụ ý rằng mọi người nên có quyền lựa chọn.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c8230a1e-0ad7-4e8b-a7f6-a421c6c667cf', '6f7820cf-3185-44c4-8f9a-04328d0cc13e', 'radio', 'Questions 21–25', '', '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "maximizing profits"}, {"option_text": "minimizing environmental damage"}, {"option_text": "meeting legal requirements"}], "question": "What do Pam and Jason primarily hope to learn more about from their project?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "providing information about contents"}, {"option_text": "extending the useful life of products"}, {"option_text": "reducing excess waste from packaging"}], "question": "Which issue about packaging do Pam and Jason feel is most important to food shoppers today?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "They are the subjects of previously published studies."}, {"option_text": "They are the most profitable food retail businesses."}, {"option_text": "They will offer good opportunities for interviews."}], "question": "Why have Pam and Jason decided to concentrate specifically on large supermarkets?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "its range of nationalities"}, {"option_text": "its high education level"}, {"option_text": "its young age"}], "question": "The professor says that the local population has unusual food-shopping habits because of"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "taste"}, {"option_text": "price"}, {"option_text": "health benefits"}], "question": "According to the literature, what influences food shoppers most?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> Hello, Pam, Jason. Thanks for coming to discuss your marketing project. I’ve read your proposal and outline, so let’s go over it, okay?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> You’ve chosen the topic of food packaging. So, what did you want to get out of doing this project?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pam:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"5\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q21) We decided if we did our project on packaging, we might find some practical tips on how a business could make more money</span>.</strong> After all, we’re Business Admin students, and that’s the ultimate reason we’re on the course, isn’t it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> So, although we know the impact of packaging on the environment is important, we feel the government regulations are pretty strict already in that area.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> Okay. Now, you’ve decided to look specifically at the packaging of food. What do you think the main issue is for shoppers these days?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Some people get upset about the waste with all the plastic and stuff used to package food, but I guess most don’t pay much attention to that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pam:</strong> A few years ago, people seemed concerned about packaging food so that buyers knew more about what it contains, from labels like calories, additives, and stuff. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"165\">(Q22) But in the current economic climate, Jason and I think people are most interested in packaging that helps keep food fresh for longer.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> And you’ve chosen to concentrate on big supermarket chains. Why not look at local stores or even convenience stores?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Well, there are some interesting published studies based on small retail outlets, and we looked at those. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">(Q23) But after a little investigation, we found that the managers of the large supermarkets in this area wanted to be helpful and are willing to let us talk to them and their employees.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pam:</strong> Of course, the supermarkets do account for most food sales around here, but that wasn’t our reason for choosing them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> Speaking of this area, you know, the food buying choices here are quite unusual. Since we’re in a university town, the population is quite young.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> But actually, my research shows that age isn’t the factor in making the area unique. And although the education level is pretty high, that doesn’t seem very important either.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pam:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"5\">(Q24) I guess it’s because we’ve got people from all over the world living here with all the foreign students at university.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> That’s it. Our supermarkets cater for a huge diversity of cultures.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> In our survey of the literature, I was struck by what shoppers say is most important to them when they buy. I would have thought how much the buyer had to pay would be the key, but that doesn’t appear to be the case.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pam:</strong> That’s right.<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"19\">(Q25) How delicious the buyer considers the product seems to be the main thing.</strong></span> Whether or not the food is good for you is pretty low down on the customer’s priorities.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> That’s interesting.</p>\n<h2 data-path-to-node=\"22\"> </h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> Let’s discuss the practical experiment you’re planning. You’re going to design the box for a new breakfast cereal, which you’ll try to market… Let’s talk through the experiment.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Okay, that would be helpful.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> Now, the number of different designs you’re proposing to show each student is two. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">(Q26) If I were you, I’d make it at least four. That way you can examine their reaction to more variety in the kinds of packaging.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pam:</strong> Okay, good idea. We do have several more designs.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Now we’ve got a sample from our class of about 20. Is that enough?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> Probably not. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">(Q27) Try talking to the assistant in the Business Studies department; he can sort out how to recruit some more from other classes for you.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pam:</strong> Right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> Now, as to how you’re going to display your packages to the students. I did talk about those technical issues in one of your first classes. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"151\">(Q28) Go back and look over what I said about the practical realities of conducting experiments.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Okay, we can do that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pam:</strong> We are going to ask each student to choose the one design they think is best, but how will we know why they chose that one?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> Well, don’t just rely on oral prompts. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">(Q29) Give them a series of written questions. That way you’ll have hard data.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Okay. But what about analyzing the data?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> Well, we’ve got an excellent computer program to gather it all together, but we still need to interpret it ourselves.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Pam:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"5\">(Q30) So we’ll need to give ourselves a few more days for that.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Professor:</strong> Yes, we will. Anyway, it’s all looking good now.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2e7e87ce-886c-4a04-bb73-cbfe24982c40', '81e283d2-50cd-4767-880e-d3528cf9e72d', 'checkbox', 'Questions 23–24', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> points did students most frequently make about music practice?</p>', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A They prefer to practise alone", "correct": false}, {"option": "B They try to practise every day", "correct": false}, {"option": "C They are motivated to practise by fear", "correct": true}, {"option": "D They feel they don’t do enough practice", "correct": false}, {"option": "E They enjoy the challenge of a difficult piece", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": ""}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('146e1699-8a11-4978-8c36-a4c563509c4f', '81e283d2-50cd-4767-880e-d3528cf9e72d', 'checkbox', 'Questions 25–26', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> points were most frequently made by students about the pieces they select for assessed performances?</p>', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A They like to hear others performing the same pieces.", "correct": true}, {"option": "B They like to choose little-known pieces", "correct": false}, {"option": "C They like to play pieces from memory", "correct": true}, {"option": "D They like their tutor to choose their pieces", "correct": false}, {"option": "E They like to choose technically demanding pieces.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": ""}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4a8af913-3060-4a37-8931-0ce08da13e95', '6f130bd7-5216-4027-a64d-a7b14ef79a07', 'radio', 'Questions 9-14', '', '<p>Choose<strong data-path-to-node="5,0" data-index-in-node="0"> TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information ,<strong data-path-to-node="5,0" data-index-in-node="50">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information ,<strong data-path-to-node="5,0" data-index-in-node="101">NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Treatment is carried out without the use of medication."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The clinic avoids using electronic equipment to treat patients."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The clinic expects patients to keep a record of their symptoms."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Children and adolescents receive different treatment from adults."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Treatment at home is provided only for the elderly."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Physiotherapists at the clinic have work experience in both state and commercial sectors."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Treatment is carried out without the use of medication. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…specializes in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">drug-free</strong> treatment of work-related conditions…”</em> (Đoạn 1)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Drug-free” (không dùng thuốc) tương ứng hoàn toàn với “without the use of medication”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. The clinic avoids using electronic equipment to treat patients. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…as well as treatments such as <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">ultrasound and laser</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Ultrasound” (siêu âm) và “Laser” là các thiết bị điện tử/công nghệ cao dùng trong điều trị. Do đó, nói phòng khám “tránh sử dụng” (avoids using) là sai so với văn bản.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. The clinic expects patients to keep a record of their symptoms. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“We assist our patients in understanding their problem and teach them what they can do to <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">relieve their symptoms themselves</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói phòng khám dạy bệnh nhân cách tự làm giảm triệu chứng, <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc yêu cầu bệnh nhân phải ghi chép lại (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"145\">keep a record</strong>) các triệu chứng đó.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Children and adolescents receive different treatment from adults. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“We see children and adolescents as well as adults, providing a full assessment and a programme <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">designed to suit the needs of each age group</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói chương trình được thiết kế phù hợp với nhu cầu từng độ tuổi, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">không khẳng định</strong> là các phương pháp điều trị này là “khác nhau” (different) hay “giống nhau” về bản chất kỹ thuật.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Treatment at home is provided only for the elderly. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“In addition we provide <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">home visits</strong> for those who are <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">currently incapacitated and unable to travel</strong> to the clinic…”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dịch vụ tại nhà dành cho bất kỳ ai đang bị mất khả năng vận động hoặc không thể di chuyển đến phòng khám, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">không chỉ giới hạn</strong> riêng cho người già (only for the elderly).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Physiotherapists at the clinic have work experience in both state and commercial sectors. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“They have a wealth of experience in both the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">National Health Service</strong> and <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">private practice</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn 5)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “National Health Service” (Dịch vụ Y tế Quốc gia) đại diện cho khu vực công/nhà nước (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">state sector</strong>), và “private practice” (phòng khám tư nhân) đại diện cho khu vực thương mại (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"189\">commercial sector</strong>).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('27ee80d0-d743-4c72-9d5f-f7bb900b5bc1', '5c61a509-f5c3-4841-bdfb-6d3011e38686', 'matrix', 'Questions 20–23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 20–23) and the list of researchers below. Match each statement with the correct researcher, A–E. </p>
<p><strong>NB You may use any letter more than once.</strong></p>', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The brain of a good multi-tasker works differently from other people’s.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "The rate of error is considerably higher when people multi-task.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "People are mistaken in their assumption that they can multi-task.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "One gender does not seem to pause to consider before taking action.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Edward M Hallowell", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Paul E Dux", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "David Strayer", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Etienne Koechlin", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Keith Laws", "categoryLetter": "E"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. The brain of a good multi-tasker works differently from other people’s: C (David Strayer)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> “David Strayer’s research… ‘super-taskers’ exhibit <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">different patterns of brain activity</strong>…”</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. The rate of error is considerably higher when people multi-task: C (David Strayer)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> “Strayer’s research shows… <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">more mistakes are made</strong> and it takes longer to complete each activity.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. People are mistaken in their assumption that they can multi-task: A (Edward M Hallowell)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"5,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> “Edward M Hallowell even describes multi-tasking as a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">‘mythical activity’</strong> in which people believe they can perform…”</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. One gender does not seem to pause to consider before taking action: E (Keith Laws)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"5,3,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> “…men tend to jump to it… ‘<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">It’s as if they don’t stop to reflect and plan for a moment</strong>,’ says Professor Keith Laws.”</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('690da8b7-300d-4f0e-b5d3-5f3a2f9e3e8e', '89d57914-1e44-46a0-b3e8-6737b80029d9', 'fillup', 'Questions 15-20', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 15-20 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>Tell a {supervisor} when you cannot be at work at the scheduled time.</p>
<p>You may have to talk to colleagues from different {locations} anywhere in the world</p>
<p>Work emails should carefully provide {details} of the purpose of the message.</p>
<p>When using the phone, your{voice} must be easy to understand.</p>
<p>Saying “hello” to co-workers at {lunch} is important</p>
<p>It is best to stay away from {gossip}</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Tell a {supervisor} when you cannot be at work at the scheduled time.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If you believe you will be <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">late for work</strong> [= cannot be at work at the scheduled time], first <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">let your supervisor know</strong> [= Tell a supervisor].”</em> (Tip 1)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Late for work” chính là việc không thể có mặt đúng giờ quy định. Hành động “let someone know” tương đương với “tell”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. You may have to talk to colleagues from different {locations} anywhere in the world.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…you must <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">communicate</strong> [= talk] with <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">co-workers</strong> [= colleagues] who are in other <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">locations</strong>.”</em> (Tip 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “International company” được cụ thể hóa bằng cụm “anywhere in the world”. Từ khóa chỉ nơi chốn ở đây là <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">locations</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Work emails should carefully provide {details} of the purpose of the message.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…required for <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">official emails</strong> [= Work emails], include all <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">details</strong> in your message…”</em> (Tip 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để thông điệp rõ ràng, bài đọc yêu cầu người viết phải đưa vào đầy đủ các chi tiết (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">details</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. When using the phone, your {voice} must be easy to understand.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“In addition, when you are <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">on a call</strong> [= using the phone], you should ensure that the person at the other end can hear your <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">voice</strong> clearly so that your message is <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"172\">easy to understand</strong>.”</em> (Tip 2 – phần bổ sung)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đây là câu bẫy nhẹ. Để “easy to understand” (dễ hiểu) khi gọi điện, cái cần được nghe rõ chính là giọng nói (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">voice</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Saying “hello” to co-workers at {lunch} is important.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It is important to <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">greet people</strong> [= Saying “hello”]… during <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">lunch</strong> with your co-workers.”</em> (Tip 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Greet” (chào hỏi) tương ứng với “Saying hello”. Thời điểm thực hiện hành động này là bữa trưa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">lunch</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. It is best to stay away from {gossip}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“You should <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">avoid</strong> [= stay away from] making negative comments… This kind of <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">gossip</strong> will damage…”</em> (Tip 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Avoid” (tránh) đồng nghĩa với “stay away from”. Đối tượng tiêu cực cần tránh ở đây là <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">gossip</strong> (chuyện phiếm/nói xấu).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b31f6657-3c3e-4a93-8fb3-d1d54c366336', '5c61a509-f5c3-4841-bdfb-6d3011e38686', 'fillup', 'Questions 24–26', '<p>Complete the summary below. Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Super-taskers</strong></span></p>
<p>Super-taskers are those of us who possess special multi-tasking ability. They can be found in all professions. People who are pilots, chefs and doctors are often super-taskers, and super-taskers are most likely to achieve a {position} that is high on the career ladder. Super-taskers typically have to undertake many tasks simultaneously that need their {attention}. Genes play an important role in having this capability; these people have a special brain {structure} which helps them do what we cannot.</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. position</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> “…super-taskers will rise to a top <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">position</strong> in any occupation…”</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những người siêu đa nhiệm thường đạt được vị trí cao trong sự nghiệp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. attention</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> “…juggling various tasks that demand <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">attention</strong> at the same time.”</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Công việc của họ đòi hỏi phải làm nhiều việc cần sự tập trung cùng lúc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. structure</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> “You are either born with the neural <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">structure</strong> that allows you to overcome…”</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khả năng này bắt nguồn từ cấu trúc não bộ đặc biệt mà họ có từ khi sinh ra.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('36eb3da3-be35-4829-8467-873e9d11ceea', '0f891c93-40e0-4d37-9df1-f34c91953f6d', 'checkbox', 'Questions 17–18', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.<br>17-18 Which <strong>TWO </strong>items is it recommended that campers bring?</p>', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A earplugs", "correct": true}, {"option": "B sunscreen", "correct": false}, {"option": "C swimming toy", "correct": false}, {"option": "D torch", "correct": false}, {"option": "E boots", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": ""}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3c25379f-0997-49ce-88c2-e35e51061c9b', '0f891c93-40e0-4d37-9df1-f34c91953f6d', 'checkbox', 'Questions 19–20', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.<br>19-20 Which does the organiser suggest are the <strong>TWO </strong>most popular concert items?</p>', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A acting", "correct": false}, {"option": "B dancing", "correct": true}, {"option": "C poetry recital", "correct": false}, {"option": "D singing", "correct": true}, {"option": "E storytelling", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": ""}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6b9cbfdb-49b2-4d97-940c-bc8bddbd6e77', '81e283d2-50cd-4767-880e-d3528cf9e72d', 'matching', 'Questions 27–30', '', '<p>Which comment did most students make about each of the following aspects of performance?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FOUR </strong>correct answers, <strong>A-G</strong>, next to question 27-30.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p> </p>\n<p>Performing solo {This is difficult but enjoyable}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Deciding which pieces to perform  {This is time-consuming}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Performing with musicians from a different genre  {This is happens infrequently}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Performing with musicians who play the same instrument  {This is very beneficial}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "This is very beneficial"}, {"optionText": "This is difficult but enjoyable"}, {"optionText": "This can affect relationships"}, {"optionText": "This makes them very nervous"}, {"optionText": "This is time-consuming"}, {"optionText": "This is easy"}, {"optionText": "This is happens infrequently"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": ""}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('afa72236-3e9a-49ef-9d49-06404e1c6c1a', 'dd129c36-a0c2-4406-b6c7-1f229a01c8fc', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p>Complete the note below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<h3><strong>  Ethics in Engineering</strong></h3>
<p><strong>Ethics – principles relating to right and wrong conduct</strong></p>
<p>– at first, engineers saw ethics as a {personal} issue</p>
<p>– attitudes changed because of three disasters involving the collapse of {bridges}</p>
<p>1876 – USA (metal fatigue)</p>
<p>1879 – Scotland (the impact of {wind} on the structure was miscalculated)</p>
<p>1907 – Canada (the structure could not support its own {weight})</p>
<p><strong>Boston Molasses Disaster</strong></p>
<p>At the time, molasses was the main {sweetener} used in the USA</p>
<p>– Boston company: collapse of a {tank} released 8 million litres of molasses</p>
<p>– the wave of molasses destroyed buildings and the railway</p>
<p>– local residents insisted on a {trial} of the molasses company</p>
<p><strong>Causes of the accident:</strong></p>
<p>– insufficient {safety} check</p>
<p>– the fermentation caused the rising of {pressure}</p>
<p>Now, every engineer has to have a {license |lice}</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 4: ETHICS IN ENGINEERING</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Good afternoon. Today we’re starting a series of lectures on ethics in engineering—that is, engineering principles relating to right and wrong conduct, and the sorts of moral responsibilities that you will have to uphold in your professional lives.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">I’m going to start by giving you a brief outline of the history of ethics in engineering. It was, of course, only in the 19th century that engineering really emerged as a profession. Initially, ethical issues were considered to be a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"233\">(31) personal</strong></span> matter, something to be decided in accordance with one’s own principles and values.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">However, things gradually changed as the profession grew and as engineering projects became larger and more complex. A need began to be felt for a more codified set of principles that all engineers would agree to follow. Unfortunately, it took three major disasters to bring about this change in attitude. All three of these involved the collapse of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"350\">(32) bridges</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">The first, known as the Ashtabula River Railroad disaster, happened in 1876 in the USA, and we now think it was probably caused by metal fatigue. Then in 1879, there was a second disaster, this time in Scotland. This occurred because engineers had failed to correctly calculate the effects that <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"295\">(33) wind</strong></span> would have on the structure. The third collapse occurred in 1907 in Canada. This was also due to an engineering design problem: the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"437\">(34) weight</strong></span> of the structure was so great that it could not support itself, and it collapsed. Public outcry over disasters such as these eventually led to the establishment of professional societies for engineers in most industrializing societies.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">THE BOSTON MOLASSES DISASTER</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Another different type of disaster also had an impact on the development of professional engineering organizations, and I’d like to talk about this in a little more detail. This incident, which happened early in the 20th century, is known as the Boston Molasses Disaster.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">At the time, molasses was used rather than sugar as the principal <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">(35) sweetener</strong></span> in the USA. It was also used in the manufacture of a number of other important products. One company in the city of Boston had a large amount of molasses waiting to be transferred to another factory. The molasses—more than 8 million liters of thick, sticky liquid—was stored in a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"361\">(36) tank</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Suddenly this collapsed, unleashing a wave of molasses up to 5 meters high. Nearby buildings were swept off their foundations and crashed to the ground. The wave also swept away a considerable stretch of railway track. Many streets round the factory were covered with a thick layer of sticky brown molasses.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">Local residents were furious, as they felt that the company was to blame. They banded together and succeeded in bringing about a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">(37) trial</strong></span>, charging the company with negligence. After three years, the company was found responsible for the accident and required to pay out in damages the equivalent of six or seven million dollars in today’s money.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAUSES AND CONSEQUENCES</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Even today, no one is absolutely sure about the immediate causes of the accident. However, it is certainly clear that not enough <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">(38) safety</strong></span> tests were carried out. Had these been done in accordance with the standards now applicable, then the accident would almost certainly have been prevented.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">It seems that the collapse was probably brought about by fermentation of the molasses, which led to an increase in <strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">(39) <span style=\"background-color: #fbeeb8;\">pressure</span></strong>. This increase probably exerted too much force against a fatigue crack or some other weakness.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">However, this was one of the main incidents which led to increased legislation in the 1920s to regulate engineers and the engineering profession. It is the reason why we can now only operate if we have gained a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"211\">(40) license</strong>(hoặc lice)</span>. This requires us always to be conscientious about doing everything necessary to avoid disasters, however time-consuming or expensive this may sometimes seem.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6a5323df-e059-4647-8d2b-c81fd68c82ee', '69c69ea2-d7fb-40c3-9a02-70d46da0022e', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="8d304ab3-da1d-4851-83b0-8d259fc56213" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling">
<p data-start="63" data-end="150">Complete the notes below</p>
<p data-start="63" data-end="150">Write <strong data-start="117" data-end="134">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer</p>
<span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>The question of dolphin intelligence</strong></span>
<p data-start="192" data-end="253">Critics of dolphin intelligence raise objections based on:</p>
<p data-start="255" data-end="269"><strong>Brain size</strong></p>
<p data-start="270" data-end="347">Glial cells are used mostly to protect dolphin brains by providing insulation</p>
<p data-start="349" data-end="361"><strong>Behavior</strong></p>
<p data-start="362" data-end="459">For example, dolphins won’t try to escape when trapped by an obstacle such as a {net}</p>
<p data-start="461" data-end="485"><strong>‘Dumb-bird’ argument</strong></p>
<p data-start="486" data-end="567">Critics cite behavior of small-brained animals like pigeons and {rats}</p>
<p data-start="569" data-end="601">Pigeons indicate thanks for food</p>
<p data-start="603" data-end="691">Pigeons’ reactions to their reflections suggest they are {aware} of themselves</p>
<strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Evidence supporting dolphin intelligence</span></strong>
<p data-start="742" data-end="755"><strong>Brain size</strong></p>
<p data-start="756" data-end="833">In addition to protecting it, glial cells act as connections within the brain</p>
<p data-start="835" data-end="846"><strong>Behavior</strong></p>
<p data-start="847" data-end="915">Some positive claims are untrue e.g. that dolphins {smile}</p>
<p data-start="917" data-end="934"><strong>In captivity:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="935" data-end="1105">
<li data-start="935" data-end="1012">
<p>dolphins imitate people’s movements, such as their way of {walking}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1013" data-end="1105">
<p>one female was given fish in exchange for rubbish so she hid {newspaper} in her tank</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1107" data-end="1178">For centuries, dolphins have been known to be {social} animals</p>
<ul data-start="1180" data-end="1347">
<li data-start="1180" data-end="1218">
<p>they support each other when injured</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1219" data-end="1286">
<p>they use a sound like a {whistle} to signal to each other</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1287" data-end="1347">
<p>they touch and stroke each other after a {fight}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1349" data-end="1373"><strong>‘Dumb-bird’ argument</strong></p>
<p data-start="1374" data-end="1485">Tricks displayed by small-brained animals usually are only conditioned responses or {instinctive} reactions</p>
<p data-start="1487" data-end="1561" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">Presley, a dolphin, spontaneously swam to a mirror when marked with paint.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-start"> </div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4: THE QUESTION OF DOLPHIN INTELLIGENCE</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> There is considerable controversy over the question of the intelligence of the marine mammal, the dolphin. Although many marine biologists, including myself, believe that it is a highly intelligent animal, I''d like to look at both sides of the question.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Critics who say dolphins are not intelligent raise objections in several areas. As to the evidence of the dolphin''s large brain size, the critics claim that this is not a sign of intelligence, but simply due to the presence of fatty glial cells. They argue that these cells are not used to think, which might imply intelligence, but rather they are used as insulation for the brain in the cold oceanic habitat. That is, I admit, one of the functions of glial cells.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">The critics also point out certain evidence of behaviour which they say shows that dolphins are rather dumb. For example, South African scientist Paul Minger says that dolphins are too stupid to jump over even a slight barrier. For example, when they are trapped in a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"268\">(Q31) net</strong></span> used to catch fish like tuna. Again, I concede that tragically, this failure to escape often happens and leads to the unnecessary injury or death of dolphins.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Finally, the critics resort to what I call the \"dumb bird\" argument. They downplay the possibility that certain animals are intelligent by pointing to seemingly remarkable feats in obviously small-brained species. If pigeons can do such things, or <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"248\">(Q32) rats</strong></span>, the critics suggest surely the fact that a dolphin or other large-brained animal might do similarly remarkable things isn''t really a mark of intelligence. For example, say these critics, some pigeons have learned to select a key marked \"thank you\" when they are delivered bits of food. Pigeons will also peck at their own reflections, indicating, some insist, that they are <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"634\">(Q33) aware</strong></span> of their own bodies. And once more, I concede that some birds do display these actions.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Let me address these arguments with what I see as the counter-evidence. First, as to brain size, the glial cells are not simply protective; they also function as important connections within the brain, which seem to be important for problem-solving and idea-creating, although scientists do not yet agree exactly how.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">As to behavior, let me begin by saying that I certainly don''t think we should believe everything positive that people claim about dolphins. For example, the notion that they <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">(Q34) smile</strong></span> when they are happy or pleased; this is certainly not true because they don''t have the facial muscles necessary for such physical expressions.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">But many aspects of their behavior do indicate to me that they are highly intelligent. In captivity, dolphins are known to watch their keeper''s particular manner of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"165\">(Q35) walking</strong></span>, for instance, and copy this. I am always impressed by how adept they are as mimics when I witness such behavior.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">And dolphins have been known to outsmart their keepers. One female dolphin who was rewarded with a fish for every piece of rubbish she collected from her tank managed to trick her trainers into a bounty of food. They discovered that she had been keeping a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"256\">(Q36) newspaper</strong></span> on the bottom of the tank and then ripping off small pieces of it to bring to the trainers one by one, thus maximizing her snacks. I''d call that smart!</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">For hundreds of years, we have known that dolphins exhibit <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">(Q37) social</strong></span> behavior. To elaborate on this interaction among dolphins, let me cite several examples. Dolphins have been known to come to the aid of sick or wounded companions, supporting the injured or ailing near the surface of the water to help them breathe.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">Each dolphin produces unique sounds, similar to a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">(Q38) whistle</strong></span>, by which they recognize each other. They use these to signal one another over very long distances. I''ll give you another instance: dolphins touch and stroke each other to make up following a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"256\">(Q39) fight</strong></span>, surely a sign of rather sophisticated intelligence.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">As for the dumb bird argument, yes, clearly even small-brained animals like pigeons can be trained to perform tricks. But these behaviours are usually no more than conditioned responses, learned in response to specific rewards like food, or they are reactions which are <span style=\"background-color: #000000;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"270\">(Q40) instinctive</strong>.</span></span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">Are these truly comparable to the actions of Presley, a dolphin at the New York Aquarium, who without any prompting whatsoever reacted to being marked with paint by taking off at high speed to a distant part of his tank where a mirror was mounted? There he spun round and round, the way humans do in a dressing room, appearing to check himself out. There are many such observations of dolphin behaviour, which is why many animal researchers believe in dolphin intelligence.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0464a1bb-8ae6-4657-a864-9a0c815b5925', 'fb04392b-e668-4899-a217-26650b1351ae', 'matrix', 'Questions 27 - 31', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 3 has eight paragraphs, <strong>A-H</strong>.</p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a summary of Franklin''s occupation in the period before his first expedition", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "a reference to a feature of Franklin''s character in Nadolny''s novel that has no definite basis in fact", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a connection between the central theme of the novel and an environmental process", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "a reference to the widespread appeal of Nadolny''s novel", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "a summary of events following Franklin''s return from his first expedition", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. a summary of Franklin’s occupation in the period before his first expedition</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: A</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“John Franklin (1786-1847) <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">joined the Navy at the age of 14, and fought at the battle of Trafalgar</strong>. When peace came, he turned his attention to Arctic exploration…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A tóm tắt các công việc của Franklin (gia nhập Hải quân, tham gia chiến trận) trước khi ông bắt đầu dẫn đầu chuyến thám hiểm Bắc Cực đầu tiên vào năm 1819.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. a reference to a feature of Franklin’s character in Nadolny’s novel that has no definite basis in fact</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Nadolny has endowed John Franklin with a defining trait for which <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">there is no historical evidence: Langsamkeit (‘slowness’)</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả bài viết chỉ ra rằng đặc điểm “chậm chạp” mà tiểu thuyết gia Nadolny gán cho Franklin là điều <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">không có bằng chứng lịch sử</strong> (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">no historical evidence</em> tương ứng với <em data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"180\">no definite basis in fact</em>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. a connection between the central theme of the novel and an environmental process</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: E</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Ice is a slow mover</strong>… crystals… thickens… consolidates into young ice… deepens to become pack ice. Ice demands a corresponding patience…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Chủ đề trung tâm của tiểu thuyết là “sự chậm chạp”. Đoạn E kết nối chủ đề này với <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">quá trình hình thành băng</strong> — một hiện tượng môi trường diễn ra từ tốn, đòi hỏi sự kiên nhẫn từ con người.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. a reference to the widespread appeal of Nadolny’s novel</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: H</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Since it was first published… has <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">sold more than a million copies and been translated into 15 languages</strong>. It has been adopted as a manual and manifesto by European pressure groups…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn H nói về sự thành công vang dội và sức ảnh hưởng rộng khắp (<em data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">widespread appeal</em>) của cuốn sách, từ doanh số kỷ lục đến việc được các tổ chức chính trị, xã hội đón nhận.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. a summary of events following Franklin’s return from his first expedition</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: B</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“There followed a <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">career as a travel writer and public speaker</strong>… Then in 1845, Franklin set off back to the Arctic…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sau chuyến đi đầu tiên (kết thúc ở đoạn A), đoạn B tóm tắt những gì Franklin làm sau khi trở về (viết sách, diễn thuyết) và kể về chuyến thám hiểm cuối cùng thảm khốc của ông.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('371f0df5-4b7f-4de8-bb08-e59ecf123c26', '53ead48a-2cb0-40b8-9d25-ffc7c9674731', 'radio', 'Questions 27–30', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It is uncertain when the Voynich manuscript was written."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Wilfrid Voynich donated the manuscript to the Beinecke Library."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Interest in the Voynich manuscript extends beyond that of academics and professional codebreakers."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The text of the Voynich manuscript contains just under 70 symbols."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>27. It is uncertain when the Voynich manuscript was written.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “…an unprepossessing vellum manuscript… containing 240-odd pages of drawings and text of <strong>unknown age and authorship</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định niên đại (age) và tác giả (authorship) của bản thảo là <strong>không rõ</strong> (unknown), do đó thời điểm viết là không chắc chắn (uncertain).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>28. Wilfrid Voynich donated the manuscript to the Beinecke Library.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “It’s known to scholars as the Voynich manuscript, after the American book dealer <strong>Wilfrid Voynich, who bought the manuscript from a Jesuit college in Italy in 1912</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nói Voynich đã <strong>mua</strong> bản thảo và hiện nó đang ở Thư viện Beinecke của Yale, nhưng <strong>không nói rõ</strong> ông có hiến tặng (donated) hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>29. Interest in the Voynich manuscript extends beyond that of academics and professional codebreakers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “Over the years, the manuscript has attracted the attention of everyone from <strong>amateur dabblers to top codebreakers</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sự quan tâm bao gồm cả “amateur dabblers” (những người nghiệp dư), không chỉ giới học thuật (academics) hay chuyên gia giải mã (professional codebreakers).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>30. The text of the Voynich manuscript contains just under 70 symbols.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “The precise size of the ‘alphabet’ of the Voynich manuscript was unclear: it’s possible to make out <strong>more than 70 distinct symbols</strong> among the 170,000-character text.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bản thảo chứa <strong>hơn 70</strong> ký hiệu riêng biệt, mâu thuẫn với nhận định “just under 70” (chỉ dưới 70).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9882b66b-7afc-459c-b066-fd7088bb51ba', '1c9eba9b-3398-4a72-a658-fcbf65d2b9dd', 'checkbox', 'Questions 23–24', '', '<p data-start="433" data-end="465">Choose <strong data-start="440" data-end="447">TWO</strong> letters, <strong data-start="457" data-end="464">A–E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="467" data-end="581"><strong data-start="467" data-end="581">For children with dyspraxia, which TWO problems with handwriting do the students think are easiest to correct?</strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A not spacing letters correctly"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B not writing in a straight line"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C applying too much pressure when writing"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D confusing letter shapes"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E writing very slowly"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e5700ba3-0dfa-4ee0-b768-bbf9b04e2187', '1b63a739-8ee5-4415-991d-6bf36b9add96', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<p>Complete the notes below</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Planning a party</strong></span></p>
<p><em>Example</em></p>
<p>Reason for event: wife’s <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">promotion</span></strong><br><strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong>EVENT DETAILS</strong></p>
<p>Event option: large surprise party</p>
<p>Number of people: {80}</p>
<p>Date: {26 September | 26th September}</p>
<p>Day of week: Friday</p>
<p>Time: 6 – 10 p.m.</p>
<p>Location: the {king} Room</p>
<p>Type of music {jazz}</p>
<p><strong>FOOD</strong></p>
<p>Service option {table}</p>
<p>Flavour of cake: {lemon}</p>
<p>Message on cake: {congratulations}</p>
<p><strong>PAYMENT</strong></p>
<p>Reservation fee paid: $100</p>
<p>Credit card type: Mastercard</p>
<p>Credit card number: {5544120043268887}</p>
<p>Name: Brian {SEBASTIAN} Troy</p>
<p>Additional fees: extra charge for {service}</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a telephone conversation between a man who is planning a party for his wife and a woman who organizes special events at a restaurant. First you have some time to look at questions 1 to 4 on page two. You will see that there is an example that has been done for you. On this occasion only, the conversation relating to this will be played first.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Good afternoon, Good Time Restaurant.</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Hi, is this Michelle?</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Yes, speaking.</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> This is Brian Troy. We spoke last week about planning a party to celebrate my wife’s promotion. Well, I would like to go ahead with it, and I have a list of things that I would like to go through with you.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> The reason for the event is his wife’s promotion, so <em>promotion</em> has been written in the space. Now we shall begin. You should answer the questions as you listen because you will not hear the recording a second time. Listen carefully and answer questions 1 to four.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Good afternoon, Good Time Restaurant.</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Hi, is this Michelle?</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Yes, speaking. This is Brian Troy. We spoke last week about planning a party to celebrate my wife’s promotion. Well, I would like to go ahead with it, and I have a list of things that I would like to go through with you.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Yes, I remember. We’d spoken about a few dinner options, like a romantic dinner for two or a small group for dinner. Have you decided yet?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Well, I think I would like to surprise my wife with a huge party. In fact, I’ve already started to contact a few of our friends and family, as well as some of the people my wife works with.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> All right. So let’s get the party details confirmed. So how many guests would you like? Are you thinking of over 100?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> No, I was thinking of more like 50, but then I realized that we have friends that are living out of town, so let’s say <strong>(1) 80</strong> in case everyone wants to come.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Okay. And do you still want October 6th?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Actually, no. I need to change that. My daughter can’t make it then because she has a piano recital. Would <strong>(2) </strong><strong>26th</strong> <strong>September </strong>work for you?</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> No problem. That date still open. Now, do you realize that’s not a Saturday? Are you okay with that?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Yes, I am. When I look at my schedule, Friday is a better choice for all of us.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Great. Now we need to decide on the times. How does 6:00 to 10:00 sound?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> That’s fine. So now let’s talk about the room. I have several options that might work: there’s the Queen Room, the Royal Room, the Palace Room, and the the <strong>(3) King</strong> Room.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Right. I’ve been there before actually. We recently renovated that room, and I think that it would be great for your party. You’ll be very happy with it. Shall I book it for you?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Sure, that would be fine. Have you planned on having music while you’re eating?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Um, I hadn’t thought about it, but it would be nice.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Well, you have some choices. We can arrange for a group to play jazz or one to play the latest pop.</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> I suspect my kids would prefer to have the pop music, but my wife is a <strong>(4) jazz</strong> fan. So let’s book that.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Okay, then I’ll book that today. They’re very good, and they might even sing at your table.</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Great.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the conversation, you have some time to look at questions 5 to 10 on page two. Now listen and answer questions 5 to ten.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Okay, now we need to talk about the type of <strong>(5) service</strong> you want for the dinner. We have two options: a self-service buffet or table.</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Let’s go with the last choice.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Just so you know, the price is the same for either chicken or a vegetarian plate. One last thing to decide on: are you planning anything special for your wife?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Well, uh, I was thinking that at 8:00 or so, I would like to have a cake brought out.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Very nice. And because you’re making reservations for such a large group, the cake is complimentary. What flavor would you like?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Well, uh, it would have to be <strong>(6) lemon</strong>. I really love chocolate, but it is her day, so let’s go with her favorite.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Good decision. Now let me tell you about the cakes. We have a square cake, which would easily serve all of your guests, or you could have two cheesecakes. They’re really popular right now.</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> I prefer the first option because I would like to have something special written on it. But let’s keep it simple. How about <strong>(7) congratulations</strong>?</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Okay, I can have our baker take care of that. He’s happy to show you what it would look like if you wish. Now, is there anything else?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> No, I don’t think so. I think that we have pretty well talked about everything. So let’s look after the reservation detail. I’ll need to have a deposit of $50.</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Let’s make it for <strong>(8) $100</strong> and I’ll put it on my Mastercard. Is that okay?</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Sure. What’s the 16 digit account?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> No. <strong>(9) 5544120043268887</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> And it expires in November. Is there another name on the card beside Brian Troy? A middle name or initial?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> Yes, <strong>(10) Sebastian</strong>. I will spell it for you: S-E-B-A-S-T-I-A-N.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> Is there anything else?</p>\n<p><strong>Brian:</strong> No, I think that’s it.</p>\n<p><strong>Michelle:</strong> However, you need to be aware of an additional fee for large groups. There is an extra charge which covers <strong>service</strong>, but I think that that’s all for now. We look forward to having your celebration dinner here.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 1. You now have half a minute to check your answers. Now turn to Section 2 on page 3.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ffff6b62-f9ef-4d55-a6d2-fd784cfd326a', '346fd6f7-7513-41f5-9370-889ecca9aab9', 'radio', 'Questions 11–12', '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. 5.30 a.m"}, {"content": "B. 6.30 a.m"}, {"content": "C. 7.30 a.m"}], "question": "Joan normally gets up at"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. clean the horses."}, {"content": "B. organise her son."}, {"content": "C. do farm work."}], "question": "Joan’s first task of the day is to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a radio talk on horse riding for disabled people. First you have some time to look at questions 11 to 14 on page three. Now listen carefully and answer questions 11 to fourteen.</p>\n<p><strong>Radio Host:</strong> This week our slot is ‘A life in the day of Joan Gilbert’, local organiser for Riding for the Disabled. Joan, would you like to tell us about this?</p>\n<p><strong>Joan:</strong> Well, I always have the very best intentions of starting the day at 5:30 to give the horses a really good muck out. But reality intervenes and I finally wake at about <strong>(Question 11) 6:30 a.m.</strong> That probably still sounds very early to you, but for a farm worker, which is what my son is at the moment, that’s cutting things pretty fine.</p>\n<p>Once I’ve managed to get <strong>(Question 12) him safely on his way</strong> at about 7:00 am, I can start turning my attention to the other important tasks of the day. For about five years, we’ve been taking overseas students from the International Centre at our local college, and I have to give them a proper breakfast. Most of our students used to be from the Middle East, but they’re no longer coming, so we tend to have Malaysian girls, and they like to have a cooked breakfast much more than any Europeans we’ve had, including me, and I don’t have anything these days.</p>\n<p>After cooking, I finally get round to the poor horses. It’s only after this that I can start thinking about what I regard as my most important task—work for Riding for the Disabled.</p>\n<p>I’ve been involved with this organisation on and off for over 20 years, but I’ve only recently taken on the job of <strong>chairperson</strong>. Most of the work seems more secretarial, but that’s how charities get organized. In our immediate district, we have had as many as 30 riders, but currently we’ve only got <strong>(Question 13) 22</strong> riders. The number of helpers who have volunteered is actually <strong>(Question 13) 40</strong>, but we can rely on <strong>(Question 14) 25</strong> to come regularly to help in the different groups. We now have four separate groups, which cater for disabled children and adults from six to 40 years old.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions 15 to 20 on page four. Now listen and answer questions 15 to twenty.</p>\n<p><strong>Joan:</strong> As I say, I feel that although I no longer have any proper full time paid employment, I do have a full and busy life. I’m a housewife which I don’t mind, because I don’t really object to doing things like washing and cooking. Then there’s my own horses, which I adore, even the revolting stuff like cleaning out the stables.</p>\n<p>The official RDA stuff is a mixed bag really. I don’t have major problems with all the letter writing and <strong>(Question 15) correspondence (B)</strong> which it entails, but like lots of shy people, I find the <strong>(Question 16) fundraising (C)</strong> horrendous. Other regular RDA duties such as <strong>(Question 17) ringing round the riders (A)</strong> to fix times etcetera is one of the pleasantest aspects of the work. After all, that’s why I’m involved with charity work, the contact with people. My working day ends with the least enjoyable job of all—sorting the <strong>(Question 18) accounts (C)</strong>.</p>\n<p>I got involved with RDA because I’ve always loved horses and I can see disabled people gaining so much. I know all the medical evidence that shows that it does wonders for muscle building and so on, which is important. But from talking to the riders, they say it is the confidence they gain and also the opportunity to be part of a new and exciting environment which gives them the greatest benefit.</p>\n<p>In terms of the RDA organization itself, I feel it works very well, but we’re always striving to make it better. I wish for example, our helpers and the organizers in the various centres could really rationalize the <strong>(Question 19) fundraising efforts (B)</strong>, which sometimes are very inefficient. And it also saddens me how unaware some of the stables can be about the <strong>(Question 20) difficulties faced by people who are disabled (E)</strong>.</p>\n<p>Anyway, I feel very privileged to work with our riders and to see such tangible benefits. It sends me to sleep with a feeling that though the day has been hard it has been worthwhile.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 2. You now have half a minute to check your answers to part two.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1e99c8ed-88e1-4290-82ba-dbaba287425a', '346fd6f7-7513-41f5-9370-889ecca9aab9', 'fillup', 'Questions 13–14', '<p>Complete the summary below</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER </strong>for each answer.</p>
<p>Joan’s official title in Riding for the Disabled (RDA) is chairperson. In her local district there are at present twenty-two riders and {40} helpers on the volunteer list, out of whom {25} come regularly.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a radio talk on horse riding for disabled people. First you have some time to look at questions 11 to 14 on page three. Now listen carefully and answer questions 11 to fourteen.</p>\n<p><strong>Radio Host:</strong> This week our slot is &#8216;A life in the day of Joan Gilbert&#8217;, local organiser for Riding for the Disabled. Joan, would you like to tell us about this?</p>\n<p><strong>Joan:</strong> Well, I always have the very best intentions of starting the day at 5:30 to give the horses a really good muck out. But reality intervenes and I finally wake at about <strong>(Question 11) 6:30 a.m.</strong> That probably still sounds very early to you, but for a farm worker, which is what my son is at the moment, that&#8217;s cutting things pretty fine.</p>\n<p>Once I&#8217;ve managed to get <strong>(Question 12) him safely on his way</strong> at about 7:00 am, I can start turning my attention to the other important tasks of the day. For about five years, we&#8217;ve been taking overseas students from the International Centre at our local college, and I have to give them a proper breakfast. Most of our students used to be from the Middle East, but they&#8217;re no longer coming, so we tend to have Malaysian girls, and they like to have a cooked breakfast much more than any Europeans we&#8217;ve had, including me, and I don&#8217;t have anything these days.</p>\n<p>After cooking, I finally get round to the poor horses. It&#8217;s only after this that I can start thinking about what I regard as my most important task—work for Riding for the Disabled.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;ve been involved with this organisation on and off for over 20 years, but I&#8217;ve only recently taken on the job of <strong>chairperson</strong>. Most of the work seems more secretarial, but that&#8217;s how charities get organized. In our immediate district, we have had as many as 30 riders, but currently we&#8217;ve only got <strong>(Question 13) 22</strong> riders. The number of helpers who have volunteered is actually <strong>(Question 13) 40</strong>, but we can rely on <strong>(Question 14) 25</strong> to come regularly to help in the different groups. We now have four separate groups, which cater for disabled children and adults from six to 40 years old.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions 15 to 20 on page four. Now listen and answer questions 15 to twenty.</p>\n<p><strong>Joan:</strong> As I say, I feel that although I no longer have any proper full time paid employment, I do have a full and busy life. I&#8217;m a housewife which I don&#8217;t mind, because I don&#8217;t really object to doing things like washing and cooking. Then there&#8217;s my own horses, which I adore, even the revolting stuff like cleaning out the stables.</p>\n<p>The official RDA stuff is a mixed bag really. I don&#8217;t have major problems with all the letter writing and <strong>(Question 15) correspondence (B)</strong> which it entails, but like lots of shy people, I find the <strong>(Question 16) fundraising (C)</strong> horrendous. Other regular RDA duties such as <strong>(Question 17) ringing round the riders (A)</strong> to fix times etcetera is one of the pleasantest aspects of the work. After all, that&#8217;s why I&#8217;m involved with charity work, the contact with people. My working day ends with the least enjoyable job of all—sorting the <strong>(Question 18) accounts (C)</strong>.</p>\n<p>I got involved with RDA because I&#8217;ve always loved horses and I can see disabled people gaining so much. I know all the medical evidence that shows that it does wonders for muscle building and so on, which is important. But from talking to the riders, they say it is the confidence they gain and also the opportunity to be part of a new and exciting environment which gives them the greatest benefit.</p>\n<p>In terms of the RDA organization itself, I feel it works very well, but we&#8217;re always striving to make it better. I wish for example, our helpers and the organizers in the various centres could really rationalize the <strong>(Question 19) fundraising efforts (B)</strong>, which sometimes are very inefficient. And it also saddens me how unaware some of the stables can be about the <strong>(Question 20) difficulties faced by people who are disabled (E)</strong>.</p>\n<p>Anyway, I feel very privileged to work with our riders and to see such tangible benefits. It sends me to sleep with a feeling that though the day has been hard it has been worthwhile.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 2. You now have half a minute to check your answers to part two.</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c0ecf75b-e4ec-44bc-9aaa-d16c8ac389cd', 'e6213f11-b604-4534-b0c3-0b55b8775c40', 'matching', 'Questions 25–30', NULL, '<p>Complete the flow – chart below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>SIX </strong>correct answers, A-H</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 16.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Geography lesson plan: student activities</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Examine a pencil and discuss where the component materials come from</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Locate the top {G producers}  on a world map</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Discuss the pros and cons of different {H methods of transport}</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">In groups, discuss countries'' possible {A export routes} to the USA</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Complete a {E worksheet}  about pencil distribute a within the USA.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Share ideas about the {B future}  of pencils.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family: Cardo;\">↓</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%;\" align=\"center\"><span lang=\"EN\" style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Prepare a {C talk} </span></p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A export routes"}, {"optionText": "B future"}, {"optionText": "C talk"}, {"optionText": "D homework"}, {"optionText": "E worksheet"}, {"optionText": "F history"}, {"optionText": "G producers"}, {"optionText": "H methods of transport"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b77df912-d602-4630-b3f6-08cc5e440781', 'daa6ae09-48d3-4266-8d97-fb471c6a8450', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">The world’s oldest mechanical computer: the Antikythera mechanism</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>Discovery</strong></p>
<p>It was part of a ship’s {cargo} , found in the sea near Antikythera, in Greece.</p>
<p>It was wrongly thought to be a piece of {rock}.</p>
<p>It was later found to be a mechanism that had broken into pieces.</p>
<p><strong>Equipment used for analysis of the mechanism</strong></p>
<p>“Dome” – produces photographs which make the {inscriptions} clearer</p>
<p>“BladeRunner” – produces X-prays</p>
<p>– originally used to identify {cracks} in engines</p>
<p><strong>Description</strong></p>
<p>The mechanism consisted of:</p>
<p>– 30 or more gear wheels made of {metal}</p>
<p>– models of the sun, moon and planets</p>
<p>– a framework made of {wood}</p>
<p><strong>How the mechanism was used</strong></p>
<p>The operator turned a {handle} to move the gear wheels.</p>
<p>The sun, moon and planets could be moved into their correct positions for any date.</p>
<p>Most surprisingly, the mechanism could calculate when an {eclipse} would occur.</p>
<p>It may have been used as a {calendar} when planning festivals.</p>
<p><strong>Later use of similar technology</strong></p>
<p>13th – 14th centuries: used for making {clocks} in Western Europe.</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Lecturer:</strong> Good morning everyone. Today, I’m going to talk about what is sometimes described as the world’s oldest mechanical computer—the Antikythera mechanism.</p>\n<p>This device was able to calculate where the sun, moon, and planets would be in the sky on any date in the past or future. It has transformed our understanding both of the world of ancient Greece and of the history of science.</p>\n<h3>Discovery and Initial Analysis</h3>\n<p>The mechanism was discovered in 1900 at the bottom of the sea off the Greek island of Antikythera, hence the name by which it’s now known. It was in the <strong>(31) cargo</strong> of a ship that sank about 2,100 years ago. Divers brought various items to the surface, and they were taken to a museum for examination.</p>\n<p>One item was assumed to be a lump of <strong>(32) rock</strong>. However, a few months later, the object started splitting, and a museum curator realized that it was actually something man-made, covered with shells and other objects from the sea. Further investigation revealed that it was in fact some sort of mechanism, and they decided to call it the Antikythera mechanism.</p>\n<p>Although it was badly damaged, it had survived in three main parts and around 80 smaller fragments. The Antikythera mechanism has been studied a great deal since its discovery, and particularly in recent years, when highly sophisticated equipment has been available to analyse it.</p>\n<h3>Equipment Used for Analysis</h3>\n<p>One machine called a Dome can surround a sample and take photographs with the light coming from slightly different angles. This has made far more of the <strong>(33) inscriptions</strong> on the mechanism legible, even though they’re faded and worn.</p>\n<p>Another state-of-the-art machine, the BladeRunner, has been used to take X-rays, which show parts of the mechanism that would otherwise be invisible. Despite weighing nearly 8 tons, it was transported from its place of manufacture to Greece, as the Antikythera mechanism is too fragile to be moved from there. The BladeRunner was originally designed to examine engines for <strong>(34) cracks</strong>, and it can work at an accuracy of less than a tenth of a millimeter.</p>\n<h3>Description and Structure</h3>\n<p>It seems the device was originally about 33 cm high, 17 cm wide, and 9 cm thick. It consisted of at least 30 gear wheels made of <strong>(35) metal</strong> —that is, wheels which interlocked with each other. The surfaces of the gear wheels were inscribed with the names of the months, explanations of how the different parts of the device were to be operated, and other information.</p>\n<p>These gear wheels in turn operated small, movable models of the sun, moon, and the five planets that were known to the ancient Greeks. The mechanism is thought to have been mounted in a frame, for which <strong>(35) wood</strong> was used.</p>\n<h3>Function and Significance</h3>\n<p>So what was the Antikythera mechanism used for? It clearly had an astronomical function. The person using the device simply rotated a <strong>(37) handle</strong> to operate the gear wheels. These engaged with each other to move the sun, moon, and planets around the earth, to show how they would appear on whatever particular date the operator was interested in, which could be years into the future.</p>\n<p>Bearing in mind that the ancient Greeks believed the sun and planets all revolved around the earth, their movements are shown with remarkable accuracy. Perhaps most astonishing of all, the mechanism also showed when an <strong>(38) eclipse</strong> was going to take place. This was very important in the ancient world, and being able to predict this accurately would have given the user great power. The mechanism probably also helped in planning the timing of festivals, both agricultural and religious, by acting as a kind of <strong>(39) calendar</strong> of events.</p>\n<h3>Later Technology</h3>\n<p>Surprisingly, to the best of our knowledge, no device equaled the complexity of the Antikythera mechanism for at least 1,000 years afterwards. The ideas seem to have survived in some form, however, particularly in the Byzantine Empire of the eastern Mediterranean. Around the 13th or 14th century, knowledge of the technology seems to have reached Western Europe, and a large number of <strong>(40) clocks</strong> were made, providing astronomical information as well as showing the time of day. It’s hard to believe that nothing reached the sophistication of the anticithara mechanism for 1,000 years, yet that might well be the case, and that has implications for our understanding of how scientific knowledge progresses.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e0fc8c26-0586-4c46-82b4-0f5310699859', '53ead48a-2cb0-40b8-9d25-ffc7c9674731', 'matrix', 'Questions 31–34', NULL, '<p>Use the information in the passage to match the people (listed A-H) with opinions or deeds below.</p>
<p>Choose the appropriate letters <strong>A-D</strong> in boxes <strong>31-34</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>NB </strong>you may use any letter more than once.</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of people", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The number of times that some words occur make it unlikely that the manuscript is based on an authentic language.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Unlike some other similar objects of fascination, people can gain direct access to the Voynich manuscript.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "The person who wrote the manuscript may not have been entirely sane.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "It is likely that the author of the manuscript is the same person as suggested by Wilfrid Voynich.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Gordon Rugg", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Roger Bacon", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "William Newbold", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "William Friedman", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Rob Churchill", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "Gabriel Landini", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "Ren Zandbergen", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "Girolamo Cardano", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>31. The number of times some words occur make it unlikely that the manuscript is based on an authentic language.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D (William Friedman)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) Friedman <strong>“discovered that some words and phrases appeared more often than expected in a standard language, casting doubt on claims that the manuscript concealed a real language…”</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Phát hiện về tần suất từ ngữ bất thường của Friedman khiến ông nghi ngờ bản thảo là ngôn ngữ nhân tạo.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>32. Unlike some other similar objects of fascination, people can gain direct access to the Voynich manuscript.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A (Gordon Rugg)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) Tiến sĩ Gordon Rugg nói: “Most other mysteries involve second-hand reports… But this is one that you <strong>can see for yourself</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Rugg nhấn mạnh khả năng tiếp cận trực tiếp bản thảo, khác với các bí ẩn khác.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>33. The person who wrote the manuscript may not have been entirely sane.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>E (Rob Churchill)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) “Others, such as <strong>Churchill, have suggested that the sheer weirdness of the illustrations and text hint at an author who had lost touch with reality</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Churchill gợi ý tác giả có thể đã mất liên lạc với thực tế (lost touch with reality/not entirely sane) vì sự kỳ lạ của minh họa và văn bản.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>34. It is likely that the author of the manuscript is the same person as suggested by Wilfrid Voynich.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C (William Newbold)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) <strong>“In 1921 Voynich’s view that Bacon was the writer appeared to win support from the work of William Newbold</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Newbold đã công bố giải mã chứng minh Roger Bacon (người được Voynich đề xuất) là tác giả.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('817e26fc-ba9a-43ec-9053-295c463f9009', '53ead48a-2cb0-40b8-9d25-ffc7c9674731', 'fillup', 'Questions 35–39', '<p>Choose the correct answer.Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Voynich Researchers</strong></span></p>
<p>William Newbold believed that the author of the Voynich manuscript had been able to look at cells through a {microscope} Other researchers later demonstrated that there were flaws in his argument.</p>
<p>William Friedman concluded that the manuscript was written in an artificial language that was based on {concepts}</p>
<p>He couldn’t find out the meaning of this language but he believed that the {computer} would continue to bring advances in codebreaking.</p>
<p>Dr Gabriel Landini used a system known as {spectral analysis} his research, and claims to have demonstrated the presence of genuine words.</p>
<p>Dr Gordon Rugg’s system involved a grille, that made it possible to quickly select symbols that appeared in a {table} Rugg’s conclusion was that the manuscript lacked genuine meaning.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>35. William Newbold believed that the author of the Voynich manuscript had been able to look at cells through a microscope.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>microscope</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “…the manuscript proved that Bacon had access to a <strong>microscope</strong> centuries before they were supposedly first invented.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>36. William Friedman concluded that the manuscript was written in an artificial language that was based on concepts.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>concepts</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…whose words are devised from <strong>concepts</strong>, rather than linguistics.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>37. He couldn’t find out the meaning of this language but he believed that the computer would continue to bring advances in codebreaking.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>computer</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “…he suspected that major insights would come from using the device that had already transformed codebreaking: the <strong>computer</strong>.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>38. Dr Gabriel Landini used a system known as spectral analysis in his research, and claims to have demonstrated the presence of genuine words.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>spectral analysis</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “…Dr Gabriel Landin… published the results of his study of the manuscript using a pattern-detecting method called <strong>spectral analysis</strong>.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>39. Dr Gordon Rugg’s system involved a grille, that made it possible to quickly select symbols that appeared in a table.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>table</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) “…Using a system… in which a specially constructed grille issued to pick out symbols from a <strong>table</strong>…”</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f5708f84-ccac-45f6-89bf-08dfaa5310ba', '89d57914-1e44-46a0-b3e8-6737b80029d9', 'fillup', 'Questions 21-27', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 21-27 on your answer sheet.</p>
<ul data-path-to-node="6">
<li>
<p>employees {punctuality} at all times is required</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="7" data-index-in-node="0">TIME-OFF POLICY</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="8">
<li>
<p>means getting {permission} beforehand</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>applies to reasonable requests and planned events</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="9" data-index-in-node="0">EMERGENCY POLICY</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="10">
<li>
<p>requires that you give your contact information</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>you may be asked later for {proof} that an emergency happened</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="11" data-index-in-node="0">DISCIPLINARY ACTION</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="12">
<li>
<p>unexplained and exceptional lateness will go on a worker’s {record}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>a short but unpaid {suspension} will be given for recurring problems in job attendance</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>a job may be lost if several {warnings} are ignored</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="0">BENEFITS</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="14">
<li>
<p>a {contest} is held to reward workers for consistently being on time</p>
</li>
</ul>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Employees {punctuality} at all times is required.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“At Britwell, we expect all our employees to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">demonstrate punctuality</strong> before and during their regularly scheduled shifts.”</em> (Đoạn 1)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Demonstrate punctuality” (thể hiện sự đúng giờ) tương ứng với yêu cầu về sự đúng giờ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">punctuality</strong>) của nhân viên. “Expect” ở đây mang nghĩa là yêu cầu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"165\">required</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. TIME-OFF POLICY means getting {permission} beforehand.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…so if you know that you will need time off, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">permission</strong> from a senior staff member will need to be <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">obtained in advance</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Obtained in advance” chính là việc xin phép trước (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">beforehand</strong>). Từ cần điền là sự cho phép (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">permission</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. EMERGENCY POLICY… you may be asked later for {proof} that an emergency happened.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Subsequently, we may request that you provide <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">proof</strong> of admission to a hospital emergency ward.”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Subsequently” (sau đó) tương ứng với “later”. Nếu có khẩn cấp, công ty có thể yêu cầu bằng chứng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">proof</strong>) như giấy nhập viện.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. DISCIPLINARY ACTION: unexplained and exceptional lateness will go on a worker’s {record}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“A full-day absence will appear on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">employees record</strong> if he or she does not show up within 30 minutes…”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Appear on” tương ứng với “go on”. Việc vắng mặt hoặc đi muộn nghiêm trọng sẽ bị ghi vào hồ sơ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">record</strong>) của nhân viên.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. DISCIPLINARY ACTION: a short but unpaid {suspension} will be given for recurring problems…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“A <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"14\">suspension without pay</strong> of up to three days will be given for continual unexcused absences.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Unpaid” tương ứng với “without pay”. “Recurring problems” tương ứng với “continual”. Hình phạt ở đây là việc đình chỉ công tác tạm thời (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">suspension</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. DISCIPLINARY ACTION: a job may be lost if several {warnings} are ignored.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Repeated <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">warnings</strong> that do not result in an improvement may lead to <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">termination of employment</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Job may be lost” chính là việc bị đuổi việc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">termination of employment</strong>). “Several” tương ứng với “Repeated”. Nếu phớt lờ các cảnh báo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">warnings</strong>), nhân viên sẽ mất việc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. BENEFITS: a {contest} is held to reward workers for consistently being on time.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…have their names submitted monthly to a <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">contest</strong> in which the winners receive $ 50.00 for showing up punctually…”</em> (Đoạn 5)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để khuyến khích nhân viên đúng giờ, công ty tổ chức một cuộc thi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">contest</strong>) hàng tháng với phần thưởng bằng tiền mặt.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4584ed1d-3529-4bc6-9528-19e74c4bfb58', 'fb04392b-e668-4899-a217-26650b1351ae', 'matching', 'Questions 32 - 35', NULL, '<p>Complete the summary using the list of words, <strong>A-L</strong>, below.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, <strong>A-L</strong>, in boxes 32-35 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>John Franklin and the Quality of Slowness</strong></p>\n<p>Little is known from Franklin''s correspondence and published writings about his {G personality} . The author, Nadolny, suggests that Franklin''s whole life can be explained by the quality of ''slowness'' . He begins the book by showing how this affects the young Franklin''s {K sporting} activities, and makes him become {F an outsider} . As a child, it is the quality of {L timelessness} that attracts Franklin to the Arctic.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A a bully"}, {"optionText": "B discoveries"}, {"optionText": "C educational"}, {"optionText": "D family"}, {"optionText": "E isolation"}, {"optionText": "F an outsider"}, {"optionText": "G personality"}, {"optionText": "H problems"}, {"optionText": "I remoteness"}, {"optionText": "J a scholar"}, {"optionText": "K sporting"}, {"optionText": "L timelessness"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. {G} personality</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">G. personality</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn C cho biết Franklin là người: “…who kept <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">introspection and self-analysis</strong> to a minimum.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vì Franklin luôn giữ việc tự phân tích bản thân ở mức tối thiểu trong các ghi chép cá nhân, nên chúng ta biết rất ít về <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">nhân cách/đời sống nội tâm</strong> (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">personality</strong>) thực sự của ông.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. {K} sporting</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">K. sporting</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn D mô tả cảnh mở đầu cuốn sách khi Franklin còn nhỏ: “…failing to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">catch a ball</strong> because his reaction time is too slow.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc “bắt bóng” là một hoạt động <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">thể thao/thể chất</strong> (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">sporting</strong>). Sự chậm chạp đã ảnh hưởng trực tiếp đến khả năng này của ông.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. {F} an outsider</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">F. an outsider</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn D đề cập: “Despite the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">bullying of his peers</strong>, Franklin resolves <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">not to fall into step</strong> with ‘their way of doing things’.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vì không theo kịp tốc độ của bạn bè và bị bắt nạt, Franklin đã chọn cách không hòa nhập, khiến ông trở thành một <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">người ngoài cuộc</strong> (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">an outsider</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. {L} timelessness</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">L. timelessness</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn D mô tả mong ước của cậu bé Franklin: “…dreaming of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">‘time without hours and days’</strong> which exists in the far north…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Franklin bị thu hút bởi Bắc Cực vì đó là nơi có khái niệm “thời gian không có giờ và ngày”, tương ứng với sự <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">vô tận/không thời gian</strong> (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"145\">timelessness</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('23c3c533-93c1-4826-93f4-dac9eec00516', 'a8698fc6-d9f1-4402-81d3-5dd084979c98', 'fillup', 'Question 1-10', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Holiday Job</strong></span></p>
<p>Location {Jamieson} Island</p>
<p>Start date {11 July|11th July}</p>
<p>Available jobs</p>
<p>Vacancy 1: Calypso Bistro</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– working as a {waiter}</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– no experience needed</p>
<p>Vacancy 2: Guest Liaison</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– must be able to {sing}</p>
<p>Vacancy 3: Activities staff</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– help with games and water sports</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– need experience with {children}</p>
<p>Vacancy 4: In reception</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– as a porter</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– must be able to {drive}</p>
<p>Benefits: For all jobs,</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– there is free {transport}</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– {meals} are provided</p>
<p>Interview</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– to be held on {Thursday} at 2pm</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;">– bring a CV and a {photo}</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2>(Section 1)</h2>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a student phoning a student careers office about a job at a holiday resort. First you have some time to look at questions 1 to 6 on page two. You will see that there is an example that has been done for you. On this occasion only the conversation relating to this will be played first.</p>\n<p><strong>Agent:</strong> Hello. I saw an advert for holiday staff on the notice board and I’m very interested. Can you tell me something about the resort?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> Let me see, yes. Those jobs are at the Sandy Shores Resort. You may have heard of it, as it’s quite well known in the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> The name of the resort is Sandy Shores, so Sandy has been written in the space. Now we shall begin. You should answer the questions as you listen because you will not hear the recording a second time. Listen carefully and answer questions 1 to six.</p>\n<p><strong>Agent:</strong> Hello. I saw an advert for holiday staff on the notice board and I’m very interested. Can you tell me something about the resort?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> Let me see, yes. Those jobs are at the Sandy Shores Resort. You may have heard of it, as it’s quite well known in the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> I’m not sure where exactly is it?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> It’s on <strong>(1) Jamison</strong> Island.</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> I haven’t heard of that one. Uh, how do you spell it?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> J-A-M-I-E-S-O-N. It was named after a famous explorer.</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> Oh, sounds interesting.</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> Yes, it’s a beautiful place, and as it’s a large resort, they have vacancies in a few different areas. When would they want someone to start?</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> It looks like the applications close by May 12th, and they would need you to begin from <strong>(2) July 11th</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> Oh, that’s perfect. My exams finish on July 5th. Can you tell me something about the jobs?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> Well, first of all, there is a vacancy in the Calypso Bistro. That’s for a <strong>(3) waiter</strong>. The work is quite easy, taking orders and serving meals. You don’t need any experience as they will train you. That’s good.</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> They’ve also got a few vacancies in what is called the Guest Liaison department. They are involved with the entertainment in the resort, especially the daily music shows and parades. They definitely need people who can <strong>(4) sing</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> What’s your voice like?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> It’s shocking! But I can play piano, would that be useful?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> I don’t think so, they already have a band. OK. So what else is there?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> Among the most popular things for guests are the games and water sports activities which take place on the beach that belongs to the resort. They are always looking for fit, young people to help out with things like volleyball, surfing and cricket, but they definitely need people who have worked with <strong>(5) children</strong> for that vacancy.</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> Well, I coach junior basketball. Sounds great.</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> Finally, there are vacancies in the reception area. You’d work as part of the Concierge department, carrying bags to and from rooms. A requirement for this role is that you can <strong>(6) drive</strong>. That might seem strange, but some of the Villas are quite far away from the resort hub, so they have little golf buggies to take the bags over to them.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the conversation, you have some time to look at questions 7 to 10 on page two. Now listen and answer questions 7 to ten.</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> I expect you’d like to know a bit more about the general benefits for staff.</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> Yes please. Do they provide free accommodation for staff?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> It looks like they only provide it to permanent employees, but staff don’t have to pay for <strong>(7) transport</strong> to and from the island, so you’d have to stay in Port Thomas, but there are plenty of cheap places there.</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> What about meals?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> Yes, <strong>(8) meals</strong> are provided when you’re on duty, so you would save money on groceries.</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> If you are interested, we can set up an interview for you. I know the resort personnel manager wants interviews on Wednesday, Thursday and Friday here at the college. Which day would suit you?</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> Can we do it on <strong>(9) Thursday</strong> as I work on Wednesdays?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> Fine. Is 2:00 OK?</p>\n<p><strong>Student:</strong> Perfect.</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> OK, I’ve booked you in for then. Is there anything I need to take to the interview?</p>\n<p><strong>Career Office:</strong> Let me see, yes. You need to bring a CV giving details of your work experience and qualifications, and because they are planning on interviewing a lot of people, they’ve asked everyone to provide a <strong>(10) photo</strong> as well, so they can remember who is who. Do you have any questions?</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 1. You now have half a minute to check your answers. Now turn to Section 2 on page 3.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('aafcbb82-24a9-461b-9a72-b923a1bc257c', '46549c74-b227-4967-8859-c8f858a000eb', 'radio', 'Questions 11–15', '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. extremely fit people."}, {"content": "B. parents with their children."}, {"content": "C. tourists unfamiliar with the local area."}], "question": "The walk is organized specifically for"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A.220"}, {"content": "B.250"}, {"content": "C.280"}], "question": "The maximum number of people on the walk will be"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. arrive without a waterproof coat."}, {"content": "B. are causing a lot of trouble."}, {"content": "C. are unable to answer basic safety questions."}], "question": "The organisers will stop walkers taking part if they"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. illness in the organising team."}, {"content": "B. very stormy weather."}, {"content": "C. problems getting people to help."}], "question": "The walk was cancelled two years previously because of"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. only when they have been ordered before the walk."}, {"content": "B. immediately people have completed the whole walk."}, {"content": "C.one week after the walk has finished."}], "question": "Badges can be obtained"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a radio talk by Peter Gentle, the organizer of an annual walk called the Tavistock Walk. First you have some time to look at questions 11 to 15 on page three. Now listen carefully and answer questions 11 to fifteen.</p>\n<p><strong>Radio Host:</strong> Today we’re pleased to welcome Peter Gentle, who is organising this year’s famous Tavistock Walk. Can you tell us about the walk, Peter?</p>\n<p><strong>Peter Gentle:</strong> Well, it’s an organised group walk which takes place every year on one day in October, across some of the most beautiful scenery in the country. Just about anyone with normal fitness can do it, but we have lots of volunteer stewards who are posted at regular intervals along the way to offer help if needed. The walk is mainly aimed at <strong>(11) families (B)</strong>. We want to help people to walk with their children. It’s healthy exercise and it helps people get to know their local area better.</p>\n<p><strong>Peter Gentle:</strong> Now, for those of your listeners who might be interested in doing the walk, it takes place this year on Sunday, October 27th. It’s 18 miles in length, so quite long. But we ensure walkers are very well looked after, and we like to involve as many people as possible, and it’s getting busier every year. For most of the walk’s history, we set a maximum of 220 walkers, but this year we’ve been able to expand to <strong>(12) 280 (C)</strong> because we’ve got a total of 50 volunteers to help us.</p>\n<p><strong>Peter Gentle:</strong> You provide a lot of support then. We have to be pretty strict about arrangements, but we do what we can to help people. If someone arrives without proper clothing, we can help out from our stocks of waterproofs, for example. We don’t just turn them away. The only time we do that is if people <strong>(13) behave badly (B)</strong> at the start. And we also spend a lot of time fielding Walker’s questions about safety, both before the walk and while it’s going on.</p>\n<p><strong>Radio Host:</strong> Do you ever cancel the walk for very bad weather?</p>\n<p><strong>Peter Gentle:</strong> Yes, but it hasn’t happened for several years. However, a couple of years ago, the organizers made a decision to cancel because <strong>(14) we didn’t get as many volunteers (C)</strong> as we needed to act as stewards on the walk. The team felt really awful about it, but these things happen. If something does go amiss, we try to inform all walkers well in advance.</p>\n<p><strong>Peter Gentle:</strong> Now if any of your listeners are interested in joining the walk, they should go to our website at www.tvwalk.org and give us their details. It costs £4.50 each to enter, and that covers a bottle of juice and a hot pie. It also helps towards maintaining the 12 staff checkpoints at different parts on the route. About 90% of our walkers do complete the whole 18 mile route, but if you’re not well or feel you can’t go any further, just inform the stewards when you get to the checkpoint and they’ll organise transport to get you where you need to go. If you do complete the course, you are entitled to receive a badge. Now unfortunately, we can’t give those to you immediately on finishing. If you want one, you have to order it one week before the walk, and you’ll get it by post two weeks after the walk, as long as you finish, of course. <strong>(15) (A)</strong>. It may seem a strange system, but we found it works because only those workers who really want a badge get one.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions 16 to 20 on page four. Now listen and answer questions 16 to twenty.</p>\n<p><strong>Radio Host:</strong> What do walkers need to take with them?</p>\n<p><strong>Peter Gentle:</strong> Good question. When you register for the walk, we send you a booklet with all the key information. But basically, we do say that you should be properly dressed. Now, it must be emphasized that this doesn’t mean that you wear <strong>(16) thick trousers like jeans (C)</strong>. A lighter waterproof apparel is better. Some people like to bring their <strong>(17) mobile phones (B)</strong>, but there isn’t always a good signal, and remember the checkpoints are there, so you can always rely on those. Some people asked if they should bring a <strong>(18) torch (C)</strong>, but frankly they’re a waste of space and weight. It’s a relatively gentle, straightforward walk. Another thing people ask about is refreshments—whether you carry things like high energy <strong>(19) drinks (B)</strong> is up to you. And finally, we say it’s a very good idea to bring a <strong>(20) rucksack (A)</strong>, but what size is up to the individual. But as I say, there’s full information in the Walker’s booklet.</p>\n<p><strong>Radio Host:</strong> Well, thank you very much Peter that’s been—</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 2. You now have half a minute to check your answers. Now turn to Section 3 on page 5.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5179c286-cb4e-448b-8e4a-b695d8009f90', '01e9f592-2c59-422f-b08b-40ddf4d0ace8', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The amount of research on giraffes in their natural environment has increased lately"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Megan Strauss disapproves of keeping giraffes in zoos"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The number of giraffes in Africa has nearly doubled"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Female giraffes tend to live longer than males"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Mother giraffes sometimes use their legs to defend their young"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Younger bulls hold their necks higher in the presence of more powerful males"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Male giraffes have been observed fighting"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"0\">Chào bạn Phát, mình gửi bạn bản bóc tách dẫn chứng một câu tốt nhất, phân tích logic và bảng từ khóa cho toàn bộ 13 câu của bài Reading <strong data-path-to-node=\"0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">\"New Understanding of Giraffes in the Wild\"</strong> (Hiểu biết mới về hươu cao cổ trong tự nhiên) để bạn cập nhật lên hệ thống <code data-path-to-node=\"0\" data-index-in-node=\"255\">vitieltstest.com</code> nhé.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"1\">Bài đọc này thuộc dạng Khoa học tự nhiên - Sinh học động vật, phân tích sâu về tập tính xã hội và các đặc điểm tiến hóa hình thể độc đáo của loài hươu cao cổ.</p>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">GIẢI THÍCH CHI TIẾT ĐÁP ÁN (1–7): TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. TRUE — The amount of research on giraffes in their natural environment has increased lately.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“All that is changing fast, as a growing number of researchers seek to understand the biology and complex behavior of this graceful giant in its native habitat.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói số lượng nghiên cứu về hươu cao cổ trong môi trường tự nhiên tăng lên gần đây (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">increased lately</em>). Bài đọc xác nhận mọi thứ đang thay đổi nhanh chóng với số lượng các nhà nghiên cứu ngày càng tăng (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"221\">a growing number of researchers</em>) đang tìm cách thấu hiểu chúng tại môi trường sống bản địa (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"313\">native habitat / natural environment</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. NOT GIVEN — Megan Strauss disapproves of keeping giraffes in zoos.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“''When I first became interested in giraffes in 2008 and started looking through the scientific literature, I was really surprised to see how little had been done,'' said Megan Strauss...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ trích dẫn lời Megan Strauss bày tỏ sự ngạc nhiên khi thấy có quá ít nghiên cứu khoa học về loài này ngoài tự nhiên vào năm 2008, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">hoàn toàn không có thông tin</strong> nào nói về việc cô ấy phản đối hay không ủng hộ (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"235\">disapproves</em>) việc nuôi nhốt hươu cao cổ trong vườn thú.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. FALSE — The number of giraffes in Africa has nearly doubled.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The giraffe is not listed as endangered, but researchers point to evidence that in the past 15 years, the population has fallen some 40 percent.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi khẳng định số lượng hươu cao cổ ở Châu Phi đã tăng gần gấp đôi (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">nearly doubled</em>). Ngược lại, bài đọc đưa ra bằng chứng rằng trong 15 năm qua, quần thể của chúng đã bị giảm khoảng 40% (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"203\">fallen some 40 percent</em>). Thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"272\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. NOT GIVEN — Female giraffes tend to live longer than males.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Female giraffes can live 20 years or more, and it makes sense they might rely on each other for clues to the best feeding grounds...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có cung cấp số liệu hươu cao cổ cái có thể sống từ 20 năm trở lên (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">live 20 years or more</em>), nhưng trong toàn bộ bài viết <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">không hề có sự so sánh</strong> tuổi thọ giữa con cái và con đực xem con nào có xu hướng sống lâu hơn (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"234\">live longer</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. TRUE — Mother giraffes sometimes use their legs to defend their young.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Giraffe calves are extremely vulnerable to predators, and though mothers will fight valiantly to keep their young alive — kicking forward and backward — half of all calves are killed in their first year of life.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói hươu cao cổ mẹ đôi khi dùng chân để bảo vệ con (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">use their legs to defend</em>). Bài đọc viết rằng các bà mẹ sẽ chiến đấu quả cảm để giữ con sống sót bằng hành động \"đá về phía trước và phía sau\" (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"215\">kicking forward and backward</strong>). Hành động đá (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"260\">kicking</em>) này chính là việc sử dụng chân.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. FALSE — Younger bulls hold their necks higher in the presence of more powerful males.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“But should a dominant older bull come into view, the younger males instantly try to make themselves look small and innocent.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói hươu cao cổ đực trẻ tuổi sẽ giữ cổ cao hơn khi có mặt các con đực quyền lực hơn. Ngược lại, bài đọc chỉ ra rằng nếu một con đực lớn thống trị xuất hiện (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"177\">dominant older bull come into view / more powerful males</em>), các con đực trẻ ngay lập tức cố gắng làm cho bản thân trông nhỏ bé và ngây thơ đi (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"319\">try to make themselves look small</em>). Thông tin bị trái ngược nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"393\">FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. TRUE — Male giraffes have been observed fighting.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Clashes have been witnessed between adults when each bull repeatedly ''necks'' the other, using his massive neck to slam his head against his rival.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói các con hươu cao cổ đực được quan sát thấy đang đánh nhau (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">observed fighting</em>). Bài đọc xác nhận các cuộc đụng độ đã được chứng kiến (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">Clashes have been witnessed</em>) khi chúng dùng chiếc cổ khổng lồ để quật đầu vào đối thủ (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"244\">slam his head against his rival</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ae5a83d3-44a6-4b5a-ac75-4cf688ce06ef', '208a6a07-940a-464d-b5f2-f57d98359169', 'matrix', 'Questions 28-32', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="26">A-G</strong>, in boxes 28-32 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a possible benefit that glacier changes could bring to people living nearby", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "the reason why Dr Traylor''s team had problems finding evidence of previous research", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "the possible economic impact of what is happening to the glaciers", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "an example of a future environmental disaster that may occur in a particular area", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a description of how modern technology has helped in the research", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. A possible benefit that glacier changes could bring to people living nearby — {E}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“We must investigate how the changes could affect local inhabitants <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">positively</strong>, in terms of <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">hydro-electricity generation</strong> that might become feasible and provide a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"173\">new source of power</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E đề cập đến một tác động <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">tích cực</strong> (positive = benefit) là việc phát điện bằng sức nước (thủy điện) có thể khả thi hơn, mang lại nguồn năng lượng mới cho người dân địa phương.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. The reason why Dr Taylor’s team had problems finding evidence of previous research — {A}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The Speke glacier had <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">receded so much</strong> that the team had difficulty finding a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">marker left by previous geographers</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lý do (the reason) mà đội của Dr. Taylor gặp khó khăn khi tìm lại dấu mốc (evidence) của các nhà địa lý trước đó là vì sông băng đã <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">lùi xa (receded/declined)</strong> quá nhanh và quá nhiều.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. The possible economic impact of what is happening to the glaciers — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…but also for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">livelihood</strong> of the Bakonzo and Baamba communities, who depend upon their local environment and <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">tourism for an income</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn G nói về tác động đến sinh kế (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">livelihood</strong>) và thu nhập (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">income</strong>) từ du lịch. Đây chính là những yếu tố thuộc về tác động kinh tế (economic impact).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. An example of a future environmental disaster that may occur in a particular area — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…there is the serious likelihood of a <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">catastrophic event</strong>, such as <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">flash flooding</strong> where the water would <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">wipe out anything in its way</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Catastrophic event” và “flash flooding” (lũ quét) là ví dụ về thảm họa môi trường (environmental disaster) có thể xảy ra trong tương lai nếu băng tiếp tục tan đến vùng bình nguyên.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. A description of how modern technology has helped in the research — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…tracing the edges of the glacier on foot with a <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">handheld GPS (Global Positioning System)</strong>. It is this piece of equipment, relying on <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">satellite transmission</strong>, which makes it possible to see a clear outline…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn D mô tả việc sử dụng hệ thống định vị toàn cầu <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">GPS</strong> và hình ảnh <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">vệ tinh</strong> (satellite imagery) – đây chính là những công nghệ hiện đại (modern technology) giúp ích cho việc nghiên cứu.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1c342de3-bdd1-4d59-b532-63eeb2a668ff', '208a6a07-940a-464d-b5f2-f57d98359169', 'radio', 'Questions 33-36', '', '<p data-path-to-node="3">Choose the correct letter <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="26">A</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="29">B</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="32">C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="37">D</strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="4">Write your answers in boxes 33-36 on your answer sheet</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A   felt relieved that at least some new ice was forming."}, {"option_text": "B   found travelling through the mountains unusually difficult."}, {"option_text": "C   were in competition with another group of researchers."}, {"option_text": "D   were surprised by what had happened to one of the glaciers"}], "question": "During their trip to Rwenzori, Dr Taylor and his team"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A   people’s lives could be put at risk"}, {"option_text": "B   communities may dispute who has access to water."}, {"option_text": "C   more people might move to ecologically important areas"}, {"option_text": "D   water could become unsafe to drink."}], "question": "Dr Taylor says that if the glacier retreats to the main plateau,"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A   reveal the overall pattern of change in glacier size over time"}, {"option_text": "B   prove the glaciers could increase in size in the future."}, {"option_text": "C   show that local factors probably cause glaciers to melt."}, {"option_text": "D   highlight the necessity for the maintenance of accurate records."}], "question": "One of the team’s aims is to"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A   be used to put pressure on governments around the world."}, {"option_text": "B   help prevent serious destruction of similar environments worldwide."}, {"option_text": "C   provide vital information to the local community."}, {"option_text": "D   have an impact on methods of local construction"}], "question": "Dr Taylor says his research is important because it could"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. During their trip to Rwenzori, Dr Taylor and his team — {D} were surprised by what had happened to one of the glaciers</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“When we eventually found it [the marker], we thought, ‘<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">Hey, can this really be true?</strong>‘”</em> (Đoạn A)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu cảm thán “Can this really be true?” (Điều này có thể là thật sao?) thể hiện sự ngạc nhiên tột độ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">surprised</strong>) của cả đội khi thấy sông băng Speke đã lùi xa hơn rất nhiều so với những gì họ tưởng tượng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Dr Taylor says that if the glacier retreats to the main plateau, — {A} people’s lives could be put at risk</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…there is the serious likelihood of a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">catastrophic event</strong>, such as flash flooding where the water would <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">wipe out anything in its way</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn C)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một sự kiện thảm khốc (catastrophic) như lũ quét có thể quét sạch mọi thứ trên đường đi của nó đồng nghĩa với việc đe dọa trực tiếp đến tính mạng con người (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">put at risk</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. One of the team’s aims is to — {A} reveal the overall pattern of change in glacier size over time</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The team also hope to find out if the observed changes are a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">short-term phenomenon or part of a long-term trend</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn E)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc tìm hiểu xem đây là hiện tượng ngắn hạn hay là một xu hướng dài hạn chính là để xác định mô hình thay đổi tổng thể (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">overall pattern of change</strong>) của sông băng theo thời gian.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. Dr Taylor says his research is important because it could — {C} provide vital information to the local community.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Knowledge of these changes will help us to <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">advise people living in affected areas</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn E) và <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">“…research is still vital since what’s happening may have important <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">implications… for the livelihood of the Bakonzo and Baamba communities</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn G)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mục đích quan trọng của nghiên cứu là đưa ra lời khuyên và thông tin thiết yếu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">vital information</strong>) cho cộng đồng địa phương (local community) để họ ứng phó với những thay đổi ảnh hưởng đến cuộc sống của mình.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c53eb11a-311b-464e-9e38-d0d6f2400571', '46549c74-b227-4967-8859-c8f858a000eb', 'matrix', 'Questions 16–20', NULL, '<p>What advice does Peter give about the following objects?</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B or C next to questions 16-20.</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a pair of thick trousers", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a mobile phone", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "a torch", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "something to drink\t", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "a rucksack\t", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Walkers are advised to have this", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Walkers can have this, if they wish", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Walkers are advised NOT to have this", "categoryLetter": "C"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7342c2e1-7554-48ff-9e05-a3abc7bf14ff', '208a6a07-940a-464d-b5f2-f57d98359169', 'radio', 'Questions 37-39', '', '<p>Choose<strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="0"> YES</strong> if the statement <strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="21">agrees</strong> with the opinions of Dr Taylor ,<strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="59">NO</strong> if the statement <strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="79">contradicts</strong> the opinions of Dr Taylor ,<strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="117">NOT GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what Dr Taylor thinks about this</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The speed at which change has occurred in the Speke glacier has increased."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There is evidence that in the past, glaciers may have expanded for a short time."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Governments should give more assistance to people"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. The speed at which change has occurred in the Speke glacier has increased. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“‘This is <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">much faster</strong> than the rates previously recorded. It’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">changing before our eyes</strong>,’ says Dr Richard Taylor…”</em> (Đoạn A)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “much faster than previously recorded” (nhanh hơn nhiều so với trước đây) khẳng định rằng tốc độ biến đổi của sông băng Speke đã tăng lên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">increased</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. There is evidence that in the past, glaciers may have expanded for a short time. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…Taylor maintains there are clear signs of a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">brief expansion</strong> of the glaciers in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">early 1960s</strong> that may have been linked to increased rainfall.”</em> (Đoạn F)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Brief expansion” tương ứng với “expanded for a short time”. Dr. Taylor khẳng định có những dấu hiệu rõ ràng (clear signs = evidence) về việc này đã xảy ra trong quá khứ (những năm 1960).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Governments should give more assistance to people. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…industrialised countries… are still doing <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">very little to slow down</strong> or prevent environmental and ecological damage.”</em> (Đoạn cuối) và <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">“Knowledge… will help us to <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">advise people living in affected areas</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn E)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến việc các nước công nghiệp chưa nỗ lực ngăn chặn thiệt hại, và nhóm nghiên cứu sẽ đưa ra lời khuyên cho người dân. Tuy nhiên, Dr. Taylor <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"168\">không hề đưa ra ý kiến khẳng định</strong> rằng chính phủ “nên hỗ trợ nhiều hơn” (should give more assistance) cho người dân. Chúng ta không tìm thấy quan điểm cụ thể này của ông trong bài.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('33f65a06-b48e-4748-be74-7613a6a4d2d4', '208a6a07-940a-464d-b5f2-f57d98359169', 'radio', 'Question 40', '', '<p data-path-to-node="8">Choose the correct letter <strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="26">A, B, C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="37">D</strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="9">Write your answer in box 40 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A The impact of mountain tourism on Ugandan ecology"}, {"option_text": "B the retreat of Ugandan glaciers and its consequences"}, {"option_text": "C Ugandan communities turn disaster to their advantage"}, {"option_text": "D A revolutionary new approach to glacier research in Uganda"}], "question": "Which of the following is the most suitable title for the text on pages 10 and 11?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Vế đầu: “The retreat of Ugandan glaciers” (Sự tan biến của các sông băng ở Uganda)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Glaciers… are in <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">rapid decline</strong>… one has <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">receded more than 300 metres</strong> in the past decade alone.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“found that in many places the snow was <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">less than 20 centimetres deep</strong>… suggesting that very little ice is currently accumulating.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các đoạn A, B, D, F tập trung mô tả hiện trạng vật lý: băng đang tan nhanh, lùi xa (recede/retreat) và mỏng dần.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Vế sau: “and its consequences” (và những hậu quả/hệ lụy của nó)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…the serious likelihood of a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">catastrophic event</strong>, such as <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">flash flooding</strong> where the water would <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">wipe out anything in its way</strong>…”</em> (Hậu quả về thiên tai).</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…cultural impact is of concern… <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">devastating consequences</strong> for extended families as they are <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">forced to separate</strong>…”</em> (Hậu quả về xã hội/văn hóa).</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…important implications… for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">livelihood</strong> of the Bakonzo and Baamba communities…”</em> (Hậu quả về kinh tế/sinh kế).</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các đoạn C, E, G phân tích sâu về việc biến đổi khí hậu này sẽ ảnh hưởng tiêu cực thế nào đến con người và môi trường sống.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('85c1aa2f-982f-4987-96eb-69e9511ed2ce', '707d2149-fede-4b11-98d0-7336813c5f68', 'matrix', 'Questions 1–5', '', '<p>For which campsite are the following statements true?</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>F</strong>, in boxes 1–5 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "You can pay to hire a tent at this campsite", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "There is a short period each day when you cannot use the showers", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "There is a place on site where you can wash clothes", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "A member of staff is available all day to help visitors", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Visitors to this campsite can go swimming in the winter", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. You can pay to hire a tent at this campsite.</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">(Bạn có thể trả tiền để thuê lều tại khu cắm trại này.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: {D} Bluewater Bay</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the site offers <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">pre-pitched ones that can be rented by the day</strong>.” (Đoạn D)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “pre-pitched ones” (lều đã được dựng sẵn) kết hợp với “rented” (được thuê) hoàn toàn khớp với việc bạn có thể trả tiền để thuê lều thay vì tự mang theo.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. There is a short period each day when you cannot use the showers.</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">(Có một khoảng thời gian ngắn mỗi ngày bạn không thể sử dụng phòng tắm vòi sen.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: {B} Treetops Farm</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the washrooms, which are <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">closed daily for an hour from midday for cleaning</strong>…” (Đoạn B)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản nêu rõ phòng tắm đóng cửa 1 tiếng mỗi ngày từ giữa trưa để dọn dẹp, nghĩa là trong khoảng thời gian đó du khách không thể sử dụng chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. There is a place on site where you can wash clothes.</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">(Có một nơi tại chỗ mà bạn có thể giặt quần áo.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: {C} The Downs</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Facilities on site include a <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">laundry room</strong>…” (Đoạn C)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Laundry room” chính là phòng giặt ủi, nơi du khách có thể giặt quần áo ngay tại khu cắm trại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. A member of staff is available all day to help visitors.</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">(Luôn có một nhân viên túc trực cả ngày để giúp đỡ du khách.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: {F} Rock Harbour</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…there’s always <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">someone in the campsite office from 9 am–9 pm</strong> if you need assistance…” (Đoạn F)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khoảng thời gian từ 9 giờ sáng đến 9 giờ tối (12 tiếng liên tục) được coi là cả ngày làm việc, luôn có người ở văn phòng để hỗ trợ khách hàng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Visitors to this campsite can go swimming in the winter.</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">(Du khách đến khu cắm trại này có thể đi bơi vào mùa đông.)</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: {E} Dean Park</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “This large campsite, which is <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">open all year</strong>… there’s an <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">indoor pool</strong>…” (Đoạn E)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vì khu cắm trại này mở cửa quanh năm (open all year) và có bể bơi trong nhà (indoor pool – không bị ảnh hưởng bởi thời tiết lạnh bên ngoài), du khách hoàn toàn có thể bơi lội vào mùa đông.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ca01e8d5-452f-4f64-b823-203503de9aaa', '53ead48a-2cb0-40b8-9d25-ffc7c9674731', 'radio', 'Questions 40', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "explain the meaning of the manuscript."}, {"content": "determine the true identity of the manuscript''s author."}, {"content": "describe the numerous attempts to decode the manuscript."}, {"content": "identify which research into the manuscript has had the most media coverage."}], "question": "The writer''s main aim in this passage is to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>40. The writer’s main aim in this passage is to</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"36\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>describe the numerous attempts to decode the manuscript.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Toàn bộ bài đọc liệt kê các nỗ lực giải mã qua nhiều thời kỳ và bởi nhiều chuyên gia khác nhau (Newbold, Friedman, Landini, Rugg), chứng minh bản thảo vẫn là một bí ẩn chưa có lời giải.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 3);
