<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling">
<p data-start="2091" data-end="2238" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">Complete the notes below.</p>
<p data-start="2091" data-end="2238" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">Choose <strong data-start="120" data-end="137">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-start">
<div class="flex flex-col text-sm pb-25">
<article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" tabindex="-1" data-turn-id="request-692808c1-5324-8321-9241-cf1905753e43-25" data-testid="conversation-turn-291" data-scroll-anchor="true" data-turn="assistant">
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto pb-10 [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="9768ccd1-a05f-45ad-ac88-5a227db9f565" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling">
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="228" data-end="261"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Creating a successful business</span></strong></p>
<p data-start="263" data-end="358">Statistically, out of all new business ventures, {half} will not survive two years.</p>
<p data-start="360" data-end="386">To avoid this possibility:</p>
<p data-start="388" data-end="558">• set clear targets and<br data-start="411" data-end="414">– arrange frequent {reviews} to ensure these goals are still practicable<br data-start="495" data-end="498">– make sure all {employees} are fully aware of them</p>
<p data-start="560" data-end="702">• ensure the projected cashflow will be adequate to get through the year by<br data-start="635" data-end="638">– noting {dates} for paying tax and other outgoings</p>
<p data-start="704" data-end="921">• select business partners carefully and draw up a document stating<br data-start="771" data-end="774">– their {rights} and what they are responsible for doing in the business<br data-start="856" data-end="859">– the procedure to follow if the business faces difficulties</p>
<p data-start="923" data-end="1076" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">• research the market:<br data-start="945" data-end="948">– find out how your product differs from what {competitors} offer<br data-start="1018" data-end="1021">– consider if the price of the product could be lowered</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</article>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</article>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Statistically, out of all new business ventures, {half} will not survive two years.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Half</strong> of small businesses fail in the first couple of years, according to official reports…” (Đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Statistically” tương ứng với “according to official reports”. Cụm từ “fail” đồng nghĩa với “not survive” (không sống sót/thất bại). Con số được nhắc đến là <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">một nửa (half)</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Arrange frequent {reviews} to ensure these goals are still practicable.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Introduce regular <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">reviews</strong> of these goals and set new ones when appropriate.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Frequent” đồng nghĩa với “regular” (thường xuyên/định kỳ). “Practicable” (khả thi) tương ứng với việc xem xét lại các mục tiêu để điều chỉnh cho phù hợp. Việc cần làm là tổ chức các buổi <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"200\">đánh giá (reviews)</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Make sure all {employees} are fully aware of them.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Most importantly, communicate your mission and goals to your <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">employees</strong>.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc “communicate” (truyền đạt) mục tiêu cho nhân viên giúp họ “fully aware” (nhận thức đầy đủ) về những gì cần làm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. Noting {dates} for paying tax and other outgoings.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Check the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">dates</strong> of major outgoings, such as tax and payments for rent and rates…” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để đảm bảo dòng tiền, chủ doanh nghiệp cần ghi chú/kiểm tra các <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">ngày hạn (dates)</strong> phải chi trả các khoản thuế và chi phí khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. Draw up a document stating their {rights} and what they are responsible for doing…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…put in place an agreement which sets out the <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">rights</strong> and responsibilities of each partner…” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Draw up a document” (soạn thảo một văn bản) đồng nghĩa với “put in place an agreement”. Văn bản này cần ghi rõ <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">quyền lợi (rights)</strong> và trách nhiệm của các bên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Find out how your product differs from what {competitors} offer.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “You should take time to understand who your <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">competitors</strong> are and identify what distinguishes your business from theirs.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Differs from” đồng nghĩa với “distinguishes from” (khác biệt/phân biệt). Bạn cần tìm hiểu xem sản phẩm của mình khác gì so với những gì <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">đối thủ cạnh tranh (competitors)</strong> đang cung cấp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7bcd722d-0e6a-4ed9-a87a-00d90d22edf2', '6c445955-24cb-4b09-a2cf-7fa6cedaf0e1', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–6', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #15191e;">Complete the notes below.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">Write </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">ONE WORD ONLY</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;"> from the passage for each answer.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Dolls</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;"> </span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Earliest known dolls</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">represented religious figures</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">used as toys</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Egypt, 2000 BC</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">bodies were made of wood</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    <span style="font-size: 10pt;">{clay}</span></span></span></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;"> was used for the hair</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Ancient Greece and Rome</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">dolls were given to {goddesses}</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;"> by older girls</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">600 BC</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">realistic dolls had separate clothes and {limbs}</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;"> that could be put in different positions</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">17th and 18th centuries</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">dolls made of {wax}</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;"> became more common</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">moulds made of {plaster}</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">1800s</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">new manufacturing process developed</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">new group of mixtures known as {composition}</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #15191e;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">o<span style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal;">    </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">recipes for these mixtures kept secret</span></span></p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<h3>1. Egypt, 2000 BC… <strong>clay</strong> was used for the hair</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>clay</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “Dolls constructed of flat pieces of wood, painted with various designs, and with ‘hair’ made of <strong>clay</strong>, have often been found in Egyptian graves dating back to 2000 BC.”</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>2. Ancient Greece and Rome… dolls were given to <strong>goddesses</strong> by older girls</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>goddesses</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “Girls from ancient Greece and Rome offered their wooden dolls to <strong>goddesses</strong> after they were too ‘grown-up’ to play with dolls.”</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>3. 600 BC… realistic dolls had separate clothes and <strong>limbs</strong> that could be put in different positions</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>limbs</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “That ideal led to the creation of dolls with <strong>movable limbs</strong> and removable garments, dating back to 600 BC.”</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>4. 17th and 18th centuries… dolls made of <strong>wax</strong> became more common</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>wax</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “In addition to wooden dolls, <strong>wax</strong> dolls grew in popularity in the 17th and 18th centuries.”</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>5. 17th and 18th centuries… moulds made of <strong>plaster</strong></h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>plaster</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “Wax dollmakers would model a doll’s head in wax or clay, and then cover it with <strong>plaster</strong> to create a mould.”</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>6. 1800s… new group of mixtures known as <strong>composition</strong></h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>composition</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “<strong>‘Composition’</strong> is a collective term for mixtures of pulped wood or paper that were used to make doll heads and bodies.”</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('123230ae-aff0-402d-8a65-eefe99a0400d', '28413af2-cd90-4143-8bb1-dbd0d235c224', 'radio', 'Questions 1–6', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information  <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information  <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Rubber plants grow only in certain regions of the world."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Rubber was extracted in Mexico as early as the sixth century"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Rubber from the Castilla elastica plant is of poorer quality than that from the Para plant."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A French mathematician inspired real interest in rubber amongst Europeans."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The process of vulcanisation was discovered by accident."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Imports of crude rubber into Britain fell during the nineteenth century."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1. Rubber plants grow only in certain regions of the world.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: FALSE<br />Dẫn chứng: (Đoạn 1) &#8220;The plants that produce rubber are spread right across the globe, and grow in many different habitats.&#8221;<br />Giải thích: Cây cao su mọc ở khắp thế giới và nhiều môi trường sống khác nhau, mâu thuẫn với nhận định &#8220;chỉ ở một số vùng&#8221;.</p>\n<p>2. Rubber was extracted in Mexico as early as the sixth century.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN<br />Dẫn chứng: (Đoạn 1) &#8220;&#8230;a wall painting dating back to the sixth century depicts a scene of a tributary offering of crude rubber.&#8221;<br />Giải thích: Có bằng chứng về việc dâng cống cao su vào thế kỷ thứ sáu, nhưng không có thông tin xác nhận quá trình chiết xuất (extracted) đã diễn ra từ thời điểm đó.</p>\n<p>3. Rubber from the Castilla elastica plant is of poorer quality than that from the Para plant.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN<br />Dẫn chứng: (Đoạn 1) &#8220;&#8230;must have been made from the indigenous Castilla elastica, as the Para plant now favoured for rubber cultivation does not grow in the Mexican region.&#8221;<br />Giải thích: Văn bản chỉ nói cây Para được &#8220;ưa chuộng&#8221; hơn cho việc canh tác (favoured), nhưng không so sánh chất lượng cao su giữa hai loại cây.</p>\n<p>4. A French mathematician inspired real interest in rubber amongst Europeans.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: TRUE<br />Dẫn chứng: (Đoạn 2) &#8220;However, no real interest in rubber was shown by any European until Charles de la Condamine, a French mathematician, published an account of his journey to South America in 1735.&#8221;<br />Giải thích: Nhà toán học Condamine (French mathematician) đã khơi dậy sự quan tâm thực sự (real interest) của người châu Âu.</p>\n<p>5. The process of vulcanisation was discovered by accident.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN<br />Dẫn chứng: (Đoạn 3) &#8220;Then in 1839 the American Charles Goodyear discovered that it was possible to stabilise rubber by mixing it with sulphur while exposing it to heat&#8230;&#8221;<br />Giải thích: Văn bản mô tả Charles Goodyear đã khám phá ra quá trình này, nhưng không nói rõ đó là do tình cờ (by accident) hay là kết quả của nghiên cứu có chủ ý.</p>\n<p>6. Imports of crude rubber into Britain fell during the nineteenth century.</p>\n<p>Đáp án: FALSE<br />Dẫn chứng: (Đoạn 4) &#8220;The import levels of rubber over the nineteenth century bear witness to its irrepressible rise. In 1830 Britain had imported just 211 kg&#8230; This had risen to 10,000kg in 1857, and by 1874 levels were just under six times as much again.&#8221;<br />Giải thích: Số liệu cho thấy nhập khẩu cao su tăng mạnh (&#8220;irrepressible rise&#8221;) trong thế kỷ 19, mâu thuẫn với việc giảm (&#8220;fell&#8221;).</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('84c60bc7-7847-4bfe-be37-9ff6dad171a8', 'ead23295-d611-4644-9614-519cd7eca090', 'matrix', 'Questions 7-14', '', '<p data-path-to-node="13">Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="26">A-G</strong>, in boxes 7-14 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="14"><strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="0">NB</strong> You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "It enables participants to improve a skill that is not related to sport.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "It is not necessary for participants to bring all their own equipment.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "It is possible to have one-to-one lessons.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Participants are encouraged to explore their surroundings.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Participants should already have some experience of tennis.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "It holds an important event every year.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "People under a certain age are not allowed to participate.", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "At certain times of the year, only group bookings are accepted.", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. It enables participants to improve a skill that is not related to sport. — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…and for overseas students to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">practice their English</strong> too.”</em> (Mackenzie Sport)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Kỹ năng không liên quan đến thể thao ở đây là <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">tiếng Anh</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. It is not necessary for participants to bring all their own equipment. — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It offers… a tennis shop, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">equipment hire</strong>, racquet services…”</em> (El Sol Club)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Có dịch vụ cho thuê thiết bị (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">equipment hire</strong>) đồng nghĩa với việc bạn không nhất thiết phải mang theo đồ của mình.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. It is possible to have one-to-one lessons. — {E}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…but <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"19\">private tuition</strong> is also available for an extra fee.”</em> (Andersons Active Holidays)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Private tuition” chính là học một kèm một (one-to-one).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. Participants are encouraged to explore their surroundings. — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“In your spare time, you will have the chance to <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">go further afield and get to know the local area</strong>.”</em> (Catalonia Leisure)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Get to know the local area” tương ứng với việc khám phá môi trường xung quanh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">explore their surroundings</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Participants should already have some experience of tennis. — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…for young athletes to <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">build on the techniques they have acquired</strong> in tennis…”</em> (Mackenzie Sport)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Build on techniques they have acquired” (phát triển dựa trên kỹ thuật đã có) chứng tỏ người tham gia phải có kinh nghiệm từ trước, không dành cho người mới bắt đầu.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. It holds an important event every year. — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…host to prestigious world-class tennis tournaments like the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">annual Thompson Cup</strong>.”</em> (El Sol Club)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Annual” nghĩa là hàng năm, tương ứng với “every year”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. People under a certain age are not allowed to participate. — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…offered <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">exclusively for adults</strong>.”</em> (William Leisure Hotels)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Chỉ dành cho người lớn” nghĩa là người dưới một độ tuổi nhất định (trẻ em) không được phép tham gia.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. At certain times of the year, only group bookings are accepted. — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“In July and August, the centre is <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">reserved for groups and is closed to individuals</strong>.”</em> (French Break)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tháng 7 và tháng 8 là “thời điểm nhất định trong năm”, lúc đó trung tâm chỉ nhận khách đoàn (groups), không nhận khách lẻ (individuals).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('52410cf0-f96f-4386-9d1d-0cfbd6b12a5b', '95d4b4ef-2803-4f2e-8ceb-ea411b28caae', 'matrix', 'Questions 14 - 17', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, <strong>A-F</strong>, in boxes 14-17 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "an explanation of how water is distributed to plants in the right quantities", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "some examples of current expressions used by Canterbury farmers", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "an argument for increased regulation of agriculture in Canterbury", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "a reference to an agricultural advantage Canterbury has over another part of the world", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. An explanation of how water is distributed to plants in the right quantities — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The crucial piece of equipment… has become the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">high-tech mechanical irrigation system</strong>. <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">Soil moisture monitors</strong> in the earth beneath each irrigation station <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">signal exactly when</strong> they need to turn the water pumps on.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C mô tả hệ thống tưới tiêu cơ giới hóa cao. Việc sử dụng các thiết bị đo độ ẩm đất (soil moisture monitors) giúp báo hiệu chính xác (signal exactly when) lượng nước cần thiết, đảm bảo nước được phân phối đúng khối lượng mà cây/cỏ cần.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Some examples of current expressions used by Canterbury farmers — {A}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Today it is <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">terms such as ‘mechanisation’ ‘intensification’ and ‘conversion’</strong> that you’ll hear on a typical farm.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Expressions” chính là các “terms” (thuật ngữ/cụm từ). Đoạn A liệt kê các từ mà bạn sẽ nghe thấy trên một nông trại điển hình ở Canterbury ngày nay như: cơ giới hóa, thâm canh và chuyển đổi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. An argument for increased regulation of agriculture in Canterbury — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Murray Rogers… insists that the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">only long-term solution is for local government to take control of how much water farmers may take</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Increased regulation” (tăng cường quy định/kiểm soát) tương ứng với việc chính quyền địa phương nắm quyền kiểm soát (government to take control) lượng nước nông dân được phép sử dụng. Murray Rogers cho rằng đây là giải pháp duy nhất để cứu các dòng sông.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. A reference to an agricultural advantage Canterbury has over another part of the world — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“One reason is that the big seed companies located in areas of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">Northern Hemisphere</strong> want to diversify, and because <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">Canterbury is in the Southern Hemisphere, we can grow crops out of season</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lợi thế nông nghiệp (advantage) ở đây là vị trí địa lý ở Nam Bán Cầu, giúp Canterbury có thể trồng cây trái vụ (out of season) so với các công ty ở Bắc Bán Cầu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('20eb9bdd-a68e-4498-b780-a3c71935ef76', 'bb14ea96-6097-4ee4-adae-5ea04fae28d8', 'fillup', 'Questions 7-13', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="33">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 7-13 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="9" data-index-in-node="0">Displaying Art in Melbourne</strong></span></p>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="0">Museum of Art</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="11">
<li>
<p>Professor Frederick McCoy favoured {education} as the main purpose of the museum</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>1861: Sculpture Gallery opened within museum – in restricted {space}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>{cards} provided detail about each museum exhibit</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="0">National Gallery</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="13">
<li>
<p>established 1863</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>gallery received financial support from {government} for new picture</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>style of art – {contemporary}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>admission – {free}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>art that was considered to be educational was moved to a special room in 1870</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>the public was expected to protect the art collection from {theft}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Professor Frederick McCoy favoured {education} as the main purpose of the museum.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Frederick McCoy… suggested placing a museum, focused on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">education</strong> of citizens about art…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Giáo sư McCoy đề xuất thành lập bảo tàng với mục tiêu trọng tâm là giáo dục người dân về nghệ thuật.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. 1861: Sculpture Gallery opened within museum – in restricted {space}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The Sculpture Gallery, although crammed into a limited <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">space</strong> in the Museum of Art…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “restricted” (bị hạn chế) trong đề bài tương ứng với “limited” trong bài đọc. Nơi trưng bày các bức tượng nằm trong một không gian hạn chế.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. {cards} provided detail about each museum exhibit.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Visitors… learned about individual works by reading the written information on <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">cards</strong> accompanying each object.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thông tin chi tiết về từng hiện vật được trình bày trên các tấm thẻ đi kèm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. Gallery received financial support from {government} for new picture.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…in 1863 the <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">government</strong> of Victoria gave one thousand pounds for the creation of a public picture gallery…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Financial support” (hỗ trợ tài chính) chính là số tiền 1000 bảng mà chính phủ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">government</strong>) đã cấp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Style of art – {contemporary}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…creation of a public picture gallery which was to display examples of <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">contemporary</strong> art.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Phong cách nghệ thuật được trưng bày tại phòng triển lãm mới này là nghệ thuật đương đại (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">contemporary</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Admission – {free}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“This new public picture gallery… was <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">free</strong> to visit.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Admission” (phí vào cửa) ở đây là miễn phí (<strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">free</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. The public was expected to protect the art collection from {theft}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…it was decided that the public’s care and attention would safeguard it from <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">theft</strong> and damage.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Protect” đồng nghĩa với “safeguard”. Công chúng được kỳ vọng sẽ giúp bảo vệ các bộ sưu tập khỏi bị trộm cắp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">theft</strong>) và hư hại.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8b6cf322-9fba-41b8-866f-67c44a9ef718', '7ba4b1e4-b981-4e71-95ea-be8199ec2b7a', 'fillup', 'Questions 15-21', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 15-21 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>Employees who miss work <strong data-path-to-node="7,0,0" data-index-in-node="27">without permission</strong> will face {disciplinary action}</p>
<p>If you need to miss all or <strong data-path-to-node="7,1,0" data-index-in-node="30">part</strong> of a working day, you need to complete the {computerized form}</p>
<p>If you are away from work because of a {medical appointment}, you must give your manager one or more days’ advance notice.</p>
<p>The general type of clothing employees must <strong data-path-to-node="7,3,0" data-index-in-node="47">wear</strong> is determined by {department directors}.</p>
<p>Employees working between <strong data-path-to-node="7,4,0" data-index-in-node="29">5 and 6 hours</strong> may skip their meal break if there is {mutual consent}</p>
<p>Only the {police} earn money <strong data-path-to-node="7,5,0" data-index-in-node="64">during</strong> their main break.</p>
<p>Long chats with colleagues lower {departmental efficiency}</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Employees who miss work without permission will face {disciplinary action}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Disciplinary action</strong> will be taken against any employee who fails to report to work as scheduled.”</em> (Mục Hours of Work)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Fails to report to work as scheduled” tương ứng với “miss work without permission”. Khi đó, nhân viên sẽ phải đối mặt với hình thức kỷ luật (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"154\">disciplinary action</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. If you need to miss all or part of a working day, you need to complete the {computerized form}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“All requests for an extended time off… must be made on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">computerized form</strong>…”</em> (Mục Time Off from Work)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khi muốn xin nghỉ (miss all or part of a working day), nhân viên phải hoàn thành mẫu đơn trên máy tính (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">computerized form</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. If you are away from work because of a {medical appointment}, you must give your manager one or more days’ advance notice.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“An employee who will be absent due to a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">medical appointment</strong> is to notify his/her supervisor at least <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">one working day before it</strong>.”</em> (Mục Reporting Absences)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “One or more days’ advance notice” tương ứng với “at least one working day before it”. Lý do nghỉ ở đây là cuộc hẹn khám bệnh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">medical appointment</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. The general type of clothing employees must wear is determined by {department directors}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Department Directors</strong> will establish whether professional, business casual or uniform is the dress standard…”</em> (Mục Appropriate Attire)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “The general type of clothing” chính là “dress standard”. Người quyết định tiêu chuẩn này là các giám đốc bộ phận (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">department directors</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Employees working between 5 and 6 hours may skip their meal break if there is {mutual consent}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The lunch or dinner break may be waived by <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">mutual consent</strong> of both the City and the employee, if the total work period… is no more than six hours.”</em> (Mục Lunch or Dinner Time)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Skip their meal break” tương ứng với “waived”. Việc này chỉ xảy ra khi có sự đồng ý từ cả hai phía (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">mutual consent</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Only the {police} earn money during their main break.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“With the exception of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">police</strong>, the lunch or dinner break is unpaid.”</em> (Mục Lunch or Dinner Time)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Unpaid” là không được trả lương. “With the exception of” (ngoại trừ) cho thấy chỉ có cảnh sát (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">police</strong>) là được trả lương (earn money) trong giờ nghỉ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Long chats with colleagues lower {departmental efficiency}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Departmental efficiency</strong> is greatly <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">reduced</strong> if the activity occurs.”</em> (Mục Excessive Dialogue)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Long chats” tương ứng với “extended conversations”. Việc này làm giảm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">lower/reduced</strong>) hiệu quả của bộ phận (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">departmental efficiency</strong>).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('eaa78cf8-7143-42d4-ab36-634e455f6e16', '7ba4b1e4-b981-4e71-95ea-be8199ec2b7a', 'fillup', 'Questions 22-27', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 22-27 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-path-to-node="14"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="0">Employee Key &amp; Access Card Procedure</strong></span></p>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="15" data-index-in-node="0">Keys &amp; Access Cards</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="16">
<li>
<p>Full-time employees get keys at {plant operations}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Part-time faculty get access cards at the {division office}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Other part-time employees need permission from the {cost center}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="17" data-index-in-node="0">Special Keys</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="18">
<li>
<p>The person in charge of security services <strong data-path-to-node="18,0,0" data-index-in-node="42">has to</strong> agree to any changes in who has master keys.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Keys that open {external doors} require the vice president’s authorisation.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Replacement is free if a key stops working because of {normal wear }</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="19" data-index-in-node="0">Loss or Damages</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="20">
<li>
<p>There is no charge if an access cards is misplaced.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Employee must pay for lost key.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="21" data-index-in-node="0">Leaving</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="22">
<li>
<p>All keys and cards must be turned in before employees get their {final pay}</p>
</li>
</ul>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Full-time employees get keys at {plant operations}</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"> Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“For full time employees, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">keys are obtained through plant operations</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn 1)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bạn điền là “plant operators” (nhân viên vận hành). Tuy nhiên, trong bài đọc ghi rõ là <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">plant operations</strong> (phòng vận hành/bộ phận kỹ thuật).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Part-time faculty get access cards at the {division office}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“For part-time faculty… <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">access cards are obtained through the division office</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 1)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đối với giảng viên bán thời gian, thẻ từ được cấp tại văn phòng khoa/bộ phận (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">division office</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Other part-time employees need permission from the {cost center}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If it becomes necessary for <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">non-faculty part-time employees</strong> [= Other part-time employees] to have a key… the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"123\">cost center</strong> must give <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"145\">authorization</strong> [= permission].”</em> (Đoạn 1)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các nhân viên bán thời gian khác cần sự cho phép (authorization) từ trung tâm chi phí (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">cost center</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. Keys that open {exterior doors} require the vice president’s authorisation.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Keys and/or access cards for <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">exterior door</strong> [hoặc <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">exterior doors</strong>] will be issued with the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">approval</strong> [= authorisation] of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">area vice president</strong>…”</em> (Đoạn 2)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Exterior door” (cửa bên ngoài) đồng nghĩa với “External doors”. Trong bài dùng “exterior door”, bạn điền <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">exterior doors</strong> hoặc <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">external doors</strong> (nếu từ này có trong bài) đều được, nhưng ưu tiên dùng từ gốc trong bài.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. Replacement is free if a key stops working because of {normal wear}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If a key <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">will not function</strong> [= stops working] due to <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">normal wear</strong>, there is <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">no charge to replace it</strong> [= replacement is free].”</em> (Đoạn 3)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nếu chìa khóa hỏng do bị mòn tự nhiên trong quá trình sử dụng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">normal wear</strong>), việc thay thế là miễn phí.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. All keys and cards must be turned in before employees get their {final pay}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“An employee’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">final pay</strong> will be <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">held</strong> until college keys and/or access cards are <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">returned</strong> [= turned in].”</em> (Đoạn 4)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lương cuối cùng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">final pay</strong>) sẽ bị giữ lại cho đến khi nhân viên trả lại (turned in) hết chìa khóa và thẻ.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('46aa8d28-2193-4d83-99b4-a3aacd0c204f', '18318151-caed-4803-a0d4-9381160a306a', 'checkbox', 'Questions 29–30', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>tasks will Charley be responsible for?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. reviewing the final draft", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. collecting basic figures", "correct": true}, {"option": "C. producing the graphics", "correct": false}, {"option": "D. processing the raw data", "correct": false}, {"option": "E. drafting the written sections", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6a1b8dd8-c4fc-4a46-981b-f83c8e1bc8a1', 'a7e03ea1-880d-416a-87c4-2532ddd17c53', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: black;">Complete the notes below.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: black;">Write <strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;"> </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; background: white; text-align: left;" align="center"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-size: 14.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Public Monument Assignment</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Section one</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">First, identify the monument and justify your choice</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Comment on the </span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;"><strong>{success} </strong></span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">of the monument</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Add information about its:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• geographical location</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• </span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;"><strong>{social} </strong></span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">significance</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• historical context</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Illustrate assignment with:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• {plans}</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• photos (with captions)</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">End with: record of architect’s achievements</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Section two: Design and construction</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Include information about</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• The </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: black;">{influence}</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;"> of any particular style on the design</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• The </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: black;">{materials}</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;"> used in construction</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• Specialist </span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;"><strong>{skills} </strong></span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">required</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Section three: Assessment of design</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Content should include:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• personal assessment</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• results of your survey</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Use personal assessment and survey to consider:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• the </span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;"><strong>{reason}</strong></span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;"> for building the monument</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• the monument’s </span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;"><strong>{emotional} </strong></span><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">effect on members of the public</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white; margin: 0in 0in 0in .5in;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">• how well the monument suits its <strong>{environment}</strong></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Remember!</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: #15191e;">Credit given for good </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 150%; mso-ascii-font-family: Calibri; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-hansi-font-family: Calibri; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: Times; color: black;">{analysis}</span></strong></p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2>(Section 4)</h2>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a university lecturer talking to his students about an architectural studies assignment. First you have some time to look at questions 31 to 40 on pages 7 and eight. Now listen carefully and answer questions 31 to forty.</p>\n<p><strong>Lecturer:</strong> Okay, before this morning’s lecture on successful design of public buildings, I want to draw your attention to your next assignment. So your assignment is on public monuments, and by that I mean any structure or statue that is built to remind us of important events or of historic figures.</p>\n<p>The assignment should be divided into three sections. At the beginning of Section 1, you should identify the monument you’re examining and say why you’ve chosen it. Include a comment on whether you think the Monument works—by that I mean its <strong>(31) success</strong>. You may think it’s wonderful, you may think it’s a public eyesore, something that people hate looking at. Next you should also include in this first section information about where the Monument was built, its geographical site, and also a discussion of its <strong>(32) social</strong> importance—how relevant it was for the people of the time. You should also include information on when it was built, its historical background, and make sure you illustrate the assignment appropriately too. I shall expect that <strong>(33) plans</strong> you can find and make sure any photographs you use have captions and are clearly referred to in the text, or they will be meaningless. To end this section, you should include something about the record of the person who designed the Monument, showing how the Monument relates to his or her other work.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Lecturer:</strong> Right, in Section 2 of the assignment, you’ll need to give a detailed account of the design and construction of the Monument. Firstly, I want to read about any particular <strong>(34) influence</strong> you think is apparent in the design. More often than not there will be something in it that links it to an established style, Classical Greek for example, or it may reflect a movement like Bauhaus or Art Nouveau; you decide. Secondly, I want information about the choice of <strong>(35) materials</strong>—not only those which were used, but reasons why they may have been selected from others that were available at the time and in the area where the designer worked. Next I want a mention of any particular <strong>(36) skills</strong> that were necessary in the construction too.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Lecturer:</strong> The third section is the most important one. Here you’ll go into much more critical detail. To add to your own comments, you’ll need to carry out a survey for this section to be as comprehensive and rounded as possible. Ask yourself and others the following questions. Firstly, was the <strong>(37) reason</strong> for erecting the Monument a valid one? For example, was it one that ordinary members of the public, the man or woman on the street, can readily relate to, and did it justify how much public money it cost? Was it a waste, or does it represent a sound cultural investment? Then think about its <strong>(38) emotional</strong> impact. When someone looks at it, how do they feel: angry, sad, indifferent? And don’t forget to consider how well the Monument sits in its <strong>(39) environment</strong>. Does it harmonize with it or does it clash with it, and is that important? Does it add to the effect or take away from it?</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Lecturer:</strong> Right, those guidelines should help. Oh, and remember, it is important to weigh up carefully how to make the maximum impact in this kind of critique within the number of words allowable. You don’t get extra marks for lots of factual information. You get those for a well constructed <strong>(40) analysis</strong>. That’s what counts, and that needs to be based on your personal opinion.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Section 4. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8f54df4d-417b-4151-b20d-0c9d7473161d', 'ea8cb1fc-3da1-41d0-94c7-22a137094ffb', 'matrix', 'Questions 28-36', '', '<p data-path-to-node="4">Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="134">A-G</strong>, in boxes 28-36 on your <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="162">answer sheet</strong>.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="5"><strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="0">NB</strong> you may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "an account of a disease currently under investigation", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "an example of the effect of plant disease on an individual", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "an example of resistance to the clinic''s recommendations", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "details of the clinic''s special privilege", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "an account of an in-country pilot project.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "the range of Dr Boa''s experience of plant disease.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "an account of how a lack of reference sources has been addressed.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "the reasons for the economic importance of a particular plant", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "an example of official support for the clinic''s suggestion.", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. An account of a disease currently under investigation — {E}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Global Plant Clinic scientists <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">suspect</strong> that the peaches are being affected by a deadly organism called a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">phytoplasma</strong>. Samples sent to the clinic are now <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"165\">in the process of being tested</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E kể về việc các nhà khoa học đang nghi ngờ và trong quá trình kiểm tra (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">in the process of being tested</strong> = under investigation) một loại sinh vật gây bệnh trên cây đào.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. An example of the effect of plant disease on an individual — {E}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…on <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"18\">one four-hectare farm</strong>, 75 per cent of this year’s peach crop has been affected… this will make a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">noticeable difference to the farmer’s income</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc đưa ra ví dụ cụ thể về <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">một người nông dân</strong> (individual) sở hữu trang trại 4 héc-ta bị thiệt hại nặng nề về thu nhập.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. An example of resistance to the clinic’s recommendations — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Convincing them to place their trust in an unfamiliar variety has proved <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">challenging</strong>, but despite this <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">local reluctance</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Reluctance” (sự miễn cưỡng/ngại ngần) và “challenging” (thách thức) chính là biểu hiện của sự <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">kháng cự/không sẵn sàng tuân theo</strong> (resistance) các đề xuất của phòng khám.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. Details of the clinic’s special privilege — {A}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…leads a team of scientists which is <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">unique in the world in being licensed from other countries for the purposes of inspection</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc là đội ngũ <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">duy nhất trên thế giới được cấp phép</strong> bởi các quốc gia khác để thực hiện thanh tra là một đặc quyền/quyền hạn đặc biệt (special privilege).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. An account of an in-country pilot project — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“An <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">initial try-out</strong> was held at a busy farmers’ market in <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">Tiraque, Bolivia</strong>… The concept is <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">now being tested</strong> in Bangladesh, Indonesia and Vietnam.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Initial try-out” (lần thử nghiệm đầu tiên) tương ứng với một dự án thí điểm (pilot project) tại một quốc gia cụ thể (Bolivia).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. The range of Dr Boa’s experience of plant disease — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“He has spent a <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">lifetime examining agricultural diseases such as</strong> Frosty Pod Rot, Cassava Mosaic Virus, Witches Broom, Corky Potato, Bunchy Top and Peach Leaf Curl…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc liệt kê hàng loạt các loại bệnh mà ông đã nghiên cứu cả đời cho thấy <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">phạm vi kinh nghiệm</strong> (range of experience) của Dr. Boa.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. An account of how a lack of reference sources has been addressed — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Until recently, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">hunger for knowledge</strong>… was in marked contrast to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">availability of information</strong>… This <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">gap is being bridged</strong> by the Crop Protection Compendium… available online and on CD Rom.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Gap is being bridged” (khoảng cách đang được lấp đầy) chính là cách giải quyết (addressed) vấn đề thiếu hụt nguồn thông tin/tài liệu tham khảo (lack of reference sources).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. The reasons for the economic importance of a particular plant — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“In these coastal communities there are <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">two staples to the economy—fish and coconuts</strong>. Coconuts offer <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">safe water</strong>, the flesh provides <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">oil</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">charcoal</strong> can be produced… and the leaves are used for <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"204\">building shelters</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F liệt kê các giá trị sử dụng của cây dừa (nước, dầu, than, vật liệu xây dựng), giải thích tại sao nó lại quan trọng về kinh tế (economic importance).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. An example of official support for the clinic’s suggestion — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…the <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"19\">Honduran government</strong> is taking the problem seriously, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">actively encouraging</strong> nurseries to plant new seedling varieties.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc chính phủ Honduras tích cực khuyến khích (actively encouraging) nông dân làm theo đề xuất của phòng khám là một ví dụ về sự hỗ trợ từ chính quyền (official support).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f5e718f2-344e-4507-b6da-e0ec64f178f1', 'ea8cb1fc-3da1-41d0-94c7-22a137094ffb', 'fillup', 'Questions 37-40', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 37-40 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>Farmers in tropical countries can send diseased plants to the Global Plant Clinic for {inspection} The Global Plant Clinic is based in the UK but it trains people in other countries to work directly with farmers. The Global Plant Clinic is trying to find ways of improving communications. It recently held a clinic at a {market} in Bolivia. The experiment was so successful that the scheme has been extended to other parts of the world. In addition, the company has produced an electronic {encyclopaedia} for general use Recently the Global Plant Clinic identified the causes of a problem affecting one country’s coconuts and has suggested a solution. Although the farmers there do not want to give up the variety they are used to, their {government} is encouraging them to listen to the clinic’s recommendations.</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Farmers in tropical countries can send diseased plants to the Global Plant Clinic for {inspection}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…leads a team of scientists which is unique in the world in being licensed from other countries for the purposes of <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">inspection</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói về mục đích (for…) của việc gửi cây bị bệnh đến phòng khám. Trong bài, các nhà khoa học được cấp phép để thực hiện việc thanh tra/kiểm tra mẫu bệnh, từ tương ứng chính là <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">inspection</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. It recently held a clinic at a {market} in Bolivia.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“An initial try-out was held at a busy <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">farmers’ market</strong> in Tiraque, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">Bolivia</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Held a clinic” tương ứng với “initial try-out” (thử nghiệm ban đầu). Địa điểm cụ thể được nhắc đến trong văn bản là một khu chợ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"142\">market</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. In addition, the company has produced an electronic {encyclopaedia} for general use.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…the most comprehensive interactive <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">encyclopaedia</strong> on all aspects of pest and disease management, now available <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">online and on CD Rom</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Electronic” (điện tử) trong câu hỏi tương ứng với “online and on CD Rom” (trực tuyến và trên đĩa CD) trong bài. Danh từ chỉ loại tài liệu này là <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">encyclopaedia</strong> (bách khoa toàn thư).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Although the farmers there do not want to give up the variety they are used to, their {government} is encouraging them to listen to the clinic’s recommendations.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…despite this <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">local reluctance</strong> the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">Honduran government</strong> is taking the problem seriously, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">actively encouraging</strong> nurseries to plant new seedling varieties.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Do not want to give up” tương ứng với “local reluctance” (sự ngại ngần/không sẵn lòng của địa phương). Chủ thể thực hiện hành động khuyến khích (encouraging) ở đây chính là chính phủ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">government</strong>).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('94aaeeb2-9c69-4721-b106-4e9034e9cc79', 'c53f3aca-d420-4265-9921-00f2c020d36a', 'matrix', 'Questions 1-8', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="26">A-J</strong>, in boxes 1-8 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "indications that a dog is registered", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "what happens if you fail to register", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "the financial advantage of becoming licensed", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "the procedure for change of dog ownership", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "what the examination consists of", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "where you should register your dog", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "the deadline for registration", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}, {"itemText": "how to prepare for the examination", "correctCategoryLetter": ""}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}, {"categoryText": "I", "categoryLetter": "I"}, {"categoryText": "J", "categoryLetter": "J"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Indications that a dog is registered — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…wearing a current <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">registration label or disc</strong>, or the owner can <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">prove</strong> that the dog is registered.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Indications” (dấu hiệu/chỉ báo) chính là cái nhãn (label) hoặc thẻ tròn (disc) đeo trên cổ chó, hoặc bằng chứng chứng minh đã đăng ký.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. What happens if you fail to register — {J}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…commits an <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">offence</strong> and is liable for a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">fine of up to $1,500</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Fail to register” (không đăng ký) sẽ dẫn đến hậu quả là phạm luật và bị phạt tiền (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">fine</strong>). Đoạn A cũng nhắc đến “penalty” nhưng đoạn J cụ thể hơn về mức phạt và tội danh.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. The financial advantage of becoming licensed — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…issued with a Dog Owner Licence and is entitled to a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">10% reduction in the yearly registration fee</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Financial advantage” (lợi ích tài chính) ở đây chính là việc được giảm 10% phí đăng ký hàng năm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. The procedure for change of dog ownership — {H}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“When a dog has a <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">new owner</strong>… provide <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">written notice</strong> of the details to the authorities within 14 days of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">transfer</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Change of ownership” (thay đổi quyền sở hữu) tương ứng với cụm “new owner” và “transfer”. Thủ tục (procedure) là phải thông báo bằng văn bản trong 14 ngày.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. What the examination consists of — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“This <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"17\">comprises a written section and a multiple choice section</strong>. The pass mark is 75%.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Examination” đồng nghĩa với “Licence Test”. Câu hỏi hỏi bài thi gồm những gì (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">consists of</strong>) và đoạn C liệt kê: phần viết và trắc nghiệm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Where you should register your dog — {E}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Application for registration must be made to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">local Council in the area where the dog is usually kept</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu này chỉ rõ địa điểm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">Where</strong>) là Hội đồng địa phương nơi chó được nuôi dưỡng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. The deadline for registration — {A}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Registration is due on an <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">annual basis</strong>. A <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">penalty is applied for late registration</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Deadline” (hạn chót) được thể hiện qua cụm “due on an annual basis” (hạn hàng năm) và cảnh báo về việc đăng ký muộn (late registration).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. How to prepare for the examination — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Those who wish to be licensed must <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">obtain and study a copy of the Dog Owner Manual</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “How to prepare” (chuẩn bị thế nào) chính là việc đi lấy và học cuốn cẩm nang dành cho chủ chó.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1fbc305c-df3d-42ae-b835-7df875319b1a', 'd1d4a99d-0768-42ea-8fc3-87ca89869e15', 'matrix', 'Questions 1-8', '', '<p data-path-to-node="6">Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="26">A-F</strong> in boxes 1-8 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="7"><strong data-path-to-node="7" data-index-in-node="0">NB</strong> You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "A number of exhibits have been specially prepared for the display.", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Items from the making of a film can be seen here.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Visitors can try to master a practical skill.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "A new opportunity will be offered to visitors at this attraction.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "It is a place where one individual turned a dream into a reality.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "The exhibits reflect the daily existence of ordinary people rather than the rich and famous.", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Exhibits are very close to where they were found.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "There are high points to observe the surrounding countryside from.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. A number of exhibits have been specially prepared for the display. — {F} American Museum in Bath</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…with many pieces having been <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">carefully restored for the occasion</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Carefully restored for the occasion” (được phục chế cẩn thận cho dịp này) chính là việc các hiện vật đã được chuẩn bị đặc biệt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">specially prepared</strong>) cho buổi triển lãm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Items from the making of a film can be seen here. — {E} National Maritime Museum, Greenwich</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“There will be a selection of <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">props from the blockbuster</strong> and an exhibition of <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">costumes</strong> too.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Props” (đạo cụ) và “costumes” (trang phục) từ một bộ phim bom tấn (blockbuster – ở đây là phim Titanic) chính là những món đồ từ quá trình làm phim (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">making of a film</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Visitors can try to master a practical skill. — {C} Historic Dockyard, Chatham</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Learn to make your own rope</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc học cách tự làm dây thừng là một hoạt động trải nghiệm giúp khách tham quan nắm bắt một kỹ năng thực tế (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">practical skill</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. A new opportunity will be offered to visitors at this attraction. — {A} West Cumbria Roman Museum</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…and the chance for the public to walk… along a <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">recently restored section of Roman road</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một đoạn đường La Mã <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">vừa mới được phục hồi</strong> (recently restored) mở ra một cơ hội trải nghiệm mới cho khách tham quan mà trước đây chưa có.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. It is a place where one individual turned a dream into a reality. — {B} Port Sunlight Merseyside</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…discover the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">vision that William Hesketh Lever had</strong> for the village… and <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">how he realised it</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Vision” (tầm nhìn/giấc mơ) của ông William và cách ông “realised it” (thực hiện hóa nó) khớp hoàn toàn với ý tưởng biến giấc mơ thành hiện thực của một cá nhân.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. The exhibits reflect the daily existence of ordinary people rather than the rich and famous. — {F} American Museum in Bath</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Instead of portraying wealthy and influential citizens</strong>, the pieces illustrate the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">lives of everyday Americans</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Everyday Americans” tương ứng với “ordinary people” (người bình thường), còn “wealthy and influential” tương ứng với “rich and famous”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Exhibits are very close to where they were found. — {A} West Cumbria Roman Museum</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…collection of Roman sculptures and artefacts <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">recovered from the nearby Roman fort</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các hiện vật được tìm thấy (recovered) từ pháo đài La Mã <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">ngay gần đó</strong> (nearby).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. There are high points to observe the surrounding countryside from. — {D} Pembroke Castle</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“There are wonderful <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">views from the mighty towers</strong>, which <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">overlook the river and its green bank</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Mighty towers” (các tòa tháp hùng vĩ) là những điểm cao (<strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">high points</strong>) để ngắm nhìn phong cảnh xung quanh (sông và bờ cỏ xanh).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9fd3f209-c00c-467b-affd-a65ae8d6f769', 'd1d4a99d-0768-42ea-8fc3-87ca89869e15', 'radio', 'Questions 9-14', '', '<p data-path-to-node="14,0,0">Choose<strong data-path-to-node="14,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"> TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-path-to-node="14,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information,<strong data-path-to-node="14,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The length of tenancy agreements varies."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "You should consider both work and leisure when selecting a place to live."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "You must provide documentary proof of your finances when you rent a flat."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It is normal for rent to be paid in cash."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The terms of a tenancy agreement are fixed until it expires."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In certain circumstances, a tenant can legally be required to vacate a property without a period of notice."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. The length of tenancy agreements varies. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“A Tenancy Agreement is usually for half a year but will <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">depend on the conditions of the estate Agency</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Depend on the conditions” (phụ thuộc vào điều kiện của đại lý) có nghĩa là độ dài hợp đồng không cố định mà sẽ thay đổi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">varies</strong>) tùy trường hợp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. You should consider both work and leisure when selecting a place to live. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Choose the most suitable area keeping in mind your <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">school, job, interests</strong>, etc.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Job” tương ứng với công việc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">work</strong>), còn “interests” (sở thích/hứng thú) tương ứng với hoạt động giải trí (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">leisure</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. You must provide documentary proof of your finances when you rent a flat. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">evidence of income</strong> (you can show your <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">payslip</strong> or your <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">bank statement</strong>)…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Evidence of income” chính là bằng chứng về tài chính, và các giấy tờ như phiếu lương (payslip) hay sao kê ngân hàng chính là bằng chứng dưới dạng văn bản/tài liệu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"177\">documentary proof</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. It is normal for rent to be paid in cash. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến “rent fee” (phí thuê) và “payment frequency” (tần suất thanh toán: hàng tuần hoặc 2 tuần một lần).</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến phương thức thanh toán là bằng tiền mặt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">cash</strong>), chuyển khoản hay thẻ. Do đó không thể khẳng định đây là việc bình thường (normal) hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. The terms of a tenancy agreement are fixed until it expires. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If the landlord wants to <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">make any alterations to the agreement</strong> for example increase the rent, he/she is obligated to notify the tenant…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói các điều khoản là cố định (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">fixed</strong>) cho đến khi hết hạn. Tuy nhiên, bài đọc cho thấy chủ nhà <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">có quyền thay đổi (alterations)</strong> hợp đồng (ví dụ tăng tiền thuê) miễn là báo trước 60 ngày. Vậy nó không hề “cố định”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. In certain circumstances, a tenant can legally be required to vacate a property without a period of notice. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…in the case of <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">major violations</strong>, there could be <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">no notice period</strong> and the landlord has the right to terminate the agreement <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">immediately</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Major violations” (vi phạm nghiêm trọng) chính là các tình huống cụ thể (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">certain circumstances</strong>). Khi đó, người thuê phải dời đi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"142\">vacate</strong>) ngay lập tức (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">immediately</strong>) mà không cần thời gian báo trước (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"211\">no notice period</strong>).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6f7e5979-1639-44c1-9658-c7b42f258445', 'e8bef659-e65c-4a18-a2f3-a67344f4a3de', 'matrix', 'Questions 28–32', '', '<p>Which paragraph mentions the following?</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, <strong>A–G</strong>, in boxes 28–32 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "how unusual it is for archaeologists and children to have equal responsibilities", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "the relevance of the children’s achievements to a country’s educational requirements", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "the location of the archaeologists’ main project", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a place where a large amount of archaeological material was found", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "a relative’s connection to a local business", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. How unusual it is for archaeologists and children to have equal responsibilities — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “What is <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">less common</strong> is to find primary school pupils working as <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">partners</strong> with an archaeologist. Our project lets primary school children take a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">joint role</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “less common” tương ứng với “unusual”. Việc học sinh làm việc như những “đối tác” (partners) và đóng “vai trò chung” (joint role) với chuyên gia chính là sự phân chia trách nhiệm công bằng (equal responsibilities), một điều hiếm thấy trong các cuộc khai quật thông thường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. The relevance of the children’s achievements to a country’s educational requirements — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “This is a <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">key principle</strong> in the Social Studies section of <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">Scotland’s Curriculum for Excellence</strong>, the national framework for learning…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F nhắc đến “Curriculum for Excellence” (Chương trình giảng dạy xuất sắc) – đây chính là yêu cầu/khung giáo dục quốc gia của Scotland. Những gì trẻ em đạt được từ dự án này hoàn toàn phù hợp với các nguyên tắc cốt lõi của chương trình đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. The location of the archaeologists’ main project — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The main project… focused on the history and archaeology of an abandoned mid-19th-century settlement, located on <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">common ground on the lower slopes of the Bennachie hills</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C cung cấp địa điểm cụ thể của dự án chính: vùng đất chung trên sườn thấp của đồi Bennachie, Aberdeenshire.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. A place where a large amount of archaeological material was found — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “They also discovered the remains of a 19th- or 20th-century <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">midden, or rubbish dump, containing many pieces of broken pottery</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một “midden” hay bãi rác (rubbish dump) là nơi tích tụ một lượng lớn vật liệu khảo cổ (trong trường hợp này là rất nhiều mảnh gốm vỡ). Địa điểm này nằm trong khu rừng nơi các em học sinh tiến hành khai quật.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. A relative’s connection to a local business — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “One of the children discovered that their <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">great-grandfather</strong> had once <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">owned the Seaton workshop</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “great-grandfather” (cụ cố) là một người thân (relative), và “Seaton workshop” là một doanh nghiệp/xưởng sản xuất tại địa phương (local business). Sự kết nối này được phát hiện trong quá trình chuẩn bị triển lãm ở đoạn G.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a95e56e0-d7ce-4a01-91de-952a6b10584e', '58aa559f-e9d6-419c-8d1a-fe6577923667', 'fillup', ' Questions 1–10', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<p class="txt"><em>Complete the notes below. </em></p>
<p class="txt"><em>Write </em><strong><em>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER </em></strong><em>for each answer.</em></p>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;"><strong>SWIMMING LESSONS</strong></p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">Classes available</p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0); width: 100.279%;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 35.5837%;" width="144"> <col style="width: 64.4163%;" width="524"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-row="row-7art">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-7art">
<p><em> Example</em></p>
<p> </p>
<p> Water</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-7art">
<p><em>Answer</em></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><em><u>Babies</u></em></strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p>For babies of three months upwards</p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; width: 100%; height: 122.917px;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 35.5245%;" width="143"> <col style="width: 64.4755%;" width="522"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 61.4583px;" data-row="row-mri5">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-mri5">
<p> Focus</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-mri5">
<p>water familiarisation using {toys}</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 61.4583px;" data-row="row-ctt0">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-ctt0">
<p> Cost</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-ctt0">
<p>£ 3.80 per lesson</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Beginners</strong></p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">For people with no experience of swimming</p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; width: 99.0223%;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 36.3861%;" width="147"> <col style="width: 63.6139%;" width="514"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-row="row-8lhq">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-8lhq">
<p> Focus</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-8lhq">
<p>– {breathing} techniques</p>
<p> </p>
<p>– opening the eyes underwater</p>
<p>– swimming five metres</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Intermediate</strong></p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; width: 99.4413%;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 36.3636%;" width="144"> <col style="width: 63.6364%;" width="504"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-row="row-72yd">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-72yd">
<p> Focus</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-72yd">
<p>– learning main swimming strokes</p>
<p> </p>
<p>– introduction to {diving}</p>
<p>– swimming underwater</p>
<p>– {safety} in the water</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr data-row="row-ro99">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-ro99">
<p> Cost</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-ro99">
<p>£61 per course</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr data-row="row-4j9d">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-4j9d">
<p> Other information:</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-4j9d">
<p>– maximum of 12 pupils per class</p>
<p> </p>
<p>– class is for {adults}</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Advances</strong></p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; width: 99.581%;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 36.0795%;" width="142"> <col style="width: 63.9205%;" width="502"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-row="row-truv">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-truv">
<p> Focus:</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" data-row="row-truv">
<p>– more efficient techniques</p>
<p> </p>
<p>– improving {speed}</p>
<p>– competitions</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Other information</strong></p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Date when Intermediate course begins: Tuesday {January 13th|January 13|13th January|13 January} (need to register soon)</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Time: 7.30 p.m.</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Participants will be provided with a swimming {hat}</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Bring change for the {locker}</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Benefits of swimming</strong></p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Health benefits</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Improvement in {confidence}</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Could save a life</p>
</div>', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a man telephoning to ask for information about swimming lessons. First you have some time to look at questions 1 to 6 on page two. You will see that there is an example that has been done for you. On this occasion only the conversation relating to this will be played first.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Hello City Swim School.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh, Hello. Uh, I wanted to ask about swimming lessons. That’s in a class, not individual, right?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, we do group lessons at various levels. To start off with, we have what we call the Water Babies class.</p>\n<p><strong>(Narrator)</strong> The first class is called Water Babies, so babies has been written in the space. Now we shall begin. You should answer the questions as you listen because you will not hear the recording a second time. Listen carefully and answer questions 1 to six.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Hello City Swim School.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh, Hello. Uh, I wanted to ask about swimming lessons. That’s in a class, not individual, right?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, we do group lessons at various levels. To start off with, we have what we call the Water Babies class. That’s for babies of three months and over.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Really, as young as that?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Yes, that’s really the best time to start.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Right. Well, we do have a baby so I’ll make a note of that. Um, what do they actually do in the lessons?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, the main aim is just to familiarise them with the water, so they feel at ease there. They get the children to enjoy themselves. They have lots of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(1) toys</strong> </span>and things they can use to play with in the water.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Right. And how much do the lessons cost?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> They’re held on Tuesday mornings and each lesson costs £3 80. It’s not really a course as such.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Okay, well, I’ll talk to my wife about that. Uh, but I was actually ringing about lessons for me.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Okay, so are you a beginner?</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Not exactly, but I’m not very good. (ha)</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, the beginner’s classes are really for people who don’t have any experience of swimming. They aim to teach you techniques for <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(2) breathing</strong></span> in the water, and they get you to do things like put your head underwater and open your eyes.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Okay, I can do that.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> And by the end of the course, they aim to have you swimming five metres.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> I think I can probably just about do that.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> OK, so you’d be better in the intermediate class then. That’s where you learn the main swimming strokes—front stroke, back stroke, and so on.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> What about <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(3) diving</strong></span>?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Yes, they’d teach you how to do that, and you’d also do some underwater swimming. Not with a tank or anything.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh no, not scuba, just ordinary underwater swimming.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> And in the intermediate course, you also look at water <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(4) safety</strong></span>. Both in the pool and when swimming in other places.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Okay, well, that sounds the right level for me.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> I think so. How much does that cost?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> <strong>£61</strong> for a course. That’s 10 lessons.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Can you tell me a bit more about the class? How many people would there be in it?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, the intermediate class is usually around 8 to 10. That’s what we aim at, though occasionally it might go up to twelve.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> OK, that sounds quite a reasonable size. Not too many. And the class is for <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(5) adults</strong></span>, is it?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Yes.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> OK. And just out of interest, is there an advanced class?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Yes. They focus on developing more efficient swimming techniques and on working on your <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(6) speed</strong></span>. And they also prepare you for competitive swimming.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Okay. Now I think I’d want to start with the intermediate one, really.</p>\n<p><strong>(Narrator)</strong> Before you hear the rest of the conversation, you have some time to look at questions 7 to 10 on page three. Now listen and answer questions 7 to ten.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Now, is there anything special I need to know?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, the classes are on Tuesdays, and the first lesson is on <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(7) January the thirteenth</strong></span>. So you need to register before then. January the 8th is the latest, but it’s filling up quickly, so I’d do it straight away. You can pick up a form here or get one off the internet.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> And classes are at 7:30 PM. Right. Then I just roll up with my swimming trunks. Do I have to bring my own towel?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> That’s right. We provide all participants with a swimming <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(8) hat</strong></span> though.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh, huh. I don’t usually wear one.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, we do insist on it, actually. It helps the instructor to identify you, apart from anything else. Oh, and don’t forget you need a 20p coin for the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(9) locker</strong></span>.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh, okay. Right. Well, I’ve been meaning to do this for ages. I really need to get some more exercise. And everyone says swimming is good for your health.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Yes, and a lot of people find it improves their <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(10) confidence</strong></span> too. And of course, it could save your life or even someone else’s.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> That’s right. Okay, well, thanks very much.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Goodbye.</p>\n<p><strong>(Narrator)</strong> That is the end of Section 1. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('972a0d0d-90b9-41b1-b3de-5084b0def8e6', '08145313-65e3-4af6-adec-179805bee78c', 'matching', 'Questions 27–30', NULL, '<p>What opinion is expressed about each of the following books?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FOUR </strong>correct answers, <strong>A-G</strong>, next to questions <strong>27-30</strong>.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Books</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Contemporary Farming Manual {G It’s boring.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Running a Small Farm {E It’s inaccurate.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Agriculture and Economics {D It’s essential reading.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Flow to Survive in Farming {B It’s out of date.}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A It’s badly organised."}, {"optionText": "B It’s out of date."}, {"optionText": "C It’s clear."}, {"optionText": "D It’s essential reading."}, {"optionText": "E It’s inaccurate."}, {"optionText": "F It’s well illustrated."}, {"optionText": "G It’s boring."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": null, "correctAnswer": null, "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('063e0fc3-67c1-45dd-83ab-7f7e7ac44a80', '64cb17d1-9c17-472c-978a-47694c707d6e', 'radio', 'Questions 11–15', NULL, '<p style="text-align: left;">Choose the correct answers</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Working for Johnson Jones</strong></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "the pay  "}, {"content": "the staff discount"}, {"content": "the working hours"}], "question": "What does Mark say first attracts people to working for Johnson Jones?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "is focused on long term planning. "}, {"content": "provides excellent customer service. "}, {"content": "offers value for money."}], "question": "Mark says the company is one of the country s most successful retailers because it"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "are better trained."}, {"content": "have better job security."}, {"content": "are given more responsibility."}], "question": "Mark says that because Johnson Jones is a partnership, the staff   "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "8% "}, {"content": "15% "}, {"content": "20%"}], "question": "What is the typical annual bonus that partners receive? "}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "one year."}, {"content": "six months."}, {"content": "three months"}], "question": "To qualify for the leisure and holiday facilities, partners must have worked for the company for   "}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a manager called Mark Bergin who works for a large retailer called Johnson Jones giving a talk at a recruitment fair. First you have some time to look at questions 11 to 15 on page three. Now listen carefully and answer questions 11 to fifteen.</p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> Good Morning. My name is Mark Bergin, I’m a human resources manager at Johnson Jones, and I’m here to tell you about what it’s like working for one of the country’s best employers. The Company has two hundred and twenty five department stores and owns a further one hundred and fifty supermarkets. At our latest store opening, we had over nine thousand applicants for seven hundred and fifty posts. So why do so many people want to work for us?</p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> Well, the first thing that attracts them isn’t so much the salary, although that is a little above average. It’s the idea of getting a massive <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(11) twenty five percent off everything</strong></span> from washing machines to designer handbags. People are prepared to put in long hours to get those kinds of perks.</p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> Johnson Jones has been going strong for nearly one hundred and fifty years and has outlived many of its strongest competitors. Of course, this has something to do with the high quality products that we sell and our motto, “Better for less,” which means customers know they are getting good value for money. But we’re not alone in that. Where we are different is in our approach to making a profit. Other companies think in the short term, whereas we always take a more strategic view, looking three or five years ahead. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(12) (focused on long term planning)</strong></span></p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> The company isn’t owned by a family or shareholders, it’s a partnership, which means it’s owned by its full time employees, who are all partners and have a share in the company. In return for the very generous benefits they get, they’re expected to put in extra effort and <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(13) take an active role in running the company</strong>.</span> This means <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(13) they’re involved</strong></span> in things like making decisions about pension contributions, for example.</p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> Another very attractive reason for working for us is the annual bonus, which we get as a percentage of our salary. Last year it was <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(14) fifteen percent</strong></span>, about two months salary, which is pretty standard. It can go down to eight percent, but that’s unusual, and a couple of times it’s even been above twenty percent.Some people use it to pay off loans; others save it for a deposit on a house.</p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> The most popular benefit for partners are the subsidized holiday centres, which are owned by the company. Once a year partners can book in for up to two weeks. It’s for anyone from cleaners to directors with a minimum of<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(15) three months</strong></span> service. After six months service, partners are entitled to a further subsidy on the cost of their stay.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions 16 to 20 on page four. Now listen and answer questions 16 to twenty.</p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> Let me just give you an idea of what’s on offer at the holiday centres. The Grange which is the largest of the holiday centres is used for conferences by the company and the board of directors always have their annual meeting there. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(16) (C: regularly used by senior management)</strong></span>. It’s all very informal, not like a normal conference centre.</p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> Meadow House is located in Kent, which is famous for its apples and other fruit, and it’s a large country house. What’s unusual about it is that unlike other hotels, you have access to the kitchen, so <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(17) it feels more like staying with a friend (F)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> Coombe Manor is a working farm. There are loads of cows and sheep, none of which actually end up on our supermarket shelves. It’s a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(18) paradise for kids (B)</strong> </span>as there’s plenty of space to run wild and also an indoor pool. You can choose to stay in cottages or camp by the lake.</p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> The Barn is where I recently celebrated my twenty fifth wedding anniversary. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(19) You can rent the whole place out for a large group of up to forty friends (A)</strong></span>. We got all our food delivered from the nearest Johnson’s Jones supermarket, so there was no cooking to be done. Perfect! All that was missing was the spa, which should be opening next year.</p>\n<p><strong>Mark Bergin:</strong> The Stable is often hard to get into because it’s so popular. That’s partly because it’s right on the beach with beautiful sea views and <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(20) only an hour by train from London (G)</strong></span>, ideal for weekends. The company sailing club is located there, which was started by the company’s founder in 1885. So I’m sure you’ll all agree that there really is…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fbd3afbb-aede-4eee-b196-2296ba69baa1', '64cb17d1-9c17-472c-978a-47694c707d6e', 'matching', 'Questions 16–20', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>FIVE </strong>answers from the box, A-G</p>
<p>What information is given about each of the following staff holiday centres?</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Staff Holiday Centres</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Grange {C regularly used by senior management}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Meadow House {F similar to being in someone’s home}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Coombe Manor {B suitable for families with children}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Barn {A available for celebrations and parties}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Stable {G good for short breaks}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A available for celebrations and parties"}, {"optionText": "B suitable for families with children"}, {"optionText": "C regularly used by senior management"}, {"optionText": "D also supplies food to the company’s supermarkets"}, {"optionText": "E spa facilities available"}, {"optionText": "F similar to being in someone’s home"}, {"optionText": "G good for short breaks"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('66aa0d81-b9e4-4908-8b76-8932fa6811db', '6c92dbf3-6522-4468-b3ff-2998ca3890ed', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21 and 22', NULL, '<p>Choose TWO letters, <strong>A-E</strong>.<br />Which <strong>TWO </strong>points did students most frequently make about their musical background before starting a music degree?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. They had already composed music.", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. They had several music qualifications.     ", "correct": false}, {"option": "C. They could play more than one instrument. ", "correct": true}, {"option": "D. They had performed in public.", "correct": true}, {"option": "E. They had had piano lesson", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> So Gareth, we need to organise the findings from our survey on music students for the final presentation.</p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Yes, Lorna, I think we’ve got some very interesting results. Obviously we need to start by saying that we interviewed all the third year students doing a music degree and state the objective of our research project, that is to find out about their attitudes to performing.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> And then we should talk about the students’ musical backgrounds before coming to university. The most important points to make are that although most people have actually composed music during the course, that wasn’t the case when they arrived. And the other thing they had in common was the piano—well they’d had access to a piano at some point, but not all had studied it formally. I thought the most interesting finding was that before coming here, almost everyone was involved in a chamber orchestra or band or singing in a choir, and <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(21/22) playing in front of live audiences (D)</strong></span> but varying enormously in size. Some had only played in tiny venues. I think it’s worth saying that.</p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Okay. And as you might expect from people wanting to study music, they all had a degree of proficiency in <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(21/22) at least two instruments (C)</strong></span> but in most cases one of the instruments was dominant. Right.</p>\n<h3>II. Thái Độ Luyện Tập (Attitudes to Music Practice)</h3>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> We need to talk about attitudes to music practice. The most striking thing here is that even students who you’d expect to practice for hours every day until they get it perfect, say it’s being <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(23/24) terrified of failing (C)</strong></span> that really makes them practice. I know, I’m the same.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> Me too. It’s interesting what was said about practicing alone; some people preferred that because they could focus more on their weak points, but that wasn’t a majority view. What most of them agree on is <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(23/24) that there’s nothing more rewarding than mastering something that’s really hard to learn (E)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> That’s right.</p>\n<h3>III. Lựa Chọn Tác Phẩm &amp; Thái Độ Biểu Diễn (Selecting Pieces &amp; Performing)</h3>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Okay, after that, we should talk a bit about the pieces that students select for assessed performances. There wasn’t quite so much consensus on this, was there? A few people prefer to do pieces which are relatively unknown, while others choose the ones they think will show off their technical ability, but they were in the minority. I think the first thing to say is that a high percentage said they would always try to <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(25/26) learn their pieces by heart (C)</strong></span> because it’s too easy to get lost if you’re trying to read and play when you’re nervous.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> Okay, and quite a lot of them said it helps to<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(25/26) listen to other people playing (A)</strong> </span>your chosen piece—preferably recordings, but even just other students.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> So finally, we need to look at the findings for students’ attitudes to performing. We should point out that this includes informal and formal public performances as well as assessed ones.</p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Yes, that’s important. I expected to find that<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(27) performing solo</strong></span> would make students very nervous, but in fact that isn’t the case. They do find it hugely challenging to start with, but they appreciate the challenge and find it <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(27) stimulating (B)</strong></span>. Right.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> I was surprised by what students said about <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(28) deciding which pieces to perform</strong></span>. I thought they’d all say this was easy. For me, it’s always been quite straightforward: which pieces do I like best and which pieces can I play well? And my repertoire is quite limited anyway.But the most commonly cited answer was that <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(28) it took them ages to make their minds up (E)</strong></span>. I suppose it’s because there are so many factors involved .You need to consider your audience, the venue, the time available to learn the piece—especially if it’s complicated. You need to think about all these things… and you can’t do that in a hurry. That’s true.</p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Then there’s<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(29) performing with musicians from a different genre</strong>,</span> like a classical musician playing with a jazz group. That can really be fun, but most of the music students had <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(29) never even considered it (G)</strong></span>. Right.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> For <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(30) performing with musicians who play the same instrument</strong></span>, almost everyone put the same thing.</p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Yes, they all said it was <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(30) incredibly helpful (A)</strong></span> and not at all intimidating. Which says a lot for the department’s ethos.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> Yes, that’s a good point. OK, what I think we should sort out now is…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a8dd04ec-45fd-4748-bf1f-d59e637b97e0', '6c92dbf3-6522-4468-b3ff-2998ca3890ed', 'checkbox', 'Questions 23 and 24', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, <strong>A-E</strong>.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>points did students most frequently make about music practice?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. They prefer to practise alone.", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. They try to practise every day.", "correct": false}, {"option": "C. They are motivated to practise by fear.", "correct": true}, {"option": "D. They feel they don''t do enough practice.", "correct": false}, {"option": "E. They enjoy the challenge of a difficult piece.", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('49ff4901-9382-420d-96ed-4ecfe5dcd994', '6c92dbf3-6522-4468-b3ff-2998ca3890ed', 'checkbox', 'Questions 25 and 26 ', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, <strong>A-E</strong>.<br />
Which <strong>TWO </strong>points were most frequently made by students about the pieces they select for assessed performances?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. They like to hear others performing the same pieces.", "correct": true}, {"option": "B. They like to choose little-known pieces.", "correct": false}, {"option": "C. They like to play pieces from memory.", "correct": true}, {"option": "D. They like their tutor to choose their pieces", "correct": false}, {"option": "E. They like to choose technically demanding pieces.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d291127c-f323-4e3e-8597-696cc76662f2', 'c53f3aca-d420-4265-9921-00f2c020d36a', 'radio', 'Questions 9-14', '', '<p data-path-to-node="5,0,0">Choose<strong data-path-to-node="5,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"> TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-path-to-node="5,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information,<strong data-path-to-node="5,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "All customers contribute to the maintenance of the system."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Bills are sent to all customers each month."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Homes with high water consumption are billed more often."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Each bill shows the exact amount of water consumed."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Meter reading takes place during the last week of the month."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The person living in the house concerned is always responsible for the bill."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. All customers contribute to the maintenance of the system. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">systems charge</strong> is a yearly charge… covers part of the cost associated with <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">running, maintaining</strong>, replacing and upgrading the water pipe network…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mọi khách hàng đều phải trả “systems charge” (phí hệ thống), và khoản phí này được dùng để bảo trì (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">maintaining</strong>) mạng lưới đường ống. Vậy tất cả khách hàng đều đóng góp vào việc bảo trì hệ thống.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. Bills are sent to all customers each month. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Metrowater bills customers either <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">every three months</strong>, or, for customers who use over 1000 cubic metres per year, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">every month</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Chỉ những khách hàng dùng trên 1000 <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"m^3\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">$m^3$</span>/năm mới nhận hóa đơn hàng tháng. Những người còn lại nhận 3 tháng một lần. Vì vậy, việc nói “tất cả khách hàng nhận hóa đơn mỗi tháng” là sai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Homes with high water consumption are billed more often. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…for customers who use <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">over 1000 cubic metres</strong> per year [high consumption], <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">every month</strong> [billed more often].”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khách hàng dùng nhiều nước (trên 1000 <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"m^3\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">$m^3$</span>) bị tính hóa đơn hàng tháng, tức là thường xuyên hơn so với mức 3 tháng/lần của khách hàng bình thường.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Each bill shows the exact amount of water consumed. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“For these customers [3-month cycle] every <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">second bill</strong> will therefore be an <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">assessed bill</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Với những người nhận hóa đơn 3 tháng/lần, cứ mỗi 2 hóa đơn thì có 1 cái là “tạm tính” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">assessed</strong>) dựa trên ước tính chứ không phải số lượng chính xác (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">exact amount</strong>) từ việc đọc đồng hồ. Do đó, không phải “mỗi” (each) hóa đơn đều hiển thị số thực tế.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Meter reading takes place during the last week of the month. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn cuối nói về việc nhân viên đến đọc số bằng thiết bị cầm tay và mang theo thẻ tên.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến thời gian cụ thể (như “tuần cuối cùng của tháng”) mà việc đọc số diễn ra.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. The person living in the house concerned is always responsible for the bill. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Metrowater has a policy that its <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">contract is with the owner</strong> of the property. If you are <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">renting</strong>… you need to discuss this with your <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">landlord</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Người chịu trách nhiệm pháp lý trên hợp đồng là <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">chủ nhà (owner)</strong>, không nhất thiết là người đang sống ở đó (người thuê nhà – tenant).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bde4f616-9994-43fd-a185-af65da069576', 'f4fcaea8-157d-4b4d-af6c-75fc3ce1a17e', 'radio', 'Questions 17–21', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES</strong> if the statement agrees with the views of the writer. <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts what the writer thinks. <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to know what the writer’s point of view is.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The impressive relics of ancient societies were influenced by Shelley''s sonnet Ozymandias."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There is a widespread belief that environmental issues pose the principal hazard to the contemporary world"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Scientists have reached a consensus about how severe the present ecological concerns are"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The presence of poisonous substances in high concentrations is a relatively modern issue"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "We should reflect cautiously when comparing the past with the present."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>17. The impressive relics of ancient societies were influenced by Shelley&#8217;s sonnet <em>Ozymandias</em>.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) &#8220;&#8230;leaving behind grand ruins <strong>reminiscent of</strong> what poet Shelley described in his sonnet <em>Ozymandias</em>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các tàn tích <strong>gợi nhớ</strong> (reminiscent of) bài thơ, không phải chúng bị bài thơ <strong>ảnh hưởng</strong> (influenced).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>18. There is a widespread belief that environmental issues pose the principal hazard to the contemporary world.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) &#8220;<strong>Currently, many individuals believe that environmental problems eclipse other global threats</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> &#8220;Eclipses other global threats&#8221; (che khuất các mối đe dọa khác) đồng nghĩa với việc là mối nguy hiểm chính (principal hazard).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>19. Scientists have reached a consensus about how severe the present ecological concerns are.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) &#8220;<strong>However, the seriousness of these modern environmental dilemmas is vigorously debated among the scientific community</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các nhà khoa học đang tranh luận sôi nổi (&#8220;vigorously debated&#8221;), tức là chưa đạt được sự đồng thuận (consensus).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>20. The presence of poisonous substances in high concentrations is a relatively modern issue.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) &#8220;&#8230;plus <strong>four new ones</strong>: human-induced climate change, <strong>the accumulation of toxic chemicals</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc tích tụ hóa chất độc hại được liệt kê là một trong bốn yếu tố &#8220;mới&#8221; (new ones) so với các vấn đề cổ đại, ám chỉ đây là vấn đề hiện đại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>21. We should reflect cautiously when comparing the past with the present.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án: YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) &#8220;<strong>Perhaps we can still learn from the past, but only if we carefully contemplate its lessons</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> &#8220;Carefully contemplate&#8221; (cân nhắc cẩn thận) đồng nghĩa với &#8220;reflect cautiously&#8221; (phản ánh thận trọng).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8c3f1a2f-d8e2-4810-85ed-bf9011c9c9ea', 'e7748f69-4c5b-4a75-8770-b62aea4c3860', 'fillup', 'Questions 15-20', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 15-20 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="7" data-index-in-node="0">Acme Insurance Anti-bullying Policy</strong></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="8,0,0"><strong>Definitions</strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="8,0,1,0,0">Bullying:</p>
<ul>
<li data-path-to-node="8,0,1,0,0">
<p>repeated and unreasonable behaviour which creates a {risk} to someone’s health and safety</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="8,1,0">Repeated behaviour</p>
<ul>
<li data-path-to-node="8,1,1,0,0">
<p>persistent misconduct that continues over a long period</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="8,2,0">Unreasonable behaviour</p>
<ul>
<li data-path-to-node="8,2,1,0,0">
<p>conduct that a reasonable person would judge to be outside acceptable limits</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="8,3,0"><strong>Commitment</strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="8,3,1,0,0">Our promise is to:</p>
<ul>
<li data-path-to-node="8,3,1,0,1,0,0">
<p>provide a safe workplace that is not only secure but also {healthy}</p>
</li>
<li data-path-to-node="8,3,1,0,1,1,0">
<p>make sure employees receive the policy during their {induction}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="8,4,0"><strong>Expectations</strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="8,4,1,0,0">What is expected of staff?</p>
<ul>
<li data-path-to-node="8,4,1,0,1,0,0">
<p>to be responsible, polite and unbiased</p>
</li>
<li data-path-to-node="8,4,1,0,1,1,0">
<p>to be prepared to {listen} and react when dealing with other where?</p>
</li>
<li data-path-to-node="8,4,1,0,1,2,0">
<p>in all work related situations and events, including:</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">
<li>
<p>handling {clients}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>attending conferences</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>on social media</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="8,5,0"><strong>Staff action against bullying</strong></p>
<ul>
<li data-path-to-node="8,5,1,0,0">
<p>talk to someone in the organization</p>
</li>
<li data-path-to-node="8,5,1,1,0">
<p>a member of a {union} can talk to their representative</p>
</li>
<li data-path-to-node="8,5,1,2,0">
<p>if you witness unreasonable behavior and inform your manager, it will remain confidential</p>
</li>
</ul>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Bullying: repeated and unreasonable behaviour which creates a {risk} to someone’s health and safety.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Workplace bullying is defined as repeated and unreasonable behaviour… that puts health and safety at <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">risk</strong>.”</em> (Đoạn 1)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “puts… at risk” đồng nghĩa với “creates a risk”. Đối tượng bị đe dọa ở đây là sức khỏe và sự an toàn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Our promise is to: provide a safe workplace that is not only secure but also {healthy}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Acme Insurance Ltd is committed to ensuring a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">safe and healthy</strong> work place…”</em> (Mục Our Commitment)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Our promise” tương ứng với “is committed to” (cam kết). Một nơi làm việc tốt được mô tả là vừa an toàn (safe/secure) vừa lành mạnh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"145\">healthy</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Make sure employees receive the policy during their {induction}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“New workers will be given a copy of this policy at <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">induction</strong> by their manager.”</em> (Mục Our Commitment)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhân viên mới (new workers) sẽ nhận được bản sao chính sách này trong buổi hướng dẫn công việc đầu vào (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">induction</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. What is expected of staff? To be prepared to {listen} and react when dealing with others.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Acme Insurance Ltd expects people to: … <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">listen</strong> and respond to the concerns of others”</em> (Mục Expected Workplace Behaviours)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “React” đồng nghĩa với “respond”. Hành động đi kèm trước đó được kỳ vọng ở nhân viên là lắng nghe (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">listen</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. In all work related situations and events, including: handling {clients}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“during work activities, for example when <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">dealing with clients</strong>“</em> (Mục Expected Workplace Behaviours)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Handling” (xử lý/làm việc với) đồng nghĩa với “dealing with”. Đối tượng mà nhân viên thường xuyên tương tác là khách hàng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">clients</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. A member of a {union} can talk to their representative.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If you belong to a <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">union</strong>, you may also raise any issues with your <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">delegate</strong>.”</em> (Mục What can you do?)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong ngữ cảnh công đoàn, “delegate” (đại biểu) chính là người đại diện (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">representative</strong>). Vì vậy, nếu là thành viên của công đoàn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">union</strong>), bạn có thể nói chuyện với họ.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4e5595b3-ade8-4332-8d90-ac8deb020775', '6c92dbf3-6522-4468-b3ff-2998ca3890ed', 'matching', 'Questions 27 - 30', NULL, '<p>Which comment did most students make about each of the following aspects of performance?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FOUR </strong>answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong>A-G</strong>, next to questions <strong>27- 30</strong>.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p>Performing solo {B. This is difficult but enjoyable}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Deciding which pieces to perform {E. This is time-consuming}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Performing with musicians from a different genre {G. This happens infrequently}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Performing with musicians who play the same instrument {A. This is very beneficial}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. This is very beneficial"}, {"optionText": "B. This is difficult but enjoyable"}, {"optionText": "C. This can affect relationships"}, {"optionText": "D. This makes them very nervous"}, {"optionText": "E. This is time-consuming"}, {"optionText": "F. This is easy"}, {"optionText": "G. This happens infrequently"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Performing solo", "correctAnswer": "B. This is difficult but enjoyable.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Deciding which pieces to perform", "correctAnswer": "E. This is time-consuming.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Performing with musicians from a different genre", "correctAnswer": "G. This happens infrequently.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Performing with musicians who play the same instrument", "correctAnswer": "A. This is very beneficial.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dda25e19-1a53-4d8c-90cf-16ee03f91aac', '3e73f30b-69be-4717-904c-1d5ff1a71760', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>The Africa clawed frog (Xenopus laevis)</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Description</strong></p>
<p>∙ Skin is {smooth} and can vary in colour</p>
<p>∙ Skin is coated with a slippery film for {protection}</p>
<p>∙ Males are {half} the size of females</p>
<p><strong>Habitats</strong></p>
<p>∙ Native to Africa</p>
<p>∙ Live in fresh water – prefered water that is {still}</p>
<p>∙ Can survive high levels of {salt} in water</p>
<p>∙ Cannot survive if there is any metal in water</p>
<p>∙ In drought conditions, may live in {mud} for up to a year</p>
<p><strong>Diet</strong></p>
<p>∙ Eat living or dead water creatures</p>
<p>∙ Find food using their sense of {smell}, their fingers, and their lateral lines</p>
<p>∙ Take food into their mouths using from legs and a {pump} system</p>
<p><strong>Other information</strong></p>
<p>∙ Now popular as a pet in the US</p>
<p>∙ In some US states they are identified as a {pest}</p>
<p>∙ Used in laboratories for developmental research</p>
<p>∙ Mucus from the skin was {antibiotic} properties</p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 4: THE AFRICAN CLAWED FROG (XENOPUS LAEVIS)</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student:</strong> The aim of our study was to look at how naturally occurring substances can be used to treat infections, and we carried out a laboratory study using a frog called the African clawed frog, which has the scientific name <em data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"226\">Xenopus laevis</em>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">So before I describe our study in detail, let me give you a general description about this frog. Like most other frogs, the African clawed frogs have a <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"152\">(31) smooth</strong></span> skin. This is one way you can distinguish them from toads, whose skin is rough, and they can change the colour of their skin to blend in with their surroundings.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">The surface of their skin also has another feature: it’s covered with a layer of mucus. This makes it hard for other creatures to pick them up, and so it provides <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"163\">(32) protection</strong></span> against predators.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">How big are they? Well, it depends on whether they’re male or female, because the females in this case are a whole lot bigger than the males. A large-sized female may be 8 inches long, while the males are about <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"211\">(33) half</strong></span> that size, so they’re pretty small in comparison.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">HABITAT</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student:</strong> What about their natural habitat? As their name suggests, these frogs are native to Africa and they’re found in most parts of Africa south of the Sahara Desert. They make their houses in fresh water, but they’re rarely found in running streams; they like <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"264\">(34) still</strong></span> water.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">As far as the temperature of the water goes, they’re not too fussy; it can be warm or cool. They don’t need to be in water where there are plants growing, and they can live in water that has quite a lot of <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"206\">(35) salt</strong></span> in it, so they can live in brackish areas such as marshes and estuaries.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">However, although they can live in a wide range of conditions, one thing that they are unable to tolerate is even very small traces of metal. That’s immediately fatal to them, and that’s important to remember when they’re being kept in captivity. You’ve got to be careful what kind of tank you use and what you put into the water. In their natural habitat, the frogs normally live in water the whole time, but in unfavorable conditions such as drought, they can burrow into the <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"323\">(36) mud</strong></span> and survive there for up to a year until conditions improve.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">DIET</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student:</strong> As far as their diet is concerned, they’re carnivorous. They eat other creatures they find in the water, and they’re scavengers, which means they’ll eat almost anything living or dead. They’ve got huge appetites.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">Because the water they live in is often quite dirty and visibility is limited, they can’t locate their food using their sense of sight. Instead, they use <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"154\">(37) smell</strong></span>, and also the sensitive fingers on their front legs, and they also have what’s called a lateral line system on the sides of their bodies which is sensitive to vibrations in the water.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">They use their front legs to get the food into their mouths, together with a type of <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">(38) pump</strong></span> arrangement that sucks the food into the mouth and down into their stomach. They don’t have any teeth, so everything just goes straight down.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">OTHER INFORMATION</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Student:</strong> Okay well, although Xenopus started off in Africa, they’re now quite widespread. One of the reasons for this is that a lot of people in the US like keeping them at home as a pet. They’re quite easy to look after and they can live for up to 20 years.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\">But in some states of the US, such as California and Virginia, they have escaped from captivity and are reproducing in the wild and threatening native species there. So they’ve been classified as a <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"198\">(39) pest</strong></span> in these areas.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">But another very important use for the frogs is for research in laboratories. Because the females lay large numbers of eggs and the embryos are transparent, it’s easy to see how they are developing, and so they’re used for research into genetics and development. Also, the slippery mucus that covers their skin acts as an<span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"258\">(40) antibiotic</strong></span>, killing parasites and bacteria. And this is why we chose this frog for our research.So let me describe the aim of our study. We wanted…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0c367b0c-6d85-40ca-b777-f34c74256cd9', 'e8bef659-e65c-4a18-a2f3-a67344f4a3de', 'radio', 'Questions 33–36', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, C or D.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A why objects break up when they are left in woodland"}, {"option_text": "B how modern objects differ from those made in the past"}, {"option_text": "C what happens to a breakable object when it hits the ground"}, {"option_text": "D how long it takes to put broken objects back together again"}], "question": "The experiment described in paragraph A is designed to show"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A They meet with experts at the site"}, {"option_text": "B They talk to people living near the site"}, {"option_text": "C They are given information about the site"}, {"option_text": "D They engage in simple activities at the site"}], "question": "In paragraph B, what does the writer say most schoolchildren do when they visit archaeological sites?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A had read about in history lessons"}, {"option_text": "B discovered using written documents"}, {"option_text": "C had heard about from local people"}, {"option_text": "D remembered from previous activities"}], "question": "The water mill is an example of something that the children"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A She recognised the pattern on some pottery"}, {"option_text": "B She showed the children how to decorate pottery"}, {"option_text": "C She regularly cooked using a pot that was very old"}, {"option_text": "D She offered the children an old pot that she had kept"}], "question": "What does the writer say about one child’s grandmother?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. The experiment described in paragraph A is designed to show — {C} what happens to a breakable object when it hits the ground.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…instructing community archaeologist Colin Shepherd when to <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">drop a china mug on the floor</strong> so that they can <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">see how it breaks on impact</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thí nghiệm thả rơi chiếc cốc sứ xuống sàn nhằm giúp các em quan sát trực tiếp cách vật thể vỡ ra khi va chạm (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">on impact</em>), từ đó hiểu hơn về tình trạng của các mảnh vỡ khảo cổ tìm thấy trong thực tế.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. In paragraph B, what does the writer say most schoolchildren do when they visit archaeological sites? — {D} They engage in simple activities at the site.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “They are normally given <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">straightforward tasks like washing and sorting finds</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả chỉ ra rằng thông thường trẻ em chỉ được giao những công việc đơn giản (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">straightforward tasks</em>) như rửa và phân loại các hiện vật tìm thấy, thay vì được tham gia sâu vào quá trình nghiên cứu như dự án này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. The water mill is an example of something that the children — {B} discovered using written documents.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Taking on the role of historians and <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">working with primary source materials, such as maps, census returns and tax payments</strong>, the children were able to develop their own lines of enquiry. Their research <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"212\">suggested that there had been a water mill in the area</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhờ nghiên cứu các tài liệu gốc (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">primary source materials</em>) như bản đồ, dữ liệu điều tra dân số và biên lai thuế, các em đã suy luận ra sự tồn tại của một chiếc cối xay nước trước khi tiến hành khai quật để tìm chứng cứ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. What does the writer say about one child’s grandmother? — {A} She recognised the pattern on some pottery.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The grandmother of another child recounted her memories of making oatmeal porridge in a small bowl <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">decorated with the same floral design as a pottery piece on display</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bà của một em học sinh đã nhận ra hoa văn trên mảnh gốm đang trưng bày (hoa văn hình hoa – <em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">floral design</em>) vì nó giống hệt với chiếc bát mà bà từng dùng để nấu cháo yến mạch trong ký ức của mình.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ecffd729-661c-47cd-9ec0-c7f6327c8b88', 'e8bef659-e65c-4a18-a2f3-a67344f4a3de', 'fillup', 'Questions 37–39', '<p data-start="90" data-end="117">Complete the summary below.</p>
<p data-start="119" data-end="174">Choose <strong data-start="126" data-end="143">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="238" data-end="271"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-start="242" data-end="271">The children’s exhibition</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="273" data-end="604">The writer helped the children to exhibit what they had found. First the children went to look at the exhibits on display at the {university} museum. After that, they placed their discoveries on a timeline to show the age of the objects. Then they created a {game} for visitors to test their knowledge of the items.</p>
<p data-start="606" data-end="861">The children were allowed to use a cabinet that belonged to the museum to display all the things they had found. One piece of pottery was recognised as being made at a particular {workshop}. It was placed next to an unbroken example of the pottery.</p>
<p data-start="863" data-end="974">The quality of the display area raised the status of the children’s exhibition for everyone who went to see it.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Đáp án: {university}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Following a visit to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">university</strong> to see the museum there, the children produced a timeline…” (Đoạn E)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trước khi bắt đầu làm triển lãm, các em học sinh đã có một chuyến tham quan đến bảo tàng nằm trong trường <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">đại học (university)</strong> để học hỏi cách trưng bày.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Đáp án: {game}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “They went on to invent a ‘guess the object’ <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">game</strong> to engage visitors in their discoveries.” (Đoạn E)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để thu hút người xem triển lãm và giúp họ kiểm tra kiến thức về các hiện vật (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">test their knowledge</em>), các em đã tự tạo ra một trò chơi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">game</strong>) có tên là “đoán đồ vật”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Đáp án: {workshop}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “During the identification of the pottery pieces, one was identified as coming from the distinctive Seaton <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">workshop</strong> in Aberdeen…” (Đoạn E)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một mảnh gốm vỡ tìm thấy đã được xác định là sản phẩm của một xưởng sản xuất (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">workshop</strong>) cụ thể mang tên Seaton tại Aberdeen. Để tăng tính chuyên nghiệp, một mẫu vật còn nguyên vẹn từ xưởng này đã được mượn từ bảo tàng để đặt cạnh mảnh vỡ của các em.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f1a5f106-3fcb-43cd-8cb8-dcba339c6c37', 'e8167d81-68e7-442d-9f95-a1cbb0b016e1', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>HOLIDAY RENTAL</strong></span></p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" border="1"><colgroup> <col width="169"> <col width="490"> <col width="100"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-row="row-ghhr">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-ghhr">
<p> Example</p>
<p> Owners’ name:</p>
</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-ghhr">
<p> Answer</p>
<p> Carol and Dave Marriott</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Aster cottage</strong></p>
<p>– Available for week beginning {September 14th | September 14 | 14th September | 14 September}</p>
<p>– Cost for the week: $ {835}</p>
<p><strong>Periwinkle Cottage</strong></p>
<p>– The same price as Aster Cottage last year</p>
<p>– Part of a building that was first used as a {school}</p>
<p>– The living room leads out to the {deck}</p>
<p>– View of the {river} from the bedroom</p>
<p>– Bring our own {towels}</p>
<p>– Doesn’t have a {garage}</p>
<p><strong>The town</strong></p>
<p>– The owner recommends the {Chinese} restaurant</p>
<p>– The town is well-known for this antique shapes</p>
<p><strong>Payment</strong></p>
<p>– Deposit: $ {200}</p>
<p>– Deadline for final payment: final day of {July}</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a woman who wants to rent a vacation cottage telephoning the owner. First you have some time to look at questions one to seven on page two. You will see that there is an example that has been done for you. On this occasion only the conversation relating to this will be played first.</p>\n<p><strong>Owner:</strong> Hello.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Oh, Hello. I’m calling about a vacation rental. The name I’ve been given is Carol Marriott.</p>\n<p><strong>Owner:</strong> I’m <strong>Dave</strong>, Carol’s husband, we own it together.</p>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><strong>Customer</strong>:</strong> Oh right. Uh, well, some friends of ours rented Aster Cottage from you for a week by the ocean last summer and they recommended it to us. My husband and I would like to rent it in the fall for a week.</p>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dave:</strong> Okay. When exactly?</p>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><strong>Customer</strong>:</strong> Um, we&#8217;re looking at the week beginning September 21st, if it&#8217;s available.</p>\n<p><strong><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dave</strong>:</strong> Let me check, uh… hmm, no I’m sorry it’s already booked that week. You could have it the previous week, from the<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(1) fourteenth</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Well, we could manage that week if we change a couple of arrangements. Um, how much would it cost?</p>\n<p><strong><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dave</strong>:</strong> That would be <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(2) Eight Hundred and thirty five dollars</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Ah, that’s rather more than we wanted to pay, I’m afraid. Uh, we were hoping to pay closer to Seven Hundred and ninety dollars, which our friends paid last year.</p>\n<p> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dave:</strong>We also have a slightly smaller cottage called Periwinkle cottage.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Excuse me, um, how do you spell the name?</p>\n<p><strong>Dave</strong>:P-e-r-i W-i-n-k-l-e, Periwinkle. It’s available the week you want it and it’s the exact same price that your friends paid last year.I take it you want a place that sleeps just two people, like Astor cottage?</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong>  Um, yes, is it near Astor cottage?</p>\n<p><strong>Dave:</strong>Yeah, it’s right across the street.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> And what’s this cottage like?</p>\n<p><strong>Dave:</strong>Well, it’s a part of a historic building that was originally a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(3) school</strong></span> a hundred years ago. It was converted into a post office around nineteen fifty, then later on the post office moved and the building was divided to make two cottages.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong>So is it on several floors?</p>\n<p><strong>Dave:</strong> No, it’s all on one floor. There’s a large living room, a kitchen that’s really well equipped, a bedroom and a bathroom with a tub and a shower.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Oh, very nice.</p>\n<p><strong>Dave: </strong>From the living room you can go out onto the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(4) deck</strong></span>, which is a great place to have your meals when the weather is nice.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> That sounds fantastic. Can you see the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(5) river</strong></span> that flows through the town from the cottage?</p>\n<p><strong>Dave:</strong>You sure can. It’s close by, you can see it from the bedroom.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Okay. Uh, would we need to bring anything? Bedding, say?</p>\n<p><strong>Dave:</strong>That’s provided, but we make a small charge for<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(6) towels</strong></span> unless you bring your own, of course.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Oh, okay, I’ll do that. Uh, because we’ll be driving, there’ll be plenty of room in the car for things like that. Oh, that reminds me, is there a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(7) garage</strong></span> that we can use?</p>\n<p><strong>Dave:</strong> I’m afraid there isn’t one, uh, but you can usually get a parking spot on the street right in front of the cottage. </p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong>No problem,We probably won’t use the car much while we’re there anyway, we like to go for walks.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the conversation, you have some time to look at questions eight to ten on page two. Now listen and answer questions eight to ten.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Oh, and what about the town itself? Are there any restaurants in the neighborhood?</p>\n<p><strong>Dave:</strong> There are a few, all within walking distance. A lot of people like the fish restaurant, but in my opinion, the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(8) Chinese</strong></span> restaurant has got to be the best for miles around.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> That’s good to know. We might end up eating out every evening.</p>\n<p><strong>Dave</strong>: Well, why not?</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong>Our friend said the town is pretty famous fo<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">r antique</span> stores.</p>\n<p><strong>Dave:</strong>That’s right, there’s a whole bunch of them, at least ten on the main street.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong>Marvelous. Okay, I’d like to make the booking please.</p>\n<p><strong>Dave:</strong> Great. We ask for a deposit of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(9) two hundred dollars</strong></span>, and final payment at least six weeks before your stay. But we’ll be away ourselves for much of August, so let’s say no later than the last day of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(10) July</strong></span>. Is that okay with you?</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Fine.</p>\n<p><strong>Dave:</strong>Okay, then let me give you our details so you can send the deposit.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4910af9f-9264-47c1-9a1f-b4a99d7329f1', '2a64c3b0-92cc-47db-9fc6-aa53bf5413f3', 'radio', 'Questions 11-14', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": " A. in the sports ground.  "}, {"content": "B. by the river.  "}, {"content": "C. in the shopping centre."}], "question": "On the day of the race the speaker recommends parking:"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. the shirt or singlet.  "}, {"content": "B. a shoe.  "}, {"content": "C. the wristband."}], "question": "The timing chip should be attached to:    "}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. yellow.  "}, {"content": "B. red.  "}, {"content": "C. purple."}], "question": "Which group will run first?    "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. giving first aid."}, {"content": "B. handing out water. "}, {"content": "C. starting the race."}], "question": "The race organisers still need to find volunteers to help with:       "}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a coordinator talking to volunteer helpers before a race involving a large number of people. First you have some time to look at questions 11 to 14 on page three. Now listen carefully and answer questions 11 to fourteen.</p>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Thank you for all volunteering to help us with the Bridge to Brisbane fun run. The purpose of this meeting is to give you some information about your duties on race day. Some of you are asking about where you can park on the day. Unfortunately, some of the usual places down by the river for example, will be out of bounds because we’ll need extra space for emergency vehicles. Probably the best option is the Jack Gray Sports field in Barker Street <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(11) (A)</strong>.</span> Although the closest parking lot is the Metro Shopping Complex, I would advise you not to park there as they tend to tow away people who aren’t customers.</p>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> At the start line, most of you will be checking that runners have the necessary gear, especially their electronic timing chip, the race number and the identity wristband. Make sure that the number is attached to the front of the running shirt or singlet, not the back. The timing chip which records the runner’s time needs to be clipped onto <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(12) one of their shoes (B)</strong>,</span> and check that they are wearing their wristband.</p>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Some of you will be responsible for organizing the starting groups. It’s very important that runners start in a particular order. There is a system of color codes. The red group are walkers and people with baby strollers. The purple group are runners that expect to finish in at less than one hour, and the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(13) yellow group (A)</strong></span> are our Elite athletes. We’d like them to start the race, and we’d like the other groups to follow after that, with the red group and the strollers at the very back. This is for their own safety.</p>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Now we are still short on volunteers for the race day, so if you have any friends or family members who might be interested, please let us know. We’re probably okay for people to help with the start, but we’ll still desperately need volunteers along the race course to <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(14) distribute water bottles to the runners (B)</strong></span>. A few of you have offered to help with First Aid, but the good people of Saint John’s Ambulance have donated their services, so that won’t be necessary.</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions fifteen to twenty on page four. Now listen and answer questions fifteen to twenty.</p>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Now I’ll show you the layout of the Race Village, which is where the race ends. Can you all see the map? If you look at the bottom right hand side, you’ll see where the runners enter the Village next to the corporate catering section. As you continue along the course, you’ll see the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(15) stage (F)</strong></span> on your right. That’s where the winners will receive their medals. Now can you all see the finish line near the center? After they finish the race, the runners can take one of two paths, it doesn’t matter which one, to get their finishers T shirts from the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(16) T-shirt stand (A)</strong> </span>at the end of those paths.</p>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Many of you will be stationed there at the end of the race. After they finish, the runners will also want their belongings, and all bags are kept in the building <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(17) bag collection area (B)</strong></span> on Bowen Road. It’s quite close to the exit in the top left hand corner of your map.</p>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Now some of you will have an important role working in the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(18) information centre (H)</strong></span>. That’s the building in the center of the map, not far from the finish line, it’s just below it on your map. And one other thing, can you all please remind the runners to enter in the prize draw for the new car. The entry box is between the shade tents and the corporate catering buildings <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(19) (G)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Coordinator:</strong> Okay, let’s see now what else do I need to point out. Ah yes, the runners are always thirsty, and the main <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(20) water station (I)</strong></span> in the Village is just beside the third exit through to Gregory Terrace. Can you see it there, to the left of the corporate catering area? So everyone please direct the race finishers there to get their free bottle water <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(20) (I)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of section two. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n"}]', 0);
SET session_replication_role = DEFAULT;
